v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

185static OOMErrorCallback g_oom_error_callback = nullptr;
186
187static ScriptOrigin GetScriptOriginForScript(
188 i::Isolate* i_isolate, i::DirectHandle<i::Script> script) {
189 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> scriptName(script->GetNameOrSourceURL(),
190 i_isolate);
191 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> source_map_url(script->source_mapping_url(),
192 i_isolate);
193 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> host_defined_options(
194 script->host_defined_options(), i_isolate);
195 ScriptOriginOptions options(script->origin_options());
196 bool is_wasm = false;
197#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
198 is_wasm = script->type() == i::Script::Type::kWasm;
199#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
200 v8::ScriptOrigin origin(
201 Utils::ToLocal(scriptName), script->line_offset(),
202 script->column_offset(), options.IsSharedCrossOrigin(), script->id(),
203 Utils::ToLocal(source_map_url), options.IsOpaque(), is_wasm,
204 options.IsModule(), Utils::ToLocal(host_defined_options));
205 return origin;
206}

208// --- E x c e p t i o n B e h a v i o r ---
209
210// When V8 cannot allocate memory FatalProcessOutOfMemory is called. The default
211// OOM error handler is called and execution is stopped.
212void i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(i::Isolate* i_isolate, const char* location,
213 const OOMDetails& details) {
214 char last_few_messages[Heap::kTraceRingBufferSize + 1];
215 char js_stacktrace[Heap::kStacktraceBufferSize + 1];
216 i::HeapStats heap_stats;
217
218 if (i_isolate == nullptr) {
219 i_isolate = Isolate::TryGetCurrent();
220 }
221
222 if (i_isolate == nullptr) {
223 // If the Isolate is not available for the current thread we cannot retrieve
224 // memory information from the Isolate. Write easy-to-recognize values on
225 // the stack.
226 memset(last_few_messages, 0x0BADC0DE, Heap::kTraceRingBufferSize + 1);
227 memset(js_stacktrace, 0x0BADC0DE, Heap::kStacktraceBufferSize + 1);
228 memset(&heap_stats, 0xBADC0DE, sizeof(heap_stats));
229 // Give the embedder a chance to handle the condition. If it doesn't,
230 // just crash.
231 if (g_oom_error_callback) g_oom_error_callback(location, details);
232 base::FatalOOM(base::OOMType::kProcess, location);
233 UNREACHABLE();
234 }
235
236 memset(last_few_messages, 0, Heap::kTraceRingBufferSize + 1);
237 memset(js_stacktrace, 0, Heap::kStacktraceBufferSize + 1);
238
239 intptr_t start_marker;
240 heap_stats.start_marker = &start_marker;
241 size_t ro_space_size;
242 heap_stats.ro_space_size = &ro_space_size;
243 size_t ro_space_capacity;
244 heap_stats.ro_space_capacity = &ro_space_capacity;
245 size_t new_space_size;
246 heap_stats.new_space_size = &new_space_size;
247 size_t new_space_capacity;
248 heap_stats.new_space_capacity = &new_space_capacity;
249 size_t old_space_size;
250 heap_stats.old_space_size = &old_space_size;
251 size_t old_space_capacity;
252 heap_stats.old_space_capacity = &old_space_capacity;
253 size_t code_space_size;
254 heap_stats.code_space_size = &code_space_size;
255 size_t code_space_capacity;
256 heap_stats.code_space_capacity = &code_space_capacity;
257 size_t map_space_size;
258 heap_stats.map_space_size = &map_space_size;
259 size_t map_space_capacity;
260 heap_stats.map_space_capacity = &map_space_capacity;
261 size_t lo_space_size;
262 heap_stats.lo_space_size = &lo_space_size;
263 size_t code_lo_space_size;
264 heap_stats.code_lo_space_size = &code_lo_space_size;
265 size_t global_handle_count;
266 heap_stats.global_handle_count = &global_handle_count;
267 size_t weak_global_handle_count;
268 heap_stats.weak_global_handle_count = &weak_global_handle_count;
269 size_t pending_global_handle_count;
270 heap_stats.pending_global_handle_count = &pending_global_handle_count;
271 size_t near_death_global_handle_count;
272 heap_stats.near_death_global_handle_count = &near_death_global_handle_count;
273 size_t free_global_handle_count;
274 heap_stats.free_global_handle_count = &free_global_handle_count;
275 size_t memory_allocator_size;
276 heap_stats.memory_allocator_size = &memory_allocator_size;
277 size_t memory_allocator_capacity;
278 heap_stats.memory_allocator_capacity = &memory_allocator_capacity;
279 size_t malloced_memory;
280 heap_stats.malloced_memory = &malloced_memory;
281 size_t malloced_peak_memory;
282 heap_stats.malloced_peak_memory = &malloced_peak_memory;
283 size_t objects_per_type[LAST_TYPE + 1] = {0};
284 heap_stats.objects_per_type = objects_per_type;
285 size_t size_per_type[LAST_TYPE + 1] = {0};
286 heap_stats.size_per_type = size_per_type;
287 int os_error;
288 heap_stats.os_error = &os_error;
289 heap_stats.last_few_messages = last_few_messages;
290 heap_stats.js_stacktrace = js_stacktrace;
291 intptr_t end_marker;
292 heap_stats.end_marker = &end_marker;
293 if (i_isolate->heap()->HasBeenSetUp()) {
294 // BUG(1718): Don't use the take_snapshot since we don't support
295 // HeapObjectIterator here without doing a special GC.
296 i_isolate->heap()->RecordStats(&heap_stats, false);
297 if (!v8_flags.correctness_fuzzer_suppressions) {
298 char* first_newline = strchr(last_few_messages, '\n');
299 if (first_newline == nullptr || first_newline[1] == '\0')
300 first_newline = last_few_messages;
301 base::OS::PrintError("\n<--- Last few GCs --->\n%s\n", first_newline);
302 base::OS::PrintError("\n<--- JS stacktrace --->\n%s\n", js_stacktrace);
303 }
304 }
305 Utils::ReportOOMFailure(i_isolate, location, details);
306 if (g_oom_error_callback) g_oom_error_callback(location, details);
307 // If the fatal error handler returns, we stop execution.
308 FATAL("API fatal error handler returned after process out of memory");
309}
310
311void i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(i::Isolate* i_isolate, const char* location,
312 const char* detail) {
313 OOMDetails details;
314 details.detail = detail;
315 FatalProcessOutOfMemory(i_isolate, location, details);
316}
317
318void Utils::ReportApiFailure(const char* location, const char* message) {
319 i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::TryGetCurrent();
320 FatalErrorCallback callback = nullptr;
321 if (i_isolate != nullptr) {
322 callback = i_isolate->exception_behavior();
323 }
324 if (callback == nullptr) {
325 base::OS::PrintError("\n#\n# Fatal error in %s\n# %s\n#\n\n", location,
326 message);
327 base::OS::Abort();
328 } else {
329 callback(location, message);
330 }
331 i_isolate->SignalFatalError();
332}
333
334void Utils::ReportOOMFailure(i::Isolate* i_isolate, const char* location,
335 const OOMDetails& details) {
336 if (auto oom_callback = i_isolate->oom_behavior()) {
337 oom_callback(location, details);
338 } else {
339 // TODO(wfh): Remove this fallback once Blink is setting OOM handler. See
340 // crbug.com/614440.
341 FatalErrorCallback fatal_callback = i_isolate->exception_behavior();
342 if (fatal_callback == nullptr) {
343 base::OOMType type = details.is_heap_oom ? base::OOMType::kJavaScript
344 : base::OOMType::kProcess;
345 base::FatalOOM(type, location);
346 UNREACHABLE();
347 } else {
348 fatal_callback(location,
349 details.is_heap_oom
350 ? "Allocation failed - JavaScript heap out of memory"
351 : "Allocation failed - process out of memory");
352 }
353 }
354 i_isolate->SignalFatalError();
355}

357void V8::SetSnapshotDataBlob(StartupData* snapshot_blob) {
358 i::V8::SetSnapshotBlob(snapshot_blob);
359}

363#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
364// ArrayBufferAllocator to use when the sandbox is enabled in which case all
365// ArrayBuffer backing stores need to be allocated inside the sandbox.
366class ArrayBufferAllocator : public v8::ArrayBuffer::Allocator {
367 public:
368 void* Allocate(size_t length) override {
369 return allocator_->Allocate(length);
370 }
371
372 void* AllocateUninitialized(size_t length) override {
373 return Allocate(length);
374 }
375
376 void Free(void* data, size_t length) override {
377 return allocator_->Free(data);
378 }
379
380 private:
381 // Backend allocator shared by all ArrayBufferAllocator instances. This way,
382 // there is a single region of virtual address space reserved inside the
383 // sandbox from which all ArrayBufferAllocators allocate their memory,
384 // instead of each allocator creating their own region, which may cause
385 // address space exhaustion inside the sandbox.
386 // TODO(chromium:1340224): replace this with a more efficient allocator.
387 class BackendAllocator {
388 public:
389 BackendAllocator() {
390 CHECK(i::Sandbox::current()->is_initialized());
391 VirtualAddressSpace* vas = i::Sandbox::current()->address_space();
392 constexpr size_t max_backing_memory_size = 8ULL * i::GB;
393 constexpr size_t min_backing_memory_size = 1ULL * i::GB;
394 size_t backing_memory_size = max_backing_memory_size;
395 i::Address backing_memory_base = 0;
396 while (!backing_memory_base &&
397 backing_memory_size >= min_backing_memory_size) {
398 backing_memory_base = vas->AllocatePages(
399 VirtualAddressSpace::kNoHint, backing_memory_size, kChunkSize,
400 PagePermissions::kNoAccess);
401 if (!backing_memory_base) {
402 backing_memory_size /= 2;
403 }
404 }
405 if (!backing_memory_base) {
406 i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(
407 nullptr,
408 "Could not reserve backing memory for ArrayBufferAllocators");
409 }
410 DCHECK(IsAligned(backing_memory_base, kChunkSize));
411
412 region_alloc_ = std::make_unique<base::RegionAllocator>(
413 backing_memory_base, backing_memory_size, kAllocationGranularity);
414 end_of_accessible_region_ = region_alloc_->begin();
415
416 // Install an on-merge callback to discard or decommit unused pages.
417 region_alloc_->set_on_merge_callback([this](i::Address start,
418 size_t size) {
419 mutex_.AssertHeld();
420 VirtualAddressSpace* vas = i::Sandbox::current()->address_space();
421 i::Address end = start + size;
422 if (end == region_alloc_->end() &&
423 start <= end_of_accessible_region_ - kChunkSize) {
424 // Can shrink the accessible region.
425 i::Address new_end_of_accessible_region = RoundUp(start, kChunkSize);
426 size_t size =
427 end_of_accessible_region_ - new_end_of_accessible_region;
428 if (!vas->DecommitPages(new_end_of_accessible_region, size)) {
429 i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(
430 nullptr, "ArrayBufferAllocator::BackendAllocator()");
431 }
432 end_of_accessible_region_ = new_end_of_accessible_region;
433 } else if (size >= 2 * kChunkSize) {
434 // Can discard pages. The pages stay accessible, so the size of the
435 // accessible region doesn't change.
436 i::Address chunk_start = RoundUp(start, kChunkSize);
437 i::Address chunk_end = RoundDown(start + size, kChunkSize);
438 if (!vas->DiscardSystemPages(chunk_start, chunk_end - chunk_start)) {
439 i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(
440 nullptr, "ArrayBufferAllocator::BackendAllocator()");
441 }
442 }
443 });
444 }
445
446 ~BackendAllocator() {
447 // The sandbox may already have been torn down, in which case there's no
448 // need to free any memory.
449 if (i::Sandbox::current()->is_initialized()) {
450 VirtualAddressSpace* vas = i::Sandbox::current()->address_space();
451 vas->FreePages(region_alloc_->begin(), region_alloc_->size());
452 }
453 }
454
455 BackendAllocator(const BackendAllocator&) = delete;
456 BackendAllocator& operator=(const BackendAllocator&) = delete;
457
458 void* Allocate(size_t length) {
459 base::SpinningMutexGuard guard(&mutex_);
460
461 length = RoundUp(length, kAllocationGranularity);
462 i::Address region = region_alloc_->AllocateRegion(length);
463 if (region == base::RegionAllocator::kAllocationFailure) return nullptr;
464
465 // Check if the memory is inside the accessible region. If not, grow it.
466 i::Address end = region + length;
467 size_t length_to_memset = length;
468 if (end > end_of_accessible_region_) {
469 VirtualAddressSpace* vas = i::Sandbox::current()->address_space();
470 i::Address new_end_of_accessible_region = RoundUp(end, kChunkSize);
471 size_t size = new_end_of_accessible_region - end_of_accessible_region_;
472 if (!vas->SetPagePermissions(end_of_accessible_region_, size,
473 PagePermissions::kReadWrite)) {
474 if (!region_alloc_->FreeRegion(region)) {
475 i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(
476 nullptr, "ArrayBufferAllocator::BackendAllocator::Allocate()");
477 }
478 return nullptr;
479 }
480
481 // The pages that were inaccessible are guaranteed to be zeroed, so only
482 // memset until the previous end of the accessible region.
483 length_to_memset = end_of_accessible_region_ - region;
484 end_of_accessible_region_ = new_end_of_accessible_region;
485 }
486
487 void* mem = reinterpret_cast<void*>(region);
488 memset(mem, 0, length_to_memset);
489 return mem;
490 }
491
492 void Free(void* data) {
493 base::SpinningMutexGuard guard(&mutex_);
494 region_alloc_->FreeRegion(reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(data));
495 }
496
497 static BackendAllocator* SharedInstance() {
498 static base::LeakyObject<BackendAllocator> instance;
499 return instance.get();
500 }
501
502 private:
503 // Use a region allocator with a "page size" of 128 bytes as a reasonable
504 // compromise between the number of regions it has to manage and the amount
505 // of memory wasted due to rounding allocation sizes up to the page size.
506 static constexpr size_t kAllocationGranularity = 128;
507 // The backing memory's accessible region is grown in chunks of this size.
508 static constexpr size_t kChunkSize = 1 * i::MB;
509
510 std::unique_ptr<base::RegionAllocator> region_alloc_;
511 size_t end_of_accessible_region_;
512 base::SpinningMutex mutex_;
513 };
514
515 BackendAllocator* allocator_ = BackendAllocator::SharedInstance();
516};
517
518#else
519
520class ArrayBufferAllocator : public v8::ArrayBuffer::Allocator {
521 public:
522 void* Allocate(size_t length) override { return base::Calloc(length, 1); }
523
524 void* AllocateUninitialized(size_t length) override {
525 return base::Malloc(length);
526 }
527
528 void Free(void* data, size_t) override { base::Free(data); }
529
530 void* Reallocate(void* data, size_t old_length, size_t new_length) override {
531 void* new_data = base::Realloc(data, new_length);
532 if (new_length > old_length) {
533 memset(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(new_data) + old_length, 0,
534 new_length - old_length);
535 }
536 return new_data;
537 }
538};
539#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX

638RegisteredExtension* RegisteredExtension::first_extension_ = nullptr;
639
640RegisteredExtension::RegisteredExtension(std::unique_ptr<Extension> extension)
641 : extension_(std::move(extension)) {}
642
643// static
644void RegisteredExtension::Register(std::unique_ptr<Extension> extension) {
645 RegisteredExtension* new_extension =
646 new RegisteredExtension(std::move(extension));
647 new_extension->next_ = first_extension_;
648 first_extension_ = new_extension;
649}
650
651// static
652void RegisteredExtension::UnregisterAll() {
653 RegisteredExtension* re = first_extension_;
654 while (re != nullptr) {
655 RegisteredExtension* next = re->next();
656 delete re;
657 re = next;
658 }
659 first_extension_ = nullptr;
660}

662namespace {
663class ExtensionResource : public String::ExternalOneByteStringResource {
664 public:
665 ExtensionResource() : data_(nullptr), length_(0) {}
666 ExtensionResource(const char* data, size_t length)
667 : data_(data), length_(length) {}
668 const char* data() const override { return data_; }
669 size_t length() const override { return length_; }
670 void Dispose() override {}
671
672 private:
673 const char* data_;
674 size_t length_;
675};
676} // anonymous namespace
677
678void RegisterExtension(std::unique_ptr<Extension> extension) {
679 RegisteredExtension::Register(std::move(extension));
680}
681
682Extension::Extension(const char* name, const char* source, int dep_count,
683 const char** deps, int source_length)
684 : name_(name),
685 source_length_(source_length >= 0
686 ? source_length
687 : (source ? static_cast<int>(strlen(source)) : 0)),
688 dep_count_(dep_count),
689 deps_(deps),
690 auto_enable_(false) {
691 source_ = new ExtensionResource(source, source_length_);
692 CHECK(source != nullptr || source_length_ == 0);
693}
694
695void ResourceConstraints::ConfigureDefaultsFromHeapSize(
696 size_t initial_heap_size_in_bytes, size_t maximum_heap_size_in_bytes) {
697 CHECK_LE(initial_heap_size_in_bytes, maximum_heap_size_in_bytes);
698 if (maximum_heap_size_in_bytes == 0) {
699 return;
700 }
701 size_t young_generation, old_generation;
702 i::Heap::GenerationSizesFromHeapSize(maximum_heap_size_in_bytes,
703 &young_generation, &old_generation);
704 set_max_young_generation_size_in_bytes(
705 std::max(young_generation, i::Heap::MinYoungGenerationSize()));
706 set_max_old_generation_size_in_bytes(
707 std::max(old_generation, i::Heap::MinOldGenerationSize()));
708 if (initial_heap_size_in_bytes > 0) {
709 i::Heap::GenerationSizesFromHeapSize(initial_heap_size_in_bytes,
710 &young_generation, &old_generation);
711 // We do not set lower bounds for the initial sizes.
712 set_initial_young_generation_size_in_bytes(young_generation);
713 set_initial_old_generation_size_in_bytes(old_generation);
714 }
715 if (i::kPlatformRequiresCodeRange) {
716 set_code_range_size_in_bytes(
717 std::min(i::kMaximalCodeRangeSize, maximum_heap_size_in_bytes));
718 }
719}
720
721void ResourceConstraints::ConfigureDefaults(uint64_t physical_memory,
722 uint64_t virtual_memory_limit) {
723 size_t heap_size = i::Heap::HeapSizeFromPhysicalMemory(physical_memory);
724 size_t young_generation, old_generation;
725 i::Heap::GenerationSizesFromHeapSize(heap_size, &young_generation,
726 &old_generation);
727 set_max_young_generation_size_in_bytes(young_generation);
728 set_max_old_generation_size_in_bytes(old_generation);
729
730 if (virtual_memory_limit > 0 && i::kPlatformRequiresCodeRange) {
731 set_code_range_size_in_bytes(
732 std::min(i::kMaximalCodeRangeSize,
733 static_cast<size_t>(virtual_memory_limit / 8)));
734 }
735}

780namespace {
781constexpr InstanceTypeChecker::TaggedAddressRange kStringMapRange =
782 *InstanceTypeChecker::UniqueMapRangeOfInstanceTypeRange(FIRST_STRING_TYPE,
783 LAST_STRING_TYPE);
784} // namespace
785
786#define EXPORTED_STATIC_ROOTS_PTR_MAPPING(V) \
787 V(UndefinedValue, i::StaticReadOnlyRoot::kUndefinedValue) \
788 V(NullValue, i::StaticReadOnlyRoot::kNullValue) \
789 V(TrueValue, i::StaticReadOnlyRoot::kTrueValue) \
790 V(FalseValue, i::StaticReadOnlyRoot::kFalseValue) \
791 V(EmptyString, i::StaticReadOnlyRoot::kempty_string) \
792 V(TheHoleValue, i::StaticReadOnlyRoot::kTheHoleValue) \
793 V(StringMapLowerBound, kStringMapRange.first) \
794 V(StringMapUpperBound, kStringMapRange.second)
795
796static_assert(std::is_same_v<Internals::Tagged_t, Tagged_t>);
797// Ensure they have the correct value.
798#define CHECK_STATIC_ROOT(name, value) \
799 static_assert(Internals::StaticReadOnlyRoot::k##name == value);
800EXPORTED_STATIC_ROOTS_PTR_MAPPING(CHECK_STATIC_ROOT)
801#undef CHECK_STATIC_ROOT
802#define PLUS_ONE(...) +1
803static constexpr int kNumberOfCheckedStaticRoots =
804 0 EXPORTED_STATIC_ROOTS_PTR_MAPPING(PLUS_ONE);
805#undef EXPORTED_STATIC_ROOTS_PTR_MAPPING
806static_assert(Internals::StaticReadOnlyRoot::kNumberOfExportedStaticRoots ==
807 kNumberOfCheckedStaticRoots);
808
809#endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL

815i::Address* GlobalizeReference(i::Isolate* i_isolate, i::Address value) {
816 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, Persistent, New);

820 if (i::v8_flags.verify_heap) {
821 i::Object::ObjectVerify(i::Tagged<i::Object>(value), i_isolate);
822 }

824 return result.location();
825}

883
884HandleScope::HandleScope(Isolate* v8_isolate) { Initialize(v8_isolate); }
885
886void HandleScope::Initialize(Isolate* v8_isolate) {
887 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
888 // We do not want to check the correct usage of the Locker class all over the
889 // place, so we do it only here: Without a HandleScope, an embedder can do
890 // almost nothing, so it is enough to check in this central place.
891 // We make an exception if the serializer is enabled, which means that the
892 // Isolate is exclusively used to create a snapshot.
893 Utils::ApiCheck(!i_isolate->was_locker_ever_used() ||
894 i_isolate->thread_manager()->IsLockedByCurrentThread() ||
895 i_isolate->serializer_enabled(),
896 "HandleScope::HandleScope",
897 "Entering the V8 API without proper locking in place");
898 i::HandleScopeData* current = i_isolate->handle_scope_data();
899 i_isolate_ = i_isolate;
900 prev_next_ = current->next;
901 prev_limit_ = current->limit;
902 current->level++;
903#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
904 scope_level_ = current->level;
905#endif
906}
907
908HandleScope::~HandleScope() {
909#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
910 CHECK_EQ(scope_level_, i_isolate_->handle_scope_data()->level);
911#endif
912 i::HandleScope::CloseScope(i_isolate_, prev_next_, prev_limit_);
913}
914
915void* HandleScope::operator new(size_t) { base::OS::Abort(); }
916void* HandleScope::operator new[](size_t) { base::OS::Abort(); }
917void HandleScope::operator delete(void*, size_t) { base::OS::Abort(); }
918void HandleScope::operator delete[](void*, size_t) { base::OS::Abort(); }
919
920int HandleScope::NumberOfHandles(Isolate* v8_isolate) {
921 return i::HandleScope::NumberOfHandles(
922 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate));
923}

925i::Address* HandleScope::CreateHandle(i::Isolate* i_isolate, i::Address value) {

927}

937
938EscapableHandleScopeBase::EscapableHandleScopeBase(Isolate* v8_isolate) {
939 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
940 escape_slot_ = CreateHandle(
941 i_isolate, i::ReadOnlyRoots(i_isolate).the_hole_value().ptr());
942 Initialize(v8_isolate);
943}
944
945i::Address* EscapableHandleScopeBase::EscapeSlot(i::Address* escape_value) {
946 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(escape_value);
947 DCHECK(i::IsTheHole(i::Tagged<i::Object>(*escape_slot_),
948 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(GetIsolate())));
949 *escape_slot_ = *escape_value;
950 return escape_slot_;
951}
952
953SealHandleScope::SealHandleScope(Isolate* v8_isolate)
954 : i_isolate_(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate)) {
955 i::HandleScopeData* current = i_isolate_->handle_scope_data();
956 prev_limit_ = current->limit;
957 current->limit = current->next;
958 prev_sealed_level_ = current->sealed_level;
959 current->sealed_level = current->level;
960}
961
962SealHandleScope::~SealHandleScope() {
963 i::HandleScopeData* current = i_isolate_->handle_scope_data();
964 DCHECK_EQ(current->next, current->limit);
965 current->limit = prev_limit_;
966 DCHECK_EQ(current->level, current->sealed_level);
967 current->sealed_level = prev_sealed_level_;
968}

970bool Data::IsModule() const {
971 return i::IsModule(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this));
972}
973bool Data::IsFixedArray() const {
974 return i::IsFixedArray(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this));
975}
976
977bool Data::IsValue() const {
978 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
979 i::Tagged<i::Object> self = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
980 if (i::IsSmi(self)) return true;
981 i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> heap_object = i::Cast<i::HeapObject>(self);
982 DCHECK(!IsTheHole(heap_object));
983 if (i::IsSymbol(heap_object)) {
984 return !i::Cast<i::Symbol>(heap_object)->is_private();
985 }
986 return IsPrimitiveHeapObject(heap_object) || IsJSReceiver(heap_object);
987}
988
989bool Data::IsPrivate() const {
990 return i::IsPrivateSymbol(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this));
991}

993bool Data::IsObjectTemplate() const {
994 return i::IsObjectTemplateInfo(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this));
995}
996
997bool Data::IsFunctionTemplate() const {
998 return i::IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this));
999}
1000
1001bool Data::IsContext() const {
1002 return i::IsContext(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this));
1003}
1004
1005void Context::Enter() {
1006 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1007 i::Tagged<i::NativeContext> env = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
1008 i::Isolate* i_isolate = env->GetIsolate();
1009 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1010 i::HandleScopeImplementer* impl = i_isolate->handle_scope_implementer();
1011 impl->EnterContext(env);
1012 impl->SaveContext(i_isolate->context());
1013 i_isolate->set_context(env);
1014}
1015
1016void Context::Exit() {
1017 auto env = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
1018 i::Isolate* i_isolate = env->GetIsolate();
1019 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1020 i::HandleScopeImplementer* impl = i_isolate->handle_scope_implementer();
1021 if (!Utils::ApiCheck(impl->LastEnteredContextWas(*env), "v8::Context::Exit()",
1022 "Cannot exit non-entered context")) {
1023 return;
1024 }
1025 impl->LeaveContext();
1026 i_isolate->set_context(impl->RestoreContext());
1027}
1028
1029Context::BackupIncumbentScope::BackupIncumbentScope(
1030 Local<Context> backup_incumbent_context)
1031 : backup_incumbent_context_(backup_incumbent_context) {
1032 DCHECK(!backup_incumbent_context_.IsEmpty());
1033
1034 auto env = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*backup_incumbent_context_);
1035 i::Isolate* i_isolate = env->GetIsolate();
1036
1037 js_stack_comparable_address_ =
1038 i::SimulatorStack::RegisterJSStackComparableAddress(i_isolate);
1039
1040 prev_ = i_isolate->top_backup_incumbent_scope();
1041 i_isolate->set_top_backup_incumbent_scope(this);
1042 // Enforce slow incumbent computation in order to make it find this
1043 // BackupIncumbentScope.
1044 i_isolate->clear_topmost_script_having_context();
1045}
1046
1047Context::BackupIncumbentScope::~BackupIncumbentScope() {
1048 auto env = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*backup_incumbent_context_);
1049 i::Isolate* i_isolate = env->GetIsolate();
1050
1051 i::SimulatorStack::UnregisterJSStackComparableAddress(i_isolate);
1052
1053 i_isolate->set_top_backup_incumbent_scope(prev_);
1054}
1055
1056static_assert(i::Internals::kEmbedderDataSlotSize == i::kEmbedderDataSlotSize);
1057static_assert(i::Internals::kEmbedderDataSlotExternalPointerOffset ==
1058 i::EmbedderDataSlot::kExternalPointerOffset);
1059
1060static i::DirectHandle<i::EmbedderDataArray> EmbedderDataFor(
1061 Context* context, int index, bool can_grow, const char* location) {
1062 auto env = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(context);
1063 i::Isolate* i_isolate = env->GetIsolate();
1064 DCHECK_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1065 bool ok = Utils::ApiCheck(i::IsNativeContext(*env), location,
1066 "Not a native context") &&
1067 Utils::ApiCheck(index >= 0, location, "Negative index");
1068 if (!ok) return {};
1069 // TODO(ishell): remove cast once embedder_data slot has a proper type.
1070 i::DirectHandle<i::EmbedderDataArray> data(
1071 i::Cast<i::EmbedderDataArray>(env->embedder_data()), i_isolate);
1072 if (index < data->length()) return data;
1073 if (!Utils::ApiCheck(can_grow && index < i::EmbedderDataArray::kMaxLength,
1074 location, "Index too large")) {
1075 return {};
1076 }
1077 data = i::EmbedderDataArray::EnsureCapacity(i_isolate, data, index);
1078 env->set_embedder_data(*data);
1079 return data;
1080}
1081
1082uint32_t Context::GetNumberOfEmbedderDataFields() {
1083 auto context = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
1084 DCHECK_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(context->GetIsolate());
1085 Utils::ApiCheck(i::IsNativeContext(*context),
1086 "Context::GetNumberOfEmbedderDataFields",
1087 "Not a native context");
1088 // TODO(ishell): remove cast once embedder_data slot has a proper type.
1089 return static_cast<uint32_t>(
1090 i::Cast<i::EmbedderDataArray>(context->embedder_data())->length());
1091}
1092
1093v8::Local<v8::Value> Context::SlowGetEmbedderData(int index) {
1094 const char* location = "v8::Context::GetEmbedderData()";
1095 i::DirectHandle<i::EmbedderDataArray> data =
1096 EmbedderDataFor(this, index, false, location);
1097 if (data.is_null()) return Local<Value>();
1098 i::Isolate* i_isolate = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this)->GetIsolate();
1099 return Utils::ToLocal(i::direct_handle(
1100 i::EmbedderDataSlot(*data, index).load_tagged(), i_isolate));
1101}
1102
1103void Context::SetEmbedderData(int index, v8::Local<Value> value) {
1104 const char* location = "v8::Context::SetEmbedderData()";
1105 i::DirectHandle<i::EmbedderDataArray> data =
1106 EmbedderDataFor(this, index, true, location);
1107 if (data.is_null()) return;
1108 auto val = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
1109 i::EmbedderDataSlot::store_tagged(*data, index, *val);
1110 DCHECK_EQ(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value),
1111 *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*GetEmbedderData(index)));
1112}
1113
1114void* Context::SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(int index) {
1115 const char* location = "v8::Context::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData()";
1116 i::Isolate* i_isolate = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this)->GetIsolate();
1117 i::HandleScope handle_scope(i_isolate);
1118 i::DirectHandle<i::EmbedderDataArray> data =
1119 EmbedderDataFor(this, index, false, location);
1120 if (data.is_null()) return nullptr;
1121 void* result;
1122 Utils::ApiCheck(
1123 i::EmbedderDataSlot(*data, index).ToAlignedPointer(i_isolate, &result),
1124 location, "Pointer is not aligned");
1125 return result;
1126}
1127
1128void Context::SetAlignedPointerInEmbedderData(int index, void* value) {
1129 const char* location = "v8::Context::SetAlignedPointerInEmbedderData()";
1130 i::Isolate* i_isolate = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this)->GetIsolate();
1131 i::DirectHandle<i::EmbedderDataArray> data =
1132 EmbedderDataFor(this, index, true, location);
1133 bool ok = i::EmbedderDataSlot(*data, index)
1134 .store_aligned_pointer(i_isolate, *data, value);
1135 Utils::ApiCheck(ok, location, "Pointer is not aligned");
1136 DCHECK_EQ(value, GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index));
1137}
1138
1139// --- T e m p l a t e ---
1140
1141void Template::Set(v8::Local<Name> name, v8::Local<Data> value,
1142 v8::PropertyAttribute attribute) {
1143 auto templ = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
1144 i::Isolate* i_isolate = templ->GetIsolateChecked();
1145 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1146 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
1147 auto value_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
1148
1149 Utils::ApiCheck(!IsJSReceiver(*value_obj) || IsTemplateInfo(*value_obj),
1150 "v8::Template::Set",
1151 "Invalid value, must be a primitive or a Template");
1152
1153 // The template cache only performs shallow clones, if we set an
1154 // ObjectTemplate as a property value then we can not cache the receiver
1155 // template.
1156 if (i::IsObjectTemplateInfo(*value_obj)) {
1157 templ->set_serial_number(i::TemplateInfo::kDoNotCache);
1158 }
1159
1160 i::ApiNatives::AddDataProperty(i_isolate, templ,
1161 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*name), value_obj,
1162 static_cast<i::PropertyAttributes>(attribute));
1163}
1164
1165void Template::SetPrivate(v8::Local<Private> name, v8::Local<Data> value,
1166 v8::PropertyAttribute attribute) {
1167 Set(Local<Name>::Cast(name), value, attribute);
1168}
1169
1170void Template::SetAccessorProperty(v8::Local<v8::Name> name,
1171 v8::Local<FunctionTemplate> getter,
1172 v8::Local<FunctionTemplate> setter,
1173 v8::PropertyAttribute attribute) {
1174 auto templ = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
1175 auto i_isolate = templ->GetIsolateChecked();
1176 i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> i_getter;
1177 if (!getter.IsEmpty()) {
1178 i_getter = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*getter);
1179 Utils::ApiCheck(i_getter->has_callback(i_isolate),
1180 "v8::Template::SetAccessorProperty",
1181 "Getter must have a call handler");
1182 }
1183 i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> i_setter;
1184 if (!setter.IsEmpty()) {
1185 i_setter = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*setter);
1186 Utils::ApiCheck(i_setter->has_callback(i_isolate),
1187 "v8::Template::SetAccessorProperty",
1188 "Setter must have a call handler");
1189 }
1190 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1191 DCHECK(!name.IsEmpty());
1192 DCHECK(!getter.IsEmpty() || !setter.IsEmpty());
1193 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
1194 i::ApiNatives::AddAccessorProperty(
1195 i_isolate, templ, Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*name), i_getter, i_setter,
1196 static_cast<i::PropertyAttributes>(attribute));
1197}

1199// --- F u n c t i o n T e m p l a t e ---
1200
1201Local<ObjectTemplate> FunctionTemplate::PrototypeTemplate() {
1202 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
1203 i::Isolate* i_isolate = self->GetIsolateChecked();
1204 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1205 i::DirectHandle<i::HeapObject> heap_obj(self->GetPrototypeTemplate(),
1206 i_isolate);
1207 if (i::IsUndefined(*heap_obj, i_isolate)) {
1208 // Do not cache prototype objects.
1209 constexpr bool do_not_cache = true;
1210 i::DirectHandle<i::ObjectTemplateInfo> proto_template =
1211 i_isolate->factory()->NewObjectTemplateInfo({}, do_not_cache);
1212 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetPrototypeTemplate(i_isolate, self,
1213 proto_template);
1214 return Utils::ToLocal(proto_template);
1215 }
1216 return ToApiHandle<ObjectTemplate>(heap_obj);
1217}
1218
1219void FunctionTemplate::SetPrototypeProviderTemplate(
1220 Local<FunctionTemplate> prototype_provider) {
1221 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
1222 i::Isolate* i_isolate = self->GetIsolateChecked();
1223 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1224 i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> result =
1225 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*prototype_provider);
1226 Utils::ApiCheck(i::IsUndefined(self->GetPrototypeTemplate(), i_isolate),
1227 "v8::FunctionTemplate::SetPrototypeProviderTemplate",
1228 "Protoype must be undefined");
1229 Utils::ApiCheck(i::IsUndefined(self->GetParentTemplate(), i_isolate),
1230 "v8::FunctionTemplate::SetPrototypeProviderTemplate",
1231 "Prototype provider must be empty");
1232 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetPrototypeProviderTemplate(i_isolate, self,
1233 result);
1234}

1236namespace {
1237static void EnsureNotPublished(i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> info,
1238 const char* func) {
1239 DCHECK_IMPLIES(info->instantiated(), info->published());
1240 Utils::ApiCheck(!info->published(), func,
1241 "FunctionTemplate already instantiated");
1242}
1243
1244i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> FunctionTemplateNew(
1245 i::Isolate* i_isolate, FunctionCallback callback, v8::Local<Value> data,
1246 v8::Local<Signature> signature, int length, ConstructorBehavior behavior,
1247 bool do_not_cache,
1248 v8::Local<Private> cached_property_name = v8::Local<Private>(),
1249 SideEffectType side_effect_type = SideEffectType::kHasSideEffect,
1250 const MemorySpan<const CFunction>& c_function_overloads = {}) {
1251 i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> obj =
1252 i_isolate->factory()->NewFunctionTemplateInfo(length, do_not_cache);
1253 {
1254 // Disallow GC until all fields of obj have acceptable types.
1255 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1256 i::Tagged<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> raw = *obj;
1257 if (!signature.IsEmpty()) {
1258 raw->set_signature(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*signature));
1259 }
1260 if (!cached_property_name.IsEmpty()) {
1261 raw->set_cached_property_name(
1262 *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*cached_property_name));
1263 }
1264 if (behavior == ConstructorBehavior::kThrow) {
1265 raw->set_remove_prototype(true);
1266 }
1267 }
1268 if (callback != nullptr) {
1269 Utils::ToLocal(obj)->SetCallHandler(callback, data, side_effect_type,
1270 c_function_overloads);
1271 }
1272 return obj;
1273}
1274} // namespace
1275
1276void FunctionTemplate::Inherit(v8::Local<FunctionTemplate> value) {
1277 auto info = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
1278 EnsureNotPublished(info, "v8::FunctionTemplate::Inherit");
1279 i::Isolate* i_isolate = info->GetIsolateChecked();
1280 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1281 Utils::ApiCheck(
1282 i::IsUndefined(info->GetPrototypeProviderTemplate(), i_isolate),
1283 "v8::FunctionTemplate::Inherit", "Protoype provider must be empty");
1284 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetParentTemplate(i_isolate, info,
1285 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value));
1286}
1287
1288Local<FunctionTemplate> FunctionTemplate::New(
1289 Isolate* v8_isolate, FunctionCallback callback, v8::Local<Value> data,
1290 v8::Local<Signature> signature, int length, ConstructorBehavior behavior,
1291 SideEffectType side_effect_type, const CFunction* c_function,
1292 uint16_t instance_type, uint16_t allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_start,
1293 uint16_t allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_end) {
1294 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
1295 // Changes to the environment cannot be captured in the snapshot. Expect no
1296 // function templates when the isolate is created for serialization.
1297 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, FunctionTemplate, New);
1298
1299 if (!Utils::ApiCheck(
1300 !c_function || behavior == ConstructorBehavior::kThrow,
1301 "FunctionTemplate::New",
1302 "Fast API calls are not supported for constructor functions")) {
1303 return Local<FunctionTemplate>();
1304 }
1305
1306 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1307 i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> templ = FunctionTemplateNew(
1308 i_isolate, callback, data, signature, length, behavior, false,
1309 Local<Private>(), side_effect_type,
1310 c_function ? MemorySpan<const CFunction>{c_function, 1}
1311 : MemorySpan<const CFunction>{});
1312
1313 if (instance_type) {
1314 if (!Utils::ApiCheck(
1315 base::IsInRange(static_cast<int>(instance_type),
1316 i::Internals::kFirstEmbedderJSApiObjectType,
1317 i::Internals::kLastEmbedderJSApiObjectType),
1318 "FunctionTemplate::New",
1319 "instance_type is outside the range of valid JSApiObject types")) {
1320 return Local<FunctionTemplate>();
1321 }
1322 templ->SetInstanceType(instance_type);
1323 }
1324
1325 if (allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_start ||
1326 allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_end) {
1327 if (!Utils::ApiCheck(i::Internals::kFirstEmbedderJSApiObjectType <=
1328 allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_start &&
1329 allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_start <=
1330 allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_end &&
1331 allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_end <=
1332 i::Internals::kLastEmbedderJSApiObjectType,
1333 "FunctionTemplate::New",
1334 "allowed receiver instance type range is outside the "
1335 "range of valid JSApiObject types")) {
1336 return Local<FunctionTemplate>();
1337 }
1338 templ->SetAllowedReceiverInstanceTypeRange(
1339 allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_start,
1340 allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_end);
1341 }
1342 return Utils::ToLocal(templ);
1343}
1344
1345Local<FunctionTemplate> FunctionTemplate::NewWithCFunctionOverloads(
1346 Isolate* v8_isolate, FunctionCallback callback, v8::Local<Value> data,
1347 v8::Local<Signature> signature, int length, ConstructorBehavior behavior,
1348 SideEffectType side_effect_type,
1349 const MemorySpan<const CFunction>& c_function_overloads) {
1350 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
1351 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, FunctionTemplate, New);
1352
1353 // Check that all overloads of the fast API callback have different numbers of
1354 // parameters. Since the number of overloads is supposed to be small, just
1355 // comparing them with each other should be fine.
1356 for (size_t i = 0; i < c_function_overloads.size(); ++i) {
1357 for (size_t j = i + 1; j < c_function_overloads.size(); ++j) {
1358 CHECK_NE(c_function_overloads.data()[i].ArgumentCount(),
1359 c_function_overloads.data()[j].ArgumentCount());
1360 }
1361 }
1362
1363 if (!Utils::ApiCheck(
1364 c_function_overloads.empty() ||
1365 behavior == ConstructorBehavior::kThrow,
1366 "FunctionTemplate::NewWithCFunctionOverloads",
1367 "Fast API calls are not supported for constructor functions")) {
1368 return Local<FunctionTemplate>();
1369 }
1370
1371 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1372 i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> templ = FunctionTemplateNew(
1373 i_isolate, callback, data, signature, length, behavior, false,
1374 Local<Private>(), side_effect_type, c_function_overloads);
1375 return Utils::ToLocal(templ);
1376}
1377
1378Local<FunctionTemplate> FunctionTemplate::NewWithCache(
1379 Isolate* v8_isolate, FunctionCallback callback,
1380 Local<Private> cache_property, Local<Value> data,
1381 Local<Signature> signature, int length, SideEffectType side_effect_type) {
1382 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
1383 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, FunctionTemplate, NewWithCache);
1384 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1385 i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> templ = FunctionTemplateNew(
1386 i_isolate, callback, data, signature, length, ConstructorBehavior::kAllow,
1387 false, cache_property, side_effect_type);
1388 return Utils::ToLocal(templ);
1389}
1390
1391Local<Signature> Signature::New(Isolate* v8_isolate,
1392 Local<FunctionTemplate> receiver) {
1393 return Local<Signature>::Cast(receiver);
1394}
1395
1396#define SET_FIELD_WRAPPED(i_isolate, obj, setter, cdata, tag) \
1397 do { \
1398 i::DirectHandle<i::UnionOf<i::Smi, i::Foreign>> foreign = \
1399 FromCData<tag>(i_isolate, cdata); \
1400 (obj)->setter(*foreign); \
1401 } while (false)
1402
1403void FunctionTemplate::SetCallHandler(
1404 FunctionCallback callback, v8::Local<Value> data,
1405 SideEffectType side_effect_type,
1406 const MemorySpan<const CFunction>& c_function_overloads) {
1407 auto info = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
1408 EnsureNotPublished(info, "v8::FunctionTemplate::SetCallHandler");
1409 i::Isolate* i_isolate = info->GetIsolateChecked();
1410 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1411 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
1412 info->set_has_side_effects(side_effect_type !=
1413 SideEffectType::kHasNoSideEffect);
1414 info->set_callback(i_isolate, reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(callback));
1415 if (data.IsEmpty()) {
1416 data = v8::Undefined(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
1417 }
1418 // "Release" callback and callback data fields.
1419 info->set_callback_data(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*data), kReleaseStore);
1420
1421 if (!c_function_overloads.empty()) {
1422 // Stores the data for a sequence of CFunction overloads into a single
1423 // FixedArray, as [address_0, signature_0, ... address_n-1, signature_n-1].
1424 i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArray> function_overloads =
1425 i_isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(static_cast<int>(
1426 c_function_overloads.size() *
1427 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::kFunctionOverloadEntrySize));
1428 int function_count = static_cast<int>(c_function_overloads.size());
1429 for (int i = 0; i < function_count; i++) {
1430 const CFunction& c_function = c_function_overloads.data()[i];
1431 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> address = FromCData<internal::kCFunctionTag>(
1432 i_isolate, c_function.GetAddress());
1433 function_overloads->set(
1434 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::kFunctionOverloadEntrySize * i, *address);
1435 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> signature =
1436 FromCData<internal::kCFunctionInfoTag>(i_isolate,
1437 c_function.GetTypeInfo());
1438 function_overloads->set(
1439 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::kFunctionOverloadEntrySize * i + 1,
1440 *signature);
1441 }
1442 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetCFunctionOverloads(i_isolate, info,
1443 function_overloads);
1444 }
1445}
1446
1447namespace {
1448
1449template <typename Getter, typename Setter>
1450i::DirectHandle<i::AccessorInfo> MakeAccessorInfo(i::Isolate* i_isolate,
1451 v8::Local<Name> name,
1452 Getter getter, Setter setter,
1453 v8::Local<Value> data,
1454 bool replace_on_access) {
1455 i::DirectHandle<i::AccessorInfo> obj =
1456 i_isolate->factory()->NewAccessorInfo();
1457 obj->set_getter(i_isolate, reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(getter));
1458 DCHECK_IMPLIES(replace_on_access, setter == nullptr);
1459 if (setter == nullptr) {
1460 setter = reinterpret_cast<Setter>(&i::Accessors::ReconfigureToDataProperty);
1461 }
1462 obj->set_setter(i_isolate, reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(setter));
1463
1464 auto accessor_name = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*name);
1465 if (!IsUniqueName(*accessor_name)) {
1466 accessor_name = i_isolate->factory()->InternalizeString(
1467 i::Cast<i::String>(accessor_name));
1468 }
1469 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1470 i::Tagged<i::AccessorInfo> raw_obj = *obj;
1471 if (data.IsEmpty()) {
1472 raw_obj->set_data(i::ReadOnlyRoots(i_isolate).undefined_value());
1473 } else {
1474 raw_obj->set_data(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*data));
1475 }
1476 raw_obj->set_name(*accessor_name);
1477 raw_obj->set_replace_on_access(replace_on_access);
1478 raw_obj->set_initial_property_attributes(i::NONE);
1479 return obj;
1480}
1481
1482} // namespace
1483
1484Local<ObjectTemplate> FunctionTemplate::InstanceTemplate() {
1485 auto constructor = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this, true);
1486 if (!Utils::ApiCheck(!constructor.is_null(),
1487 "v8::FunctionTemplate::InstanceTemplate()",
1488 "Reading from empty handle")) {
1489 return Local<ObjectTemplate>();
1490 }
1491 i::Isolate* i_isolate = constructor->GetIsolateChecked();
1492 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1493 auto maybe_templ = constructor->GetInstanceTemplate();
1494 if (!i::IsUndefined(maybe_templ, i_isolate)) {
1495 return Utils::ToLocal(i::direct_handle(
1496 i::Cast<i::ObjectTemplateInfo>(maybe_templ), i_isolate));
1497 }
1498 constexpr bool do_not_cache = false;
1499 i::DirectHandle<i::ObjectTemplateInfo> templ =
1500 i_isolate->factory()->NewObjectTemplateInfo(constructor, do_not_cache);
1501 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetInstanceTemplate(i_isolate, constructor, templ);
1502 return Utils::ToLocal(templ);
1503}

1575namespace {
1576// Ensure that the object template has a constructor. If no
1577// constructor is available we create one.
1578i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> EnsureConstructor(
1579 i::Isolate* i_isolate, ObjectTemplate* object_template) {
1580 i::Tagged<i::Object> obj =
1581 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(object_template)->constructor();
1582 if (!IsUndefined(obj, i_isolate)) {
1583 i::Tagged<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> info =
1584 i::Cast<i::FunctionTemplateInfo>(obj);
1585 return i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo>(info, i_isolate);
1586 }
1587 Local<FunctionTemplate> templ =
1588 FunctionTemplate::New(reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(i_isolate));
1589 auto constructor = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*templ);
1590 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetInstanceTemplate(
1591 i_isolate, constructor, Utils::OpenDirectHandle(object_template));
1592 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(object_template)->set_constructor(*constructor);
1593 return constructor;
1594}
1595
1596template <typename Getter, typename Setter, typename Data, typename Template>
1597void TemplateSetAccessor(Template* template_obj, v8::Local<Name> name,
1598 Getter getter, Setter setter, Data data,
1599 PropertyAttribute attribute, bool replace_on_access,
1600 SideEffectType getter_side_effect_type,
1601 SideEffectType setter_side_effect_type) {
1602 auto info = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(template_obj);
1603 auto i_isolate = info->GetIsolateChecked();
1604 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1605 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
1606 i::DirectHandle<i::AccessorInfo> accessor_info = MakeAccessorInfo(
1607 i_isolate, name, getter, setter, data, replace_on_access);
1608 {
1609 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
1610 i::Tagged<i::AccessorInfo> raw = *accessor_info;
1611 raw->set_initial_property_attributes(
1612 static_cast<i::PropertyAttributes>(attribute));
1613 raw->set_getter_side_effect_type(getter_side_effect_type);
1614 raw->set_setter_side_effect_type(setter_side_effect_type);
1615 }
1616 i::ApiNatives::AddNativeDataProperty(i_isolate, info, accessor_info);
1617}

1652
1653namespace {
1654enum class PropertyType { kNamed, kIndexed };
1655template <PropertyType property_type, typename Getter, typename Setter,
1656 typename Query, typename Descriptor, typename Deleter,
1657 typename Enumerator, typename Definer>
1658i::DirectHandle<i::InterceptorInfo> CreateInterceptorInfo(
1659 i::Isolate* i_isolate, Getter getter, Setter setter, Query query,
1660 Descriptor descriptor, Deleter remover, Enumerator enumerator,
1661 Definer definer, Local<Value> data,
1662 base::Flags<PropertyHandlerFlags> flags) {
1663 // TODO(saelo): instead of an in-sandbox struct with a lot of external
1664 // pointers (with different tags), consider creating an object in trusted
1665 // space instead. That way, only a single reference going out of the sandbox
1666 // would be required.
1667 auto obj = i::Cast<i::InterceptorInfo>(i_isolate->factory()->NewStruct(
1668 i::INTERCEPTOR_INFO_TYPE, i::AllocationType::kOld));
1669 obj->set_flags(0);
1670
1671#define CALLBACK_TAG(NAME) \
1672 property_type == PropertyType::kNamed \
1673 ? internal::kApiNamedProperty##NAME##CallbackTag \
1674 : internal::kApiIndexedProperty##NAME##CallbackTag;
1675
1676 if (getter != nullptr) {
1677 constexpr internal::ExternalPointerTag tag = CALLBACK_TAG(Getter);
1678 SET_FIELD_WRAPPED(i_isolate, obj, set_getter, getter, tag);
1679 }
1680 if (setter != nullptr) {
1681 constexpr internal::ExternalPointerTag tag = CALLBACK_TAG(Setter);
1682 SET_FIELD_WRAPPED(i_isolate, obj, set_setter, setter, tag);
1683 }
1684 if (query != nullptr) {
1685 constexpr internal::ExternalPointerTag tag = CALLBACK_TAG(Query);
1686 SET_FIELD_WRAPPED(i_isolate, obj, set_query, query, tag);
1687 }
1688 if (descriptor != nullptr) {
1689 constexpr internal::ExternalPointerTag tag = CALLBACK_TAG(Descriptor);
1690 SET_FIELD_WRAPPED(i_isolate, obj, set_descriptor, descriptor, tag);
1691 }
1692 if (remover != nullptr) {
1693 constexpr internal::ExternalPointerTag tag = CALLBACK_TAG(Deleter);
1694 SET_FIELD_WRAPPED(i_isolate, obj, set_deleter, remover, tag);
1695 }
1696 if (enumerator != nullptr) {
1697 SET_FIELD_WRAPPED(i_isolate, obj, set_enumerator, enumerator,
1698 internal::kApiIndexedPropertyEnumeratorCallbackTag);
1699 }
1700 if (definer != nullptr) {
1701 constexpr internal::ExternalPointerTag tag = CALLBACK_TAG(Definer);
1702 SET_FIELD_WRAPPED(i_isolate, obj, set_definer, definer, tag);
1703 }
1704
1705#undef CALLBACK_TAG
1706
1707 obj->set_can_intercept_symbols(
1708 !(flags & PropertyHandlerFlags::kOnlyInterceptStrings));
1709 obj->set_non_masking(flags & PropertyHandlerFlags::kNonMasking);
1710 obj->set_has_no_side_effect(flags & PropertyHandlerFlags::kHasNoSideEffect);
1711
1712 if (data.IsEmpty()) {
1713 data = v8::Undefined(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
1714 }
1715 obj->set_data(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*data));
1716 return obj;
1717}
1718
1719template <typename Getter, typename Setter, typename Query, typename Descriptor,
1720 typename Deleter, typename Enumerator, typename Definer>
1721i::DirectHandle<i::InterceptorInfo> CreateNamedInterceptorInfo(
1722 i::Isolate* i_isolate, Getter getter, Setter setter, Query query,
1723 Descriptor descriptor, Deleter remover, Enumerator enumerator,
1724 Definer definer, Local<Value> data,
1725 base::Flags<PropertyHandlerFlags> flags) {
1726 auto interceptor = CreateInterceptorInfo<PropertyType::kNamed>(
1727 i_isolate, getter, setter, query, descriptor, remover, enumerator,
1728 definer, data, flags);
1729 interceptor->set_is_named(true);
1730 return interceptor;
1731}
1732
1733template <typename Getter, typename Setter, typename Query, typename Descriptor,
1734 typename Deleter, typename Enumerator, typename Definer>
1735i::DirectHandle<i::InterceptorInfo> CreateIndexedInterceptorInfo(
1736 i::Isolate* i_isolate, Getter getter, Setter setter, Query query,
1737 Descriptor descriptor, Deleter remover, Enumerator enumerator,
1738 Definer definer, Local<Value> data,
1739 base::Flags<PropertyHandlerFlags> flags) {
1740 auto interceptor = CreateInterceptorInfo<PropertyType::kIndexed>(
1741 i_isolate, getter, setter, query, descriptor, remover, enumerator,
1742 definer, data, flags);
1743 interceptor->set_is_named(false);
1744 return interceptor;
1745}
1746
1747template <typename Getter, typename Setter, typename Query, typename Descriptor,
1748 typename Deleter, typename Enumerator, typename Definer>
1749void ObjectTemplateSetNamedPropertyHandler(
1750 ObjectTemplate* templ, Getter getter, Setter setter, Query query,
1751 Descriptor descriptor, Deleter remover, Enumerator enumerator,
1752 Definer definer, Local<Value> data, PropertyHandlerFlags flags) {
1753 i::Isolate* i_isolate = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(templ)->GetIsolate();
1754 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1755 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
1756 auto cons = EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, templ);
1757 EnsureNotPublished(cons, "ObjectTemplateSetNamedPropertyHandler");
1758 auto obj =
1759 CreateNamedInterceptorInfo(i_isolate, getter, setter, query, descriptor,
1760 remover, enumerator, definer, data, flags);
1761 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetNamedPropertyHandler(i_isolate, cons, obj);
1762}
1763} // namespace

1767 ObjectTemplateSetNamedPropertyHandler(
1768 this, config.getter, config.setter, config.query, config.descriptor,
1769 config.deleter, config.enumerator, config.definer, config.data,
1770 config.flags);

1782void ObjectTemplate::SetAccessCheckCallback(AccessCheckCallback callback,
1783 Local<Value> data) {
1784 i::Isolate* i_isolate = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this)->GetIsolate();
1785 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1786 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
1787 auto cons = EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, this);
1788 EnsureNotPublished(cons, "v8::ObjectTemplate::SetAccessCheckCallback");
1789
1790 i::DirectHandle<i::Struct> struct_info = i_isolate->factory()->NewStruct(
1791 i::ACCESS_CHECK_INFO_TYPE, i::AllocationType::kOld);
1792 auto info = i::Cast<i::AccessCheckInfo>(struct_info);
1793
1794 SET_FIELD_WRAPPED(i_isolate, info, set_callback, callback,
1795 internal::kApiAccessCheckCallbackTag);
1796 info->set_named_interceptor(i::Smi::zero());
1797 info->set_indexed_interceptor(i::Smi::zero());
1798
1799 if (data.IsEmpty()) {
1800 data = v8::Undefined(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
1801 }
1802 info->set_data(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*data));
1803
1804 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetAccessCheckInfo(i_isolate, cons, info);
1805 cons->set_needs_access_check(true);
1806}
1807
1808void ObjectTemplate::SetAccessCheckCallbackAndHandler(
1809 AccessCheckCallback callback,
1810 const NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration& named_handler,
1811 const IndexedPropertyHandlerConfiguration& indexed_handler,
1812 Local<Value> data) {
1813 i::Isolate* i_isolate = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this)->GetIsolate();
1814 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1815 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
1816 auto cons = EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, this);
1817 EnsureNotPublished(cons,
1818 "v8::ObjectTemplate::SetAccessCheckCallbackWithHandler");
1819
1820 i::DirectHandle<i::Struct> struct_info = i_isolate->factory()->NewStruct(
1821 i::ACCESS_CHECK_INFO_TYPE, i::AllocationType::kOld);
1822 auto info = i::Cast<i::AccessCheckInfo>(struct_info);
1823
1824 SET_FIELD_WRAPPED(i_isolate, info, set_callback, callback,
1825 internal::kApiAccessCheckCallbackTag);
1826 auto named_interceptor = CreateNamedInterceptorInfo(
1827 i_isolate, named_handler.getter, named_handler.setter,
1828 named_handler.query, named_handler.descriptor, named_handler.deleter,
1829 named_handler.enumerator, named_handler.definer, named_handler.data,
1830 named_handler.flags);
1831 info->set_named_interceptor(*named_interceptor);
1832 auto indexed_interceptor = CreateIndexedInterceptorInfo(
1833 i_isolate, indexed_handler.getter, indexed_handler.setter,
1834 indexed_handler.query, indexed_handler.descriptor,
1835 indexed_handler.deleter, indexed_handler.enumerator,
1836 indexed_handler.definer, indexed_handler.data, indexed_handler.flags);
1837 info->set_indexed_interceptor(*indexed_interceptor);
1838
1839 if (data.IsEmpty()) {
1840 data = v8::Undefined(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
1841 }
1842 info->set_data(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*data));
1843
1844 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetAccessCheckInfo(i_isolate, cons, info);
1845 cons->set_needs_access_check(true);
1846}

1848void ObjectTemplate::SetHandler(

1850 i::Isolate* i_isolate = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this)->GetIsolate();

1852 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);

1855 auto obj = CreateIndexedInterceptorInfo(

1861
1862void ObjectTemplate::SetCallAsFunctionHandler(FunctionCallback callback,
1863 Local<Value> data) {
1864 i::Isolate* i_isolate = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this)->GetIsolate();
1865 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1866 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
1867 auto cons = EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, this);
1868 EnsureNotPublished(cons, "v8::ObjectTemplate::SetCallAsFunctionHandler");
1869 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(callback);
1870
1871 // This template is just a container for callback and data values and thus
1872 // it's not supposed to be instantiated. Don't cache it.
1873 constexpr bool do_not_cache = true;
1874 constexpr int length = 0;
1875 i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> templ =
1876 i_isolate->factory()->NewFunctionTemplateInfo(length, do_not_cache);
1877 templ->set_is_object_template_call_handler(true);
1878 Utils::ToLocal(templ)->SetCallHandler(callback, data);
1879 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetInstanceCallHandler(i_isolate, cons, templ);
1880}

1882int ObjectTemplate::InternalFieldCount() const {
1883 return Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this)->embedder_field_count();
1884}
1885
1886void ObjectTemplate::SetInternalFieldCount(int value) {
1887 i::Isolate* i_isolate = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this)->GetIsolate();
1888 if (!Utils::ApiCheck(i::Smi::IsValid(value),
1889 "v8::ObjectTemplate::SetInternalFieldCount()",
1890 "Invalid embedder field count")) {
1891 return;
1892 }
1893 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1894 if (value > 0) {
1895 // The embedder field count is set by the constructor function's
1896 // construct code, so we ensure that there is a constructor
1897 // function to do the setting.
1898 EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, this);
1899 }
1900 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this)->set_embedder_field_count(value);
1901}

1945// Internally, UnboundScript and UnboundModuleScript are SharedFunctionInfos,
1946// and Script is a JSFunction.
1947
1948ScriptCompiler::CachedData::CachedData(const uint8_t* data_, int length_,
1949 BufferPolicy buffer_policy_)
1950 : data(data_),
1951 length(length_),
1952 rejected(false),
1953 buffer_policy(buffer_policy_) {}
1954
1955ScriptCompiler::CachedData::~CachedData() {
1956 if (buffer_policy == BufferOwned) {
1957 delete[] data;
1958 }
1959}
1960
1961ScriptCompiler::CachedData::CompatibilityCheckResult
1962ScriptCompiler::CachedData::CompatibilityCheck(Isolate* isolate) {
1963 i::AlignedCachedData aligned(data, length);
1964 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
1965 i::SerializedCodeSanityCheckResult result;
1966 i::SerializedCodeData scd =
1967 i::SerializedCodeData::FromCachedDataWithoutSource(
1968 i_isolate->AsLocalIsolate(), &aligned, &result);
1969 return static_cast<ScriptCompiler::CachedData::CompatibilityCheckResult>(
1970 result);
1971}

1979Local<Script> UnboundScript::BindToCurrentContext() {
1980 auto function_info = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
1981 // TODO(jgruber): Remove this DCHECK once Function::GetUnboundScript is gone.
1982 DCHECK(!i::HeapLayout::InReadOnlySpace(*function_info));
1983 i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::GetIsolateFromWritableObject(*function_info);
1984 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
1985 i::DirectHandle<i::JSFunction> function =
1986 i::Factory::JSFunctionBuilder{i_isolate, function_info,
1987 i_isolate->native_context()}
1988 .Build();
1989 return ToApiHandle<Script>(function);
1990}

2116
2117MaybeLocal<Value> Script::Run(Local<Context> context) {
2118 return Run(context, Local<Data>());
2119}
2120
2121MaybeLocal<Value> Script::Run(Local<Context> context,
2122 Local<Data> host_defined_options) {
2123 auto v8_isolate = context->GetIsolate();
2124 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
2125 TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.Execute");
2126 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Script, Run, InternalEscapableScope);
2127 i::TimerEventScope<i::TimerEventExecute> timer_scope(i_isolate);
2128 i::NestedTimedHistogramScope execute_timer(i_isolate->counters()->execute(),
2129 i_isolate);
2130 i::AggregatingHistogramTimerScope histogram_timer(
2131 i_isolate->counters()->compile_lazy());
2132
2133#if defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
2134 // In case ETW has been activated, tasks to log existing code are
2135 // created. But in case the task runner does not run those before
2136 // starting to execute code (as it happens in d8, that will run
2137 // first the code from prompt), then that code will not have
2138 // JIT instrumentation on time.
2139 //
2140 // To avoid this, on running scripts check first if JIT code log is
2141 // pending and generate immediately.
2142 if (i::v8_flags.enable_etw_stack_walking ||
2143 i::v8_flags.enable_etw_by_custom_filter_only) {
2144 i::ETWJITInterface::MaybeSetHandlerNow(i_isolate);
2145 }
2146#endif // V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING
2147 auto fun = i::Cast<i::JSFunction>(Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this));
2148 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> receiver = i_isolate->global_proxy();
2149 // TODO(cbruni, chromium:1244145): Remove once migrated to the context.
2150 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> options(
2151 i::Cast<i::Script>(fun->shared()->script())->host_defined_options(),
2152 i_isolate);
2153 Local<Value> result;
2154 has_exception = !ToLocal<Value>(
2155 i::Execution::CallScript(i_isolate, fun, receiver, options), &result);
2156
2157 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Value);
2158 RETURN_ESCAPED(result);
2159}

2193
2194std::vector<int> Script::GetProducedCompileHints() const {
2195 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2196 auto func = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
2197 i::Isolate* i_isolate = func->GetIsolate();
2198 i::Tagged<i::SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = func->shared();
2199 CHECK(IsScript(sfi->script()));
2200 i::Tagged<i::Script> script = i::Cast<i::Script>(sfi->script());
2201 i::Tagged<i::Object> maybe_array_list =
2202 script->compiled_lazy_function_positions();
2203 std::vector<int> result;
2204 if (!IsUndefined(maybe_array_list, i_isolate)) {
2205 i::Tagged<i::ArrayList> array_list =
2206 i::Cast<i::ArrayList>(maybe_array_list);
2207 result.reserve(array_list->length());
2208 for (int i = 0; i < array_list->length(); ++i) {
2209 i::Tagged<i::Object> item = array_list->get(i);
2210 CHECK(IsSmi(item));
2211 result.push_back(i::Smi::ToInt(item));
2212 }
2213 }
2214 return result;
2215}
2216
2217Local<CompileHintsCollector> Script::GetCompileHintsCollector() const {
2218 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2219 auto func = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
2220 i::Isolate* i_isolate = func->GetIsolate();
2221 i::Tagged<i::SharedFunctionInfo> sfi = func->shared();
2222 CHECK(IsScript(sfi->script()));
2223 i::DirectHandle<i::Script> script(i::Cast<i::Script>(sfi->script()),
2224 i_isolate);
2225 return ToApiHandle<CompileHintsCollector>(script);
2226}
2227
2228std::vector<int> CompileHintsCollector::GetCompileHints(
2229 Isolate* v8_isolate) const {
2230 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
2231 auto script = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
2232 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
2233 i::Tagged<i::Object> maybe_array_list =
2234 script->compiled_lazy_function_positions();
2235 std::vector<int> result;
2236 if (!IsUndefined(maybe_array_list, i_isolate)) {
2237 i::Tagged<i::ArrayList> array_list =
2238 i::Cast<i::ArrayList>(maybe_array_list);
2239 result.reserve(array_list->length());
2240 for (int i = 0; i < array_list->length(); ++i) {
2241 i::Tagged<i::Object> item = array_list->get(i);
2242 CHECK(IsSmi(item));
2243 result.push_back(i::Smi::ToInt(item));
2244 }
2245 }
2246 return result;
2247}

2327
2328Module::Status Module::GetStatus() const {
2329 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
2330 switch (self->status()) {
2331 case i::Module::kUnlinked:
2332 case i::Module::kPreLinking:
2333 return kUninstantiated;
2334 case i::Module::kLinking:
2335 return kInstantiating;
2336 case i::Module::kLinked:
2337 return kInstantiated;
2338 case i::Module::kEvaluating:
2339 return kEvaluating;
2340 case i::Module::kEvaluatingAsync:
2341 // TODO(syg): Expose kEvaluatingAsync in API as well.
2342 case i::Module::kEvaluated:
2343 return kEvaluated;
2344 case i::Module::kErrored:
2345 return kErrored;
2346 }
2347 UNREACHABLE();
2348}
2349

2351 Utils::ApiCheck(GetStatus() == kErrored, "v8::Module::GetException",
2352 "Module status must be kErrored");

2354 i::Isolate* i_isolate = self->GetIsolate();
2355 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
2356 return ToApiHandle<Value>(i::direct_handle(self->GetException(), i_isolate));
2357}
2358
2359Local<FixedArray> Module::GetModuleRequests() const {
2360 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
2361 i::Isolate* i_isolate = self->GetIsolate();
2362 DCHECK_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
2363 if (i::IsSyntheticModule(*self)) {
2364 // Synthetic modules are leaf nodes in the module graph. They have no
2365 // ModuleRequests.
2366 return ToApiHandle<FixedArray>(i_isolate->factory()->empty_fixed_array());
2367 } else {
2368 return ToApiHandle<FixedArray>(i::direct_handle(
2369 i::Cast<i::SourceTextModule>(self)->info()->module_requests(),
2370 i_isolate));
2371 }
2372}

2454Maybe<bool> Module::InstantiateModule(Local<Context> context,
2455 ResolveModuleCallback module_callback,
2456 ResolveSourceCallback source_callback) {
2457 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
2458 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Module, InstantiateModule, i::HandleScope);
2459 has_exception =
2460 !i::Module::Instantiate(i_isolate, Utils::OpenHandle(this), context,
2461 module_callback, source_callback);
2462 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
2463 return Just(true);
2464}
2465
2466MaybeLocal<Value> Module::Evaluate(Local<Context> context) {
2467 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
2468 TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.Execute");
2469 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Module, Evaluate, InternalEscapableScope);
2470 i::TimerEventScope<i::TimerEventExecute> timer_scope(i_isolate);
2471 i::NestedTimedHistogramScope execute_timer(i_isolate->counters()->execute(),
2472 i_isolate);
2473 i::AggregatingHistogramTimerScope timer(
2474 i_isolate->counters()->compile_lazy());
2475
2476 auto self = Utils::OpenHandle(this);
2477 Utils::ApiCheck(self->status() >= i::Module::kLinked, "Module::Evaluate",
2478 "Expected instantiated module");
2479
2480 Local<Value> result;
2481 has_exception = !ToLocal(i::Module::Evaluate(i_isolate, self), &result);
2482 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Value);
2483 RETURN_ESCAPED(result);
2484}

2486Local<Module> Module::CreateSyntheticModule(
2487 Isolate* v8_isolate, Local<String> module_name,
2488 const MemorySpan<const Local<String>>& export_names,
2489 v8::Module::SyntheticModuleEvaluationSteps evaluation_steps) {
2490 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
2491 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
2492 auto i_module_name = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*module_name);
2493 i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArray> i_export_names =
2494 i_isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(
2495 static_cast<int>(export_names.size()));
2496 for (int i = 0; i < i_export_names->length(); ++i) {
2497 i::DirectHandle<i::String> str = i_isolate->factory()->InternalizeString(
2498 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*export_names[i]));
2499 i_export_names->set(i, *str);
2500 }
2501 return v8::Utils::ToLocal(
2502 i::DirectHandle<i::Module>(i_isolate->factory()->NewSyntheticModule(
2503 i_module_name, i_export_names, evaluation_steps)));
2504}
2505
2506Maybe<bool> Module::SetSyntheticModuleExport(Isolate* v8_isolate,
2507 Local<String> export_name,
2508 Local<v8::Value> export_value) {
2509 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
2510 auto i_export_name = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*export_name);
2511 auto i_export_value = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*export_value);
2512 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
2513 Utils::ApiCheck(i::IsSyntheticModule(*self),
2514 "v8::Module::SyntheticModuleSetExport",
2515 "v8::Module::SyntheticModuleSetExport must only be called on "
2516 "a SyntheticModule");
2517 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT(i_isolate, v8_isolate->GetCurrentContext(), Module,
2518 SetSyntheticModuleExport, i::HandleScope);
2519 has_exception = i::SyntheticModule::SetExport(
2520 i_isolate, i::Cast<i::SyntheticModule>(self),
2521 i_export_name, i_export_value)
2522 .IsNothing();
2523 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
2524 return Just(true);
2525}
2526
2527std::pair<LocalVector<Module>, LocalVector<Message>>
2528Module::GetStalledTopLevelAwaitMessages(Isolate* isolate) {
2529 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
2530 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
2531 Utils::ApiCheck(i::IsSourceTextModule(*self),
2532 "v8::Module::GetStalledTopLevelAwaitMessages",
2533 "v8::Module::GetStalledTopLevelAwaitMessages must only be "
2534 "called on a SourceTextModule");
2535 std::pair<i::DirectHandleVector<i::SourceTextModule>,
2536 i::DirectHandleVector<i::JSMessageObject>>
2537 stalled_awaits =
2538 i::Cast<i::SourceTextModule>(self)->GetStalledTopLevelAwaitMessages(
2539 i_isolate);
2540
2541 LocalVector<Module> modules(isolate);
2542 if (size_t stalled_awaits_count = stalled_awaits.first.size();
2543 stalled_awaits_count > 0) {
2544 modules.reserve(stalled_awaits_count);
2545 for (auto module : stalled_awaits.first)
2546 modules.push_back(ToApiHandle<Module>(module));
2547 }
2548 LocalVector<Message> messages(isolate);
2549 if (size_t stalled_awaits_count = stalled_awaits.second.size();
2550 stalled_awaits_count > 0) {
2551 messages.reserve(stalled_awaits_count);
2552 for (auto message : stalled_awaits.second)
2553 messages.push_back(ToApiHandle<Message>(message));
2554 }
2555
2556 return {modules, messages};
2557}
2558
2559namespace {
2560
2561i::ScriptDetails GetScriptDetails(
2562 i::Isolate* i_isolate, Local<Value> resource_name, int resource_line_offset,
2563 int resource_column_offset, Local<Value> source_map_url,
2564 Local<Data> host_defined_options, ScriptOriginOptions origin_options) {
2565 i::ScriptDetails script_details(Utils::OpenHandle(*(resource_name), true),
2566 origin_options);
2567 script_details.line_offset = resource_line_offset;
2568 script_details.column_offset = resource_column_offset;
2569 script_details.host_defined_options =
2570 host_defined_options.IsEmpty()
2571 ? i_isolate->factory()->empty_fixed_array()
2572 : Utils::OpenHandle(*(host_defined_options));
2573 if (!source_map_url.IsEmpty()) {
2574 script_details.source_map_url = Utils::OpenHandle(*(source_map_url));
2575 }
2576 return script_details;
2577}
2578
2579} // namespace
2580
2581MaybeLocal<UnboundScript> ScriptCompiler::CompileUnboundInternal(
2582 Isolate* v8_isolate, Source* source, CompileOptions options,
2583 NoCacheReason no_cache_reason) {
2584 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
2585 TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.ScriptCompiler");
2586 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT(i_isolate, v8_isolate->GetCurrentContext(), ScriptCompiler,
2587 CompileUnbound, InternalEscapableScope);
2588
2589 auto str = Utils::OpenHandle(*(source->source_string));
2590
2591 i::DirectHandle<i::SharedFunctionInfo> result;
2592 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"), "V8.CompileScript");
2593 i::ScriptDetails script_details = GetScriptDetails(
2594 i_isolate, source->resource_name, source->resource_line_offset,
2595 source->resource_column_offset, source->source_map_url,
2596 source->host_defined_options, source->resource_options);
2597
2598 i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_function_info;
2599 if (options & kConsumeCodeCache) {
2600 if (source->consume_cache_task) {
2601 // Take ownership of the internal deserialization task and clear it off
2602 // the consume task on the source.
2603 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(source->consume_cache_task->impl_);
2604 std::unique_ptr<i::BackgroundDeserializeTask> deserialize_task =
2605 std::move(source->consume_cache_task->impl_);
2606 maybe_function_info =
2607 i::Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfoForScriptWithDeserializeTask(
2608 i_isolate, str, script_details, deserialize_task.get(), options,
2609 no_cache_reason, i::NOT_NATIVES_CODE,
2610 &source->compilation_details);
2611 source->cached_data->rejected = deserialize_task->rejected();
2612 } else {
2613 DCHECK(source->cached_data);
2614 // AlignedCachedData takes care of pointer-aligning the data.
2615 auto cached_data = std::make_unique<i::AlignedCachedData>(
2616 source->cached_data->data, source->cached_data->length);
2617 maybe_function_info =
2618 i::Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfoForScriptWithCachedData(
2619 i_isolate, str, script_details, cached_data.get(), options,
2620 no_cache_reason, i::NOT_NATIVES_CODE,
2621 &source->compilation_details);
2622 source->cached_data->rejected = cached_data->rejected();
2623 }
2624 } else if (options & kConsumeCompileHints) {
2625 maybe_function_info =
2626 i::Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfoForScriptWithCompileHints(
2627 i_isolate, str, script_details, source->compile_hint_callback,
2628 source->compile_hint_callback_data, options, no_cache_reason,
2629 i::NOT_NATIVES_CODE, &source->compilation_details);
2630 } else {
2631 // Compile without any cache.
2632 maybe_function_info = i::Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfoForScript(
2633 i_isolate, str, script_details, options, no_cache_reason,
2634 i::NOT_NATIVES_CODE, &source->compilation_details);
2635 }
2636
2637 has_exception = !maybe_function_info.ToHandle(&result);
2638 DCHECK_IMPLIES(!has_exception, !i::HeapLayout::InReadOnlySpace(*result));
2639 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(UnboundScript);
2640 RETURN_ESCAPED(ToApiHandle<UnboundScript>(result));
2641}
2642
2643MaybeLocal<UnboundScript> ScriptCompiler::CompileUnboundScript(
2644 Isolate* v8_isolate, Source* source, CompileOptions options,
2645 NoCacheReason no_cache_reason) {
2646 Utils::ApiCheck(
2647 !source->GetResourceOptions().IsModule(),
2648 "v8::ScriptCompiler::CompileUnboundScript",
2649 "v8::ScriptCompiler::CompileModule must be used to compile modules");
2650 return CompileUnboundInternal(v8_isolate, source, options, no_cache_reason);
2651}
2652
2653MaybeLocal<Script> ScriptCompiler::Compile(Local<Context> context,
2654 Source* source,
2655 CompileOptions options,
2656 NoCacheReason no_cache_reason) {
2657 Utils::ApiCheck(
2658 !source->GetResourceOptions().IsModule(), "v8::ScriptCompiler::Compile",
2659 "v8::ScriptCompiler::CompileModule must be used to compile modules");
2660 auto i_isolate = context->GetIsolate();
2661 MaybeLocal<UnboundScript> maybe =
2662 CompileUnboundInternal(i_isolate, source, options, no_cache_reason);
2663 Local<UnboundScript> result;
2664 if (!maybe.ToLocal(&result)) return MaybeLocal<Script>();
2665 v8::Context::Scope scope(context);
2666 return result->BindToCurrentContext();
2667}
2668
2669MaybeLocal<Module> ScriptCompiler::CompileModule(
2670 Isolate* v8_isolate, Source* source, CompileOptions options,
2671 NoCacheReason no_cache_reason) {
2672 Utils::ApiCheck(v8::ScriptCompiler::CompileOptionsIsValid(options),
2673 "v8::ScriptCompiler::CompileModule",
2674 "Invalid CompileOptions");
2675 Utils::ApiCheck(source->GetResourceOptions().IsModule(),
2676 "v8::ScriptCompiler::CompileModule",
2677 "Invalid ScriptOrigin: is_module must be true");
2678 MaybeLocal<UnboundScript> maybe =
2679 CompileUnboundInternal(v8_isolate, source, options, no_cache_reason);
2680 Local<UnboundScript> unbound;
2681 if (!maybe.ToLocal(&unbound)) return MaybeLocal<Module>();
2682 auto shared = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*unbound);
2683 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
2684 return ToApiHandle<Module>(i_isolate->factory()->NewSourceTextModule(shared));
2685}
2686
2687// static
2688V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT MaybeLocal<Function> ScriptCompiler::CompileFunction(
2689 Local<Context> v8_context, Source* source, size_t arguments_count,
2690 Local<String> arguments[], size_t context_extension_count,
2691 Local<Object> context_extensions[], CompileOptions options,
2692 NoCacheReason no_cache_reason) {
2693 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(v8_context, ScriptCompiler, CompileFunction);
2694 TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.ScriptCompiler");
2695
2696 DCHECK(options == CompileOptions::kConsumeCodeCache ||
2697 options == CompileOptions::kEagerCompile ||
2698 options == CompileOptions::kNoCompileOptions);
2699
2700 i::DirectHandle<i::Context> context = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*v8_context);
2701
2702 DCHECK(IsNativeContext(*context));
2703
2704 i::Handle<i::FixedArray> arguments_list =
2705 i_isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(static_cast<int>(arguments_count));
2706 for (int i = 0; i < static_cast<int>(arguments_count); i++) {
2707 auto argument = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*arguments[i]);
2708 if (!i::String::IsIdentifier(i_isolate, argument)) return Local<Function>();
2709 arguments_list->set(i, *argument);
2710 }
2711
2712 for (size_t i = 0; i < context_extension_count; ++i) {
2713 i::DirectHandle<i::JSReceiver> extension =
2714 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*context_extensions[i]);
2715 if (!IsJSObject(*extension)) return Local<Function>();
2716 context = i_isolate->factory()->NewWithContext(
2717 context,
2718 i::ScopeInfo::CreateForWithScope(
2719 i_isolate,
2720 IsNativeContext(*context)
2721 ? i::Handle<i::ScopeInfo>::null()
2722 : i::Handle<i::ScopeInfo>(context->scope_info(), i_isolate)),
2723 extension);
2724 }
2725
2726 i::ScriptDetails script_details = GetScriptDetails(
2727 i_isolate, source->resource_name, source->resource_line_offset,
2728 source->resource_column_offset, source->source_map_url,
2729 source->host_defined_options, source->resource_options);
2730 script_details.wrapped_arguments = arguments_list;
2731
2732 std::unique_ptr<i::AlignedCachedData> cached_data;
2733 if (options & kConsumeCodeCache) {
2734 DCHECK(source->cached_data);
2735 // ScriptData takes care of pointer-aligning the data.
2736 cached_data.reset(new i::AlignedCachedData(source->cached_data->data,
2737 source->cached_data->length));
2738 }
2739
2740 i::DirectHandle<i::JSFunction> result;
2741 has_exception =
2742 !i::Compiler::GetWrappedFunction(
2743 Utils::OpenHandle(*source->source_string), context, script_details,
2744 cached_data.get(), options, no_cache_reason)
2745 .ToHandle(&result);
2746 if (options & kConsumeCodeCache) {
2747 source->cached_data->rejected = cached_data->rejected();
2748 }
2749 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Function);
2750 return handle_scope.Escape(Utils::CallableToLocal(result));
2751}
2752
2753void ScriptCompiler::ScriptStreamingTask::Run() { data_->task->Run(); }
2754
2755ScriptCompiler::ScriptStreamingTask* ScriptCompiler::StartStreaming(
2756 Isolate* v8_isolate, StreamedSource* source, v8::ScriptType type,
2757 CompileOptions options, CompileHintCallback compile_hint_callback,
2758 void* compile_hint_callback_data) {
2759 Utils::ApiCheck(v8::ScriptCompiler::CompileOptionsIsValid(options),
2760 "v8::ScriptCompiler::StartStreaming",
2761 "Invalid CompileOptions");
2762 if (!i::v8_flags.script_streaming) return nullptr;
2763 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
2764 i::ScriptStreamingData* data = source->impl();
2765 std::unique_ptr<i::BackgroundCompileTask> task =
2766 std::make_unique<i::BackgroundCompileTask>(
2767 data, i_isolate, type, options, &source->compilation_details(),
2768 compile_hint_callback, compile_hint_callback_data);
2769 data->task = std::move(task);
2770 return new ScriptCompiler::ScriptStreamingTask(data);
2771}

2773ScriptCompiler::ConsumeCodeCacheTask::ConsumeCodeCacheTask(
2774 std::unique_ptr<i::BackgroundDeserializeTask> impl)
2775 : impl_(std::move(impl)) {}
2776
2777ScriptCompiler::ConsumeCodeCacheTask::~ConsumeCodeCacheTask() = default;

2779void ScriptCompiler::ConsumeCodeCacheTask::Run() { impl_->Run(); }

2788 GetScriptDetails(i_isolate, origin.ResourceName(), origin.LineOffset(),
2789 origin.ColumnOffset(), origin.SourceMapUrl(),
2790 origin.GetHostDefinedOptions(), origin.Options());
2791 impl_->SourceTextAvailable(i_isolate, str, script_details);
2792}

2797 .merge_background_deserialized_script_with_compilation_cache) {
2798 return false;
