2800 return impl_->ShouldMergeWithExistingScript();

2829namespace {
2830i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::SharedFunctionInfo> CompileStreamedSource(
2831 i::Isolate* i_isolate, ScriptCompiler::StreamedSource* v8_source,
2832 Local<String> full_source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin) {
2833 auto str = Utils::OpenHandle(*full_source_string);
2834 i::ScriptDetails script_details =
2835 GetScriptDetails(i_isolate, origin.ResourceName(), origin.LineOffset(),
2836 origin.ColumnOffset(), origin.SourceMapUrl(),
2837 origin.GetHostDefinedOptions(), origin.Options());
2838 i::ScriptStreamingData* data = v8_source->impl();
2839 return i::Compiler::GetSharedFunctionInfoForStreamedScript(
2840 i_isolate, str, script_details, data, &v8_source->compilation_details());
2841}
2842
2843} // namespace
2844
2845MaybeLocal<Script> ScriptCompiler::Compile(Local<Context> context,
2846 StreamedSource* v8_source,
2847 Local<String> full_source_string,
2848 const ScriptOrigin& origin) {
2849 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, ScriptCompiler, Compile);
2850 TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.ScriptCompiler");
2851 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
2852 "V8.CompileStreamedScript");
2853 i::DirectHandle<i::SharedFunctionInfo> sfi;
2854 i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_sfi =
2855 CompileStreamedSource(i_isolate, v8_source, full_source_string, origin);
2856 has_exception = !maybe_sfi.ToHandle(&sfi);
2857 if (has_exception) i_isolate->ReportPendingMessages();
2858 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Script);
2859 Local<UnboundScript> generic = ToApiHandle<UnboundScript>(sfi);
2860 if (generic.IsEmpty()) return Local<Script>();
2861 Local<Script> bound = generic->BindToCurrentContext();
2862 if (bound.IsEmpty()) return Local<Script>();
2863 RETURN_ESCAPED(bound);
2864}
2865
2866MaybeLocal<Module> ScriptCompiler::CompileModule(
2867 Local<Context> context, StreamedSource* v8_source,
2868 Local<String> full_source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin) {
2869 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, ScriptCompiler, Compile);
2870 TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.ScriptCompiler");
2871 TRACE_EVENT0(TRACE_DISABLED_BY_DEFAULT("v8.compile"),
2872 "V8.CompileStreamedModule");
2873 i::DirectHandle<i::SharedFunctionInfo> sfi;
2874 i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::SharedFunctionInfo> maybe_sfi =
2875 CompileStreamedSource(i_isolate, v8_source, full_source_string, origin);
2876 has_exception = !maybe_sfi.ToHandle(&sfi);
2877 if (has_exception) i_isolate->ReportPendingMessages();
2878 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Module);
2879 RETURN_ESCAPED(
2880 ToApiHandle<Module>(i_isolate->factory()->NewSourceTextModule(sfi)));
2881}

2883uint32_t ScriptCompiler::CachedDataVersionTag() {
2884 return static_cast<uint32_t>(base::hash_combine(
2885 internal::Version::Hash(), internal::FlagList::Hash(),
2886 static_cast<uint32_t>(internal::CpuFeatures::SupportedFeatures())));
2887}
2888
2889ScriptCompiler::CachedData* ScriptCompiler::CreateCodeCache(
2890 Local<UnboundScript> unbound_script) {
2891 auto shared = Utils::OpenHandle(*unbound_script);
2892 // TODO(jgruber): Remove this DCHECK once Function::GetUnboundScript is gone.
2893 DCHECK(!i::HeapLayout::InReadOnlySpace(*shared));
2894 i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::GetIsolateFromWritableObject(*shared);
2895 Utils::ApiCheck(!i_isolate->serializer_enabled(),
2896 "ScriptCompiler::CreateCodeCache",
2897 "Cannot create code cache while creating a snapshot");
2898 DCHECK_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
2899 DCHECK(shared->is_toplevel());
2900 return i::CodeSerializer::Serialize(i_isolate, shared);
2901}
2902
2903// static
2904ScriptCompiler::CachedData* ScriptCompiler::CreateCodeCache(
2905 Local<UnboundModuleScript> unbound_module_script) {
2906 i::Handle<i::SharedFunctionInfo> shared =
2907 Utils::OpenHandle(*unbound_module_script);
2908 // TODO(jgruber): Remove this DCHECK once Function::GetUnboundScript is gone.
2909 DCHECK(!i::HeapLayout::InReadOnlySpace(*shared));
2910 i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::GetIsolateFromWritableObject(*shared);
2911 Utils::ApiCheck(!i_isolate->serializer_enabled(),
2912 "ScriptCompiler::CreateCodeCache",
2913 "Cannot create code cache while creating a snapshot");
2914 DCHECK_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
2915 DCHECK(shared->is_toplevel());
2916 return i::CodeSerializer::Serialize(i_isolate, shared);
2917}
2918
2919ScriptCompiler::CachedData* ScriptCompiler::CreateCodeCacheForFunction(
2920 Local<Function> function) {
2921 auto js_function = i::Cast<i::JSFunction>(Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*function));
2922 i::Isolate* i_isolate = js_function->GetIsolate();
2923 Utils::ApiCheck(!i_isolate->serializer_enabled(),
2924 "ScriptCompiler::CreateCodeCacheForFunction",
2925 "Cannot create code cache while creating a snapshot");
2926 i::Handle<i::SharedFunctionInfo> shared(js_function->shared(), i_isolate);
2927 DCHECK_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
2928 Utils::ApiCheck(shared->is_wrapped(),
2929 "v8::ScriptCompiler::CreateCodeCacheForFunction",
2930 "Expected SharedFunctionInfo with wrapped source code");
2931 return i::CodeSerializer::Serialize(i_isolate, shared);
2932}
2933
2934MaybeLocal<Script> Script::Compile(Local<Context> context, Local<String> source,
2935 ScriptOrigin* origin) {
2936 if (origin) {
2937 ScriptCompiler::Source script_source(source, *origin);
2938 return ScriptCompiler::Compile(context, &script_source);
2939 }
2940 ScriptCompiler::Source script_source(source);
2941 return ScriptCompiler::Compile(context, &script_source);
2942}

2944// --- E x c e p t i o n s ---
2945
2946v8::TryCatch::TryCatch(v8::Isolate* v8_isolate)
2947 : i_isolate_(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate)),
2948 next_(i_isolate_->try_catch_handler()),
2949 is_verbose_(false),
2950 can_continue_(true),
2951 capture_message_(true),
2952 rethrow_(false) {
2953 ResetInternal();
2954 // Special handling for simulators which have a separate JS stack.
2955 js_stack_comparable_address_ = static_cast<internal::Address>(
2956 i::SimulatorStack::RegisterJSStackComparableAddress(i_isolate_));
2957 i_isolate_->RegisterTryCatchHandler(this);
2958}
2959
2960namespace {
2961
2962i::Tagged<i::Object> ToObject(void* object) {
2963 return i::Tagged<i::Object>(reinterpret_cast<i::Address>(object));
2964}
2965
2966} // namespace
2967
2968v8::TryCatch::~TryCatch() {
2969 if (HasCaught()) {
2970 if (rethrow_ || (V8_UNLIKELY(HasTerminated()) &&
2971 !i_isolate_->thread_local_top()->CallDepthIsZero())) {
2972 if (capture_message_) {
2973 // If an exception was caught and rethrow_ is indicated, the saved
2974 // message, script, and location need to be restored to Isolate TLS
2975 // for reuse. capture_message_ needs to be disabled so that Throw()
2976 // does not create a new message.
2977 i_isolate_->thread_local_top()->rethrowing_message_ = true;
2978 i_isolate_->set_pending_message(ToObject(message_obj_));
2979 }
2980 i_isolate_->UnregisterTryCatchHandler(this);
2981 i_isolate_->clear_internal_exception();
2982 i_isolate_->Throw(ToObject(exception_));
2983 return;
2984 }
2985 Reset();
2986 }
2987 i_isolate_->UnregisterTryCatchHandler(this);
2988 DCHECK_IMPLIES(rethrow_,
2989 !i_isolate_->thread_local_top()->rethrowing_message_);
2990}
2991
2992void* v8::TryCatch::operator new(size_t) { base::OS::Abort(); }
2993void* v8::TryCatch::operator new[](size_t) { base::OS::Abort(); }
2994void v8::TryCatch::operator delete(void*, size_t) { base::OS::Abort(); }
2995void v8::TryCatch::operator delete[](void*, size_t) { base::OS::Abort(); }
2996
2997bool v8::TryCatch::HasCaught() const {
2998 return !IsTheHole(ToObject(exception_), i_isolate_);
2999}
3000
3001bool v8::TryCatch::CanContinue() const { return can_continue_; }
3002
3003bool v8::TryCatch::HasTerminated() const {
3004 return ToObject(exception_) ==
3005 i::ReadOnlyRoots(i_isolate_).termination_exception();
3006}
3007
3008v8::Local<v8::Value> v8::TryCatch::ReThrow() {
3009 if (!HasCaught()) return v8::Local<v8::Value>();
3010 rethrow_ = true;
3011 return v8::Undefined(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate_));
3012}
3013
3014v8::Local<Value> v8::TryCatch::Exception() const {
3015 if (!HasCaught()) return v8::Local<Value>();
3016 if (HasTerminated()) {
3017 return v8::Utils::ToLocal(i_isolate_->factory()->null_value());
3018 }
3019 return v8::Utils::ToLocal(i::direct_handle(ToObject(exception_), i_isolate_));
3020}
3021
3022MaybeLocal<Value> v8::TryCatch::StackTrace(Local<Context> context,
3023 Local<Value> exception) {
3024 auto i_exception = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*exception);
3025 if (!IsJSObject(*i_exception)) return v8::Local<Value>();
3026 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, TryCatch, StackTrace);
3027 auto obj = i::Cast<i::JSObject>(i_exception);
3028 i::DirectHandle<i::String> name = i_isolate->factory()->stack_string();
3029 Maybe<bool> maybe = i::JSReceiver::HasProperty(i_isolate, obj, name);
3030 has_exception = maybe.IsNothing();
3031 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Value);
3032 if (!maybe.FromJust()) return v8::Local<Value>();
3033 Local<Value> result;
3034 has_exception = !ToLocal<Value>(
3035 i::JSReceiver::GetProperty(i_isolate, obj, name), &result);
3036 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Value);
3037 RETURN_ESCAPED(result);
3038}
3039
3040MaybeLocal<Value> v8::TryCatch::StackTrace(Local<Context> context) const {
3041 if (!HasCaught()) return v8::Local<Value>();
3042 return StackTrace(context, Exception());
3043}
3044
3045v8::Local<v8::Message> v8::TryCatch::Message() const {
3046 i::Tagged<i::Object> message = ToObject(message_obj_);
3047 DCHECK(IsJSMessageObject(message) || IsTheHole(message, i_isolate_));
3048 if (HasCaught() && !IsTheHole(message, i_isolate_)) {
3049 return v8::Utils::MessageToLocal(i::direct_handle(message, i_isolate_));
3050 } else {
3051 return v8::Local<v8::Message>();
3052 }
3053}
3054
3055void v8::TryCatch::Reset() {
3056 if (rethrow_) return;
3057 if (V8_UNLIKELY(i_isolate_->is_execution_terminating()) &&
3058 !i_isolate_->thread_local_top()->CallDepthIsZero()) {
3059 return;
3060 }
3061 i_isolate_->clear_internal_exception();
3062 i_isolate_->clear_pending_message();
3063 ResetInternal();
3064}
3065
3066void v8::TryCatch::ResetInternal() {
3067 i::Tagged<i::Object> the_hole = i::ReadOnlyRoots(i_isolate_).the_hole_value();
3068 exception_ = reinterpret_cast<void*>(the_hole.ptr());
3069 message_obj_ = reinterpret_cast<void*>(the_hole.ptr());
3070}

3073
3074bool v8::TryCatch::IsVerbose() const { return is_verbose_; }
3075
3076void v8::TryCatch::SetCaptureMessage(bool value) { capture_message_ = value; }

3102
3103void ScriptOrigin::VerifyHostDefinedOptions() const {
3104 // TODO(cbruni, chromium:1244145): Remove checks once we allow arbitrary
3105 // host-defined options.
3106 if (host_defined_options_.IsEmpty()) return;
3107 Utils::ApiCheck(host_defined_options_->IsFixedArray(), "ScriptOrigin()",
3108 "Host-defined options has to be a PrimitiveArray");
3109 auto options =
3110 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*host_defined_options_.As<FixedArray>());
3111 for (int i = 0; i < options->length(); i++) {
3112 Utils::ApiCheck(i::IsPrimitive(options->get(i)), "ScriptOrigin()",
3113 "PrimitiveArray can only contain primtive values");
3114 }
3115}

3174
3175int Message::GetWasmFunctionIndex() const {
3176#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3177 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
3178 i::Isolate* i_isolate = self->GetIsolate();
3179 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
3180 HandleScope handle_scope(reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(i_isolate));
3181 i::JSMessageObject::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(i_isolate, self);
3182 int start_position = self->GetColumnNumber();
3183 if (start_position == -1) return Message::kNoWasmFunctionIndexInfo;
3184
3185 i::DirectHandle<i::Script> script(self->script(), i_isolate);
3186
3187 if (script->type() != i::Script::Type::kWasm) {
3188 return Message::kNoWasmFunctionIndexInfo;
3189 }
3190
3191 auto debug_script = ToApiHandle<debug::Script>(script);
3192 return Local<debug::WasmScript>::Cast(debug_script)
3193 ->GetContainingFunction(start_position);
3194#else
3195 return Message::kNoWasmFunctionIndexInfo;
3196#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3197}

3199Maybe<int> Message::GetStartColumn(Local<Context> context) const {
3200 return Just(GetStartColumn());
3201}
3202
3203int Message::GetEndColumn() const {
3204 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
3205 i::Isolate* i_isolate = self->GetIsolate();
3206 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
3207 HandleScope handle_scope(reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(i_isolate));
3208 i::JSMessageObject::EnsureSourcePositionsAvailable(i_isolate, self);
3209 const int column_number = self->GetColumnNumber();
3210 if (column_number == -1) return -1;
3211 const int start = self->GetStartPosition();
3212 const int end = self->GetEndPosition();
3213 return column_number + (end - start);
3214}

3277
3278Local<StackTrace> StackTrace::CurrentStackTrace(Isolate* v8_isolate,
3279 int frame_limit,
3280 StackTraceOptions options) {
3281 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
3282 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
3283 i::DirectHandle<i::StackTraceInfo> stack_trace =
3284 i_isolate->CaptureDetailedStackTrace(frame_limit, options);
3285 return Utils::StackTraceToLocal(stack_trace);
3286}

3288Local<String> StackTrace::CurrentScriptNameOrSourceURL(Isolate* v8_isolate) {

3290 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
3291 i::DirectHandle<i::String> name_or_source_url =
3292 i_isolate->CurrentScriptNameOrSourceURL();

3296// --- S t a c k F r a m e ---
3297
3298Location StackFrame::GetLocation() const {
3299 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
3300 i::Isolate* i_isolate = self->GetIsolate();
3301 i::DirectHandle<i::Script> script(self->script(), i_isolate);
3302 i::Script::PositionInfo info;
3303 CHECK(i::Script::GetPositionInfo(
3304 script, i::StackFrameInfo::GetSourcePosition(self), &info));
3305 if (script->HasSourceURLComment()) {
3306 info.line -= script->line_offset();
3307 if (info.line == 0) {
3308 info.column -= script->column_offset();
3309 }
3310 }
3311 return {info.line, info.column};
3312}
3313
3314int StackFrame::GetSourcePosition() const {
3315 auto self = Utils::OpenHandle(this);
3316
3317 return i::StackFrameInfo::GetSourcePosition(self);
3318}
3319
3320int StackFrame::GetScriptId() const {
3321 return Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this)->script()->id();
3322}

3324Local<String> StackFrame::GetScriptName() const {
3325 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
3326 i::Isolate* i_isolate = self->GetIsolate();
3327 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> name(self->script()->name(), i_isolate);
3328 if (!IsString(*name)) return {};
3329 return Utils::ToLocal(i::Cast<i::String>(name));
3330}

3336 self->script()->GetNameOrSourceURL(), i_isolate);
3337 if (!IsString(*name_or_source_url)) return {};
3338 return Utils::ToLocal(i::Cast<i::String>(name_or_source_url));

3341Local<String> StackFrame::GetScriptSource() const {

3343 i::Isolate* i_isolate = self->GetIsolate();
3344 if (!self->script()->HasValidSource()) return {};
3345 i::DirectHandle<i::PrimitiveHeapObject> source(self->script()->source(),
3346 i_isolate);
3347 if (!IsString(*source)) return {};
3348 return Utils::ToLocal(i::Cast<i::String>(source));
3349}

3384// --- J S O N ---
3385
3386MaybeLocal<Value> JSON::Parse(Local<Context> context,
3387 Local<String> json_string) {
3388 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, JSON, Parse);
3389 auto string = Utils::OpenHandle(*json_string);
3390 i::Handle<i::String> source = i::String::Flatten(i_isolate, string);
3391 i::Handle<i::Object> undefined = i_isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
3392 auto maybe =
3393 source->IsOneByteRepresentation()
3394 ? i::JsonParser<uint8_t>::Parse(i_isolate, source, undefined)
3395 : i::JsonParser<uint16_t>::Parse(i_isolate, source, undefined);
3396 Local<Value> result;
3397 has_exception = !ToLocal<Value>(maybe, &result);
3398 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Value);
3399 RETURN_ESCAPED(result);
3400}
3401
3402MaybeLocal<String> JSON::Stringify(Local<Context> context,
3403 Local<Value> json_object,
3404 Local<String> gap) {
3405 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, JSON, Stringify);
3406 i::Handle<i::JSAny> object;
3407 if (!Utils::ApiCheck(
3408 i::TryCast<i::JSAny>(Utils::OpenHandle(*json_object), &object),
3409 "JSON::Stringify",
3410 "Invalid object, must be a JSON-serializable object.")) {
3411 return {};
3412 }
3413 i::Handle<i::Undefined> replacer = i_isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
3414 i::Handle<i::String> gap_string = gap.IsEmpty()
3415 ? i_isolate->factory()->empty_string()
3416 : Utils::OpenHandle(*gap);
3417 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> maybe;
3418 has_exception = !i::JsonStringify(i_isolate, object, replacer, gap_string)
3419 .ToHandle(&maybe);
3420 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(String);
3421 Local<String> result;
3422 has_exception =
3423 !ToLocal<String>(i::Object::ToString(i_isolate, maybe), &result);
3424 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(String);
3425 RETURN_ESCAPED(result);
3426}

3597struct ValueDeserializer::PrivateData {
3598 PrivateData(i::Isolate* i_isolate, base::Vector<const uint8_t> data,
3599 Delegate* delegate)
3600 : isolate(i_isolate), deserializer(i_isolate, data, delegate) {}
3601 i::Isolate* isolate;
3602 i::ValueDeserializer deserializer;
3603 bool supports_legacy_wire_format = false;
3604};
3605
3606ValueDeserializer::ValueDeserializer(Isolate* v8_isolate, const uint8_t* data,
3607 size_t size)
3608 : ValueDeserializer(v8_isolate, data, size, nullptr) {}
3609
3610ValueDeserializer::ValueDeserializer(Isolate* v8_isolate, const uint8_t* data,
3611 size_t size, Delegate* delegate) {
3612 private_ = new PrivateData(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate),
3613 base::Vector<const uint8_t>(data, size), delegate);
3614}
3615
3616ValueDeserializer::~ValueDeserializer() { delete private_; }
3617
3618Maybe<bool> ValueDeserializer::ReadHeader(Local<Context> context) {
3619 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
3620 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT(i_isolate, context, ValueDeserializer, ReadHeader,
3621 i::HandleScope);
3622
3623 bool read_header = false;
3624 has_exception = !private_->deserializer.ReadHeader().To(&read_header);
3625 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
3626 DCHECK(read_header);
3627
3628 static const uint32_t kMinimumNonLegacyVersion = 13;
3629 if (GetWireFormatVersion() < kMinimumNonLegacyVersion &&
3630 !private_->supports_legacy_wire_format) {
3631 i_isolate->Throw(*i_isolate->factory()->NewError(
3632 i::MessageTemplate::kDataCloneDeserializationVersionError));
3633 has_exception = true;
3634 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
3635 }
3636
3637 return Just(true);
3638}
3639
3640void ValueDeserializer::SetSupportsLegacyWireFormat(
3641 bool supports_legacy_wire_format) {
3642 private_->supports_legacy_wire_format = supports_legacy_wire_format;
3643}
3644
3645uint32_t ValueDeserializer::GetWireFormatVersion() const {
3646 return private_->deserializer.GetWireFormatVersion();
3647}
3648
3649MaybeLocal<Value> ValueDeserializer::ReadValue(Local<Context> context) {
3650 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, ValueDeserializer, ReadValue);
3651 i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::Object> result;
3652 if (GetWireFormatVersion() > 0) {
3653 result = private_->deserializer.ReadObjectWrapper();
3654 } else {
3655 result =
3656 private_->deserializer.ReadObjectUsingEntireBufferForLegacyFormat();
3657 }
3658 Local<Value> value;
3659 has_exception = !ToLocal(result, &value);
3660 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Value);
3661 RETURN_ESCAPED(value);
3662}

3766 Utils::ApiCheck(i::v8_flags.js_float16array, "Value::IsFloat16Array",
3767 "Float16Array is not supported");

3837bool Value::IsInt32() const {
3838 i::Tagged<i::Object> obj = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
3839 if (i::IsSmi(obj)) return true;
3840 if (i::IsNumber(obj)) {
3841 return i::IsInt32Double(i::Object::NumberValue(i::Cast<i::Number>(obj)));
3842 }
3843 return false;
3844}
3845
3846bool Value::IsUint32() const {
3847 auto obj = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
3848 if (i::IsSmi(obj)) return i::Smi::ToInt(obj) >= 0;
3849 if (i::IsNumber(obj)) {
3850 double value = i::Object::NumberValue(i::Cast<i::Number>(obj));
3851 return !i::IsMinusZero(value) && value >= 0 && value <= i::kMaxUInt32 &&
3852 value == i::FastUI2D(i::FastD2UI(value));
3853 }
3854 return false;
3855}

3867 if (!IsJSFunction(obj)) return false;
3868 auto func = i::Cast<i::JSFunction>(obj);
3869 return i::IsAsyncFunction(func->shared()->kind());
3870}
3871
3872bool Value::IsGeneratorFunction() const {
3873 auto obj = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
3874 if (!IsJSFunction(obj)) return false;
3875 auto func = i::Cast<i::JSFunction>(obj);
3876 DCHECK_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(func->GetIsolate());
3877 return i::IsGeneratorFunction(func->shared()->kind());
3878}

3882}

3900MaybeLocal<String> Value::ToString(Local<Context> context) const {
3901 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
3902 if (i::IsString(*obj)) return ToApiHandle<String>(obj);
3903 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, Object, ToString);
3904 Local<String> result;
3905 has_exception =
3906 !ToLocal<String>(i::Object::ToString(i_isolate, obj), &result);
3907 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(String);
3908 RETURN_ESCAPED(result);
3909}
3910
3911MaybeLocal<String> Value::ToDetailString(Local<Context> context) const {
3912 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
3913 i::Isolate* i_isolate;
3914 if (!context.IsEmpty()) {
3915 i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
3916 } else if (IsSmi(*obj) || !i::GetIsolateFromHeapObject(
3917 i::Cast<i::HeapObject>(*obj), &i_isolate)) {
3918 i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
3919 }
3920 if (i::IsString(*obj)) return ToApiHandle<String>(obj);
3921 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
3922 return Utils::ToLocal(i::Object::NoSideEffectsToString(i_isolate, obj));
3923}

3931 !ToLocal<Object>(i::Object::ToObject(i_isolate, obj), &result);

3933 RETURN_ESCAPED(result);
3934}

4029namespace api_internal {
4030i::Address ConvertToJSGlobalProxyIfNecessary(i::Address holder_ptr) {
4031 i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> holder =
4032 i::Cast<i::HeapObject>(i::Tagged<i::Object>(holder_ptr));
4033
4034 if (i::IsJSGlobalObject(holder)) {
4035 return i::Cast<i::JSGlobalObject>(holder)->global_proxy().ptr();
4036 }
4037 return holder_ptr;
4038}
4039} // namespace api_internal

4041bool i::ShouldThrowOnError(i::Isolate* i_isolate) {
4042 return i::GetShouldThrow(i_isolate, Nothing<i::ShouldThrow>()) ==
4043 i::ShouldThrow::kThrowOnError;
4044}

4230
4231// static
4232std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore> v8::BackingStore::Reallocate(
4233 v8::Isolate* v8_isolate, std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore> backing_store,
4234 size_t byte_length) {
4235 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
4236 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, ArrayBuffer, BackingStore_Reallocate);
4237 Utils::ApiCheck(byte_length <= i::JSArrayBuffer::kMaxByteLength,
4238 "v8::BackingStore::Reallocate", "byte_length is too large");
4239 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
4240 i::BackingStore* i_backing_store =
4241 reinterpret_cast<i::BackingStore*>(backing_store.get());
4242 if (!i_backing_store->Reallocate(i_isolate, byte_length)) {
4243 i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(i_isolate, "v8::BackingStore::Reallocate");
4244 }
4245 return backing_store;
4246}
4247
4248// static
4249void v8::BackingStore::EmptyDeleter(void* data, size_t length,
4250 void* deleter_data) {
4251 DCHECK_NULL(deleter_data);
4252}
4253
4254std::shared_ptr<v8::BackingStore> v8::ArrayBuffer::GetBackingStore() {
4255 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4256 std::shared_ptr<i::BackingStore> backing_store = self->GetBackingStore();
4257 if (!backing_store) {
4258 backing_store =
4259 i::BackingStore::EmptyBackingStore(i::SharedFlag::kNotShared);
4260 }
4261 std::shared_ptr<i::BackingStoreBase> bs_base = backing_store;
4262 return std::static_pointer_cast<v8::BackingStore>(bs_base);
4263}

4307 void v8::Type##Array::CheckCast(Value* that) { \
4308 auto obj = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(that); \
4309 Utils::ApiCheck( \
4310 i::IsJSTypedArray(obj) && i::Cast<i::JSTypedArray>(obj)->type() == \
4311 i::kExternal##Type##Array, \
4312 "v8::" #Type "Array::Cast()", "Value is not a " #Type "Array"); \
4313 }

4381
4382Maybe<double> Value::NumberValue(Local<Context> context) const {
4383 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4384 if (i::IsNumber(*obj)) {
4385 return Just(i::Object::NumberValue(i::Cast<i::Number>(*obj)));
4386 }
4387 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
4388 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Value, NumberValue, i::HandleScope);
4389 i::DirectHandle<i::Number> num;
4390 has_exception = !i::Object::ToNumber(i_isolate, obj).ToHandle(&num);
4391 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(double);
4392 return Just(i::Object::NumberValue(*num));
4393}
4394
4395Maybe<int64_t> Value::IntegerValue(Local<Context> context) const {
4396 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4397 if (i::IsNumber(*obj)) {
4398 return Just(NumberToInt64(*obj));
4399 }
4400 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
4401 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Value, IntegerValue, i::HandleScope);
4402 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> num;
4403 has_exception = !i::Object::ToInteger(i_isolate, obj).ToHandle(&num);
4404 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(int64_t);
4405 return Just(NumberToInt64(*num));
4406}
4407
4408Maybe<int32_t> Value::Int32Value(Local<Context> context) const {
4409 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4410 if (i::IsNumber(*obj)) return Just(NumberToInt32(*obj));
4411 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
4412 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Value, Int32Value, i::HandleScope);
4413 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> num;
4414 has_exception = !i::Object::ToInt32(i_isolate, obj).ToHandle(&num);
4415 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(int32_t);
4416 return Just(IsSmi(*num) ? i::Smi::ToInt(*num)
4417 : static_cast<int32_t>(
4418 i::Cast<i::HeapNumber>(*num)->value()));
4419}
4420
4421Maybe<uint32_t> Value::Uint32Value(Local<Context> context) const {
4422 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4423 if (i::IsNumber(*obj)) return Just(NumberToUint32(*obj));
4424 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
4425 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Value, Uint32Value, i::HandleScope);
4426 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> num;
4427 has_exception = !i::Object::ToUint32(i_isolate, obj).ToHandle(&num);
4428 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(uint32_t);
4429 return Just(IsSmi(*num) ? static_cast<uint32_t>(i::Smi::ToInt(*num))
4430 : static_cast<uint32_t>(
4431 i::Cast<i::HeapNumber>(*num)->value()));
4432}
4433
4434MaybeLocal<Uint32> Value::ToArrayIndex(Local<Context> context) const {
4435 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4436 if (i::IsSmi(*self)) {
4437 if (i::Smi::ToInt(*self) >= 0) return Utils::Uint32ToLocal(self);
4438 return Local<Uint32>();
4439 }
4440 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, Object, ToArrayIndex);
4441 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> string_obj;
4442 has_exception = !i::Object::ToString(i_isolate, self).ToHandle(&string_obj);
4443 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Uint32);
4444 auto str = i::Cast<i::String>(string_obj);
4445 uint32_t index;
4446 if (str->AsArrayIndex(&index)) {
4447 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> value;
4448 if (index <= static_cast<uint32_t>(i::Smi::kMaxValue)) {
4449 value = direct_handle(i::Smi::FromInt(index), i_isolate);
4450 } else {
4451 value = i_isolate->factory()->NewNumber(index);
4452 }
4453 RETURN_ESCAPED(Utils::Uint32ToLocal(value));
4454 }
4455 return Local<Uint32>();
4456}

4460 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Value, Equals, i::HandleScope);

4463 Maybe<bool> result = i::Object::Equals(i_isolate, self, other);
4464 has_exception = result.IsNothing();
4465 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);

4467}

4489Maybe<bool> Value::InstanceOf(v8::Local<v8::Context> context,
4490 v8::Local<v8::Object> object) {
4491 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
4492 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Value, InstanceOf, i::HandleScope);
4493 i::DirectHandle<i::JSAny> left;
4494 if (!Utils::ApiCheck(
4495 i::TryCast<i::JSAny>(Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this), &left),
4496 "Value::InstanceOf",
4497 "Invalid type, must be a JS primitive or object.")) {
4498 return Nothing<bool>();
4499 }
4500 auto right = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*object);
4501 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> result;
4502 has_exception =
4503 !i::Object::InstanceOf(i_isolate, left, right).ToHandle(&result);
4504 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
4505 return Just(i::IsTrue(*result, i_isolate));
4506}

4558Maybe<bool> v8::Object::CreateDataProperty(v8::Local<v8::Context> context,
4559 v8::Local<Name> key,
4560 v8::Local<Value> value) {
4561 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());

4564 auto value_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
4565

4567 if (i::IsJSObject(*self)) {

4569 i::HandleScope);
4570 Maybe<bool> result = i::JSObject::CreateDataProperty(
4571 i_isolate, i::Cast<i::JSObject>(self), lookup_key, value_obj,
4572 Just(i::kDontThrow));
4573 has_exception = result.IsNothing();
4574 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
4575 return result;
4576 }
4577 // JSProxy or WasmObject or other non-JSObject.
4578 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Object, CreateDataProperty, i::HandleScope);
4579 Maybe<bool> result = i::JSReceiver::CreateDataProperty(
4580 i_isolate, self, lookup_key, value_obj, Just(i::kDontThrow));
4581 has_exception = result.IsNothing();
4582 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
4583 return result;
4584}

4613struct v8::PropertyDescriptor::PrivateData {

4615 i::PropertyDescriptor desc;
4616};

4620// DataDescriptor
4621v8::PropertyDescriptor::PropertyDescriptor(v8::Local<v8::Value> value)
4622 : private_(new PrivateData()) {
4623 private_->desc.set_value(
4624 Cast<i::JSAny>(Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value, true)));
4625}

4630 : private_(new PrivateData()) {

4632 Cast<i::JSAny>(Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value, true)));

4634}

4640 DCHECK(get.IsEmpty() || get->IsUndefined() || get->IsFunction());
4641 DCHECK(set.IsEmpty() || set->IsUndefined() || set->IsFunction());
4642 private_->desc.set_get(Cast<i::JSAny>(Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*get, true)));
4643 private_->desc.set_set(Cast<i::JSAny>(Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*set, true)));
4644}

4707
4708Maybe<bool> v8::Object::DefineOwnProperty(v8::Local<v8::Context> context,
4709 v8::Local<Name> key,
4710 v8::Local<Value> value,
4711 v8::PropertyAttribute attributes) {
4712 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
4713 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4714 auto key_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
4715 auto value_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
4716
4717 i::PropertyDescriptor desc;
4718 desc.set_writable(!(attributes & v8::ReadOnly));
4719 desc.set_enumerable(!(attributes & v8::DontEnum));
4720 desc.set_configurable(!(attributes & v8::DontDelete));
4721 desc.set_value(i::Cast<i::JSAny>(value_obj));
4722
4723 if (i::IsJSObject(*self)) {
4724 // If it's not a JSProxy, i::JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty should never run
4725 // a script.
4726 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT(i_isolate, context, Object, DefineOwnProperty,
4727 i::HandleScope);
4728 Maybe<bool> success = i::JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty(
4729 i_isolate, self, key_obj, &desc, Just(i::kDontThrow));
4730 has_exception = success.IsNothing();
4731 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
4732 return success;
4733 }
4734 // JSProxy or WasmObject or other non-JSObject.
4735 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Object, DefineOwnProperty, i::HandleScope);
4736 Maybe<bool> success = i::JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty(
4737 i_isolate, self, key_obj, &desc, Just(i::kDontThrow));
4738 // Even though we said kDontThrow, there might be accessors that do throw.
4739 has_exception = success.IsNothing();
4740 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
4741 return success;
4742}
4743
4744Maybe<bool> v8::Object::DefineProperty(v8::Local<v8::Context> context,
4745 v8::Local<Name> key,
4746 PropertyDescriptor& descriptor) {
4747 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
4748 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Object, DefineOwnProperty, i::HandleScope);
4749 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4750 auto key_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
4751
4752 Maybe<bool> success = i::JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty(
4753 i_isolate, self, key_obj, &descriptor.get_private()->desc,
4754 Just(i::kDontThrow));
4755 has_exception = success.IsNothing();
4756 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
4757 return success;
4758}
4759
4760Maybe<bool> v8::Object::SetPrivate(Local<Context> context, Local<Private> key,
4761 Local<Value> value) {
4762 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
4763 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT(i_isolate, context, Object, SetPrivate, i::HandleScope);
4764 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4765 auto key_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(reinterpret_cast<Name*>(*key));
4766 auto value_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
4767 if (i::IsJSObject(*self)) {
4768 auto js_object = i::Cast<i::JSObject>(self);
4769 i::LookupIterator it(i_isolate, js_object, key_obj, js_object);
4770 has_exception = i::JSObject::DefineOwnPropertyIgnoreAttributes(
4771 &it, value_obj, i::DONT_ENUM)
4772 .is_null();
4773 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
4774 return Just(true);
4775 }
4776 if (i::IsJSProxy(*self)) {
4777 i::PropertyDescriptor desc;
4778 desc.set_writable(true);
4779 desc.set_enumerable(false);
4780 desc.set_configurable(true);
4781 desc.set_value(i::Cast<i::JSAny>(value_obj));
4782 return i::JSProxy::SetPrivateSymbol(i_isolate, i::Cast<i::JSProxy>(self),
4783 i::Cast<i::Symbol>(key_obj), &desc,
4784 Just(i::kDontThrow));
4785 }
4786 // Wasm object, or other kind of special object not supported here.
4787 return Just(false);
4788}

4800}

4833
4834Maybe<PropertyAttribute> v8::Object::GetPropertyAttributes(
4835 Local<Context> context, Local<Value> key) {
4836 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
4837 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Object, GetPropertyAttributes, i::HandleScope);
4838 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4839 auto key_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
4840 if (!i::IsName(*key_obj)) {
4841 has_exception = !i::Object::ToString(i_isolate, key_obj).ToHandle(&key_obj);
4842 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(PropertyAttribute);
4843 }
4844 auto key_name = i::Cast<i::Name>(key_obj);
4845 auto result = i::JSReceiver::GetPropertyAttributes(i_isolate, self, key_name);
4846 has_exception = result.IsNothing();
4847 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(PropertyAttribute);
4848 if (result.FromJust() == i::ABSENT) {
4849 return Just(static_cast<PropertyAttribute>(i::NONE));
4850 }
4851 return Just(static_cast<PropertyAttribute>(result.FromJust()));
4852}
4853
4854MaybeLocal<Value> v8::Object::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(Local<Context> context,
4855 Local<Name> key) {
4856 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, Object, GetOwnPropertyDescriptor);
4857 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4858 auto key_name = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
4859
4860 i::PropertyDescriptor desc;
4861 Maybe<bool> found =
4862 i::JSReceiver::GetOwnPropertyDescriptor(i_isolate, obj, key_name, &desc);
4863 has_exception = found.IsNothing();
4864 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Value);
4865 if (!found.FromJust()) {
4866 return v8::Undefined(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
4867 }
4868 RETURN_ESCAPED(Utils::ToLocal(desc.ToObject(i_isolate)));
4869}

4871Local<Value> v8::Object::GetPrototype() {
4872 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4873 auto i_isolate = self->GetIsolate();
4874 i::PrototypeIterator iter(i_isolate, self);
4875 return Utils::ToLocal(i::PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent(iter));
4876}
4877
4878Local<Value> v8::Object::GetPrototypeV2() {
4879 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4880 auto i_isolate = self->GetIsolate();
4881 i::PrototypeIterator iter(i_isolate, self);
4882 if (i::IsJSGlobalProxy(*self)) {
4883 // Skip hidden prototype (i.e. JSGlobalObject).
4884 iter.Advance();
4885 }
4886 DCHECK(!i::IsJSGlobalObject(*i::PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent(iter)));
4887 return Utils::ToLocal(i::PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent(iter));
4888}

4890namespace {
4891
4892Maybe<bool> SetPrototypeImpl(v8::Object* this_, Local<Context> context,
4893 Local<Value> value, bool from_javascript) {
4894 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
4895 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this_);
4896 auto value_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
4897 // TODO(333672197): turn this to DCHECK once it's no longer possible
4898 // to get JSGlobalObject via API.
4899 CHECK_IMPLIES(from_javascript, !i::IsJSGlobalObject(*value_obj));
4900 if (i::IsJSObject(*self)) {
4901 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
4902 // TODO(333672197): turn this to DCHECK once it's no longer possible
4903 // to get JSGlobalObject via API.
4904 CHECK_IMPLIES(from_javascript, !i::IsJSGlobalObject(*self));
4905 auto result =
4906 i::JSObject::SetPrototype(i_isolate, i::Cast<i::JSObject>(self),
4907 value_obj, from_javascript, i::kDontThrow);
4908 if (!result.FromJust()) return Nothing<bool>();
4909 return Just(true);
4910 }
4911 if (i::IsJSProxy(*self)) {
4912 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Object, SetPrototype, i::HandleScope);
4913 // We do not allow exceptions thrown while setting the prototype
4914 // to propagate outside.
4915 TryCatch try_catch(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
4916 auto result =
4917 i::JSProxy::SetPrototype(i_isolate, i::Cast<i::JSProxy>(self),
4918 value_obj, from_javascript, i::kThrowOnError);
4919 has_exception = result.IsNothing();
4920 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
4921 return Just(true);
4922 }
4923 // Wasm object or other kind of special object not supported here.
4924 return Nothing<bool>();
4925}
4926
4927} // namespace
4928
4929Maybe<bool> v8::Object::SetPrototype(Local<Context> context,
4930 Local<Value> value) {
4931 static constexpr bool from_javascript = false;
4932 return SetPrototypeImpl(this, context, value, from_javascript);
4933}
4934
4935Maybe<bool> v8::Object::SetPrototypeV2(Local<Context> context,
4936 Local<Value> value) {
4937 static constexpr bool from_javascript = true;
4938 return SetPrototypeImpl(this, context, value, from_javascript);
4939}
4940
4941Local<Object> v8::Object::FindInstanceInPrototypeChain(
4942 v8::Local<FunctionTemplate> tmpl) {
4943 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4944 auto i_isolate = self->GetIsolate();
4945 i::PrototypeIterator iter(i_isolate, *self, i::kStartAtReceiver);
4946 i::Tagged<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> tmpl_info =
4947 *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*tmpl);
4948 if (!IsJSObject(iter.GetCurrent())) return Local<Object>();
4949 while (!tmpl_info->IsTemplateFor(iter.GetCurrent<i::JSObject>())) {
4950 iter.Advance();
4951 if (iter.IsAtEnd()) return Local<Object>();
4952 if (!IsJSObject(iter.GetCurrent())) return Local<Object>();
4953 }
4954 // IsTemplateFor() ensures that iter.GetCurrent() can't be a Proxy here.
4955 return Utils::ToLocal(
4956 i::direct_handle(iter.GetCurrent<i::JSObject>(), i_isolate));
4957}
4958
4959MaybeLocal<Array> v8::Object::GetPropertyNames(Local<Context> context) {
4960 return GetPropertyNames(
4961 context, v8::KeyCollectionMode::kIncludePrototypes,
4962 static_cast<v8::PropertyFilter>(ONLY_ENUMERABLE | SKIP_SYMBOLS),
4963 v8::IndexFilter::kIncludeIndices);
4964}
4965
4966MaybeLocal<Array> v8::Object::GetPropertyNames(
4967 Local<Context> context, KeyCollectionMode mode,
4968 PropertyFilter property_filter, IndexFilter index_filter,
4969 KeyConversionMode key_conversion) {
4970 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, Object, GetPropertyNames);
4971 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
4972 i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArray> value;
4973 i::KeyAccumulator accumulator(
4974 i_isolate, static_cast<i::KeyCollectionMode>(mode),
4975 static_cast<i::PropertyFilter>(property_filter));
4976 accumulator.set_skip_indices(index_filter == IndexFilter::kSkipIndices);
4977 has_exception = accumulator.CollectKeys(self, self).IsNothing();
4978 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Array);
4979 value =
4980 accumulator.GetKeys(static_cast<i::GetKeysConversion>(key_conversion));
4981 DCHECK(self->map()->EnumLength() == i::kInvalidEnumCacheSentinel ||
4982 self->map()->EnumLength() == 0 ||
4983 self->map()->instance_descriptors(i_isolate)->enum_cache()->keys() !=
4984 *value);
4985 auto result = i_isolate->factory()->NewJSArrayWithElements(value);
4986 RETURN_ESCAPED(Utils::ToLocal(result));
4987}
4988
4989MaybeLocal<Array> v8::Object::GetOwnPropertyNames(Local<Context> context) {
4990 return GetOwnPropertyNames(
4991 context, static_cast<v8::PropertyFilter>(ONLY_ENUMERABLE | SKIP_SYMBOLS));
4992}
4993
4994MaybeLocal<Array> v8::Object::GetOwnPropertyNames(
4995 Local<Context> context, PropertyFilter filter,
4996 KeyConversionMode key_conversion) {
4997 return GetPropertyNames(context, KeyCollectionMode::kOwnOnly, filter,
4998 v8::IndexFilter::kIncludeIndices, key_conversion);
4999}

5001MaybeLocal<String> v8::Object::ObjectProtoToString(Local<Context> context) {
5002 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, Object, ObjectProtoToString);
5003 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5004 Local<Value> result;
5005 has_exception =
5006 !ToLocal<Value>(i::Execution::CallBuiltin(
5007 i_isolate, i_isolate->object_to_string(), self, {}),
5008 &result);
5009 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(String);
5010 RETURN_ESCAPED(Local<String>::Cast(result));
5011}

5040
5041Maybe<bool> v8::Object::Delete(Local<Context> context, Local<Value> key) {
5042 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
5043 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5044 auto key_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
5045 if (i::IsJSProxy(*self)) {
5046 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Object, Delete, i::HandleScope);
5047 Maybe<bool> result = i::Runtime::DeleteObjectProperty(
5048 i_isolate, self, key_obj, i::LanguageMode::kSloppy);
5049 has_exception = result.IsNothing();
5050 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
5051 return result;
5052 } else {
5053 // If it's not a JSProxy, i::Runtime::DeleteObjectProperty should never run
5054 // a script.
5055 DCHECK(i::IsJSObject(*self) || i::IsWasmObject(*self));
5056 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT(i_isolate, context, Object, Delete, i::HandleScope);
5057 Maybe<bool> result = i::Runtime::DeleteObjectProperty(
5058 i_isolate, self, key_obj, i::LanguageMode::kSloppy);
5059 has_exception = result.IsNothing();
5060 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
5061 return result;
5062 }
5063}

5065Maybe<bool> v8::Object::DeletePrivate(Local<Context> context,

5077 return result;
5078}
5079
5080Maybe<bool> v8::Object::Has(Local<Context> context, Local<Value> key) {
5081 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
5082 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Object, Has, i::HandleScope);
5083 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5084 auto key_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
5085 Maybe<bool> maybe = Nothing<bool>();
5086 // Check if the given key is an array index.
5087 uint32_t index = 0;
5088 if (i::Object::ToArrayIndex(*key_obj, &index)) {
5089 maybe = i::JSReceiver::HasElement(i_isolate, self, index);
5090 } else {
5091 // Convert the key to a name - possibly by calling back into JavaScript.
5092 i::DirectHandle<i::Name> name;
5093 if (i::Object::ToName(i_isolate, key_obj).ToHandle(&name)) {
5094 maybe = i::JSReceiver::HasProperty(i_isolate, self, name);
5095 }
5096 }
5097 has_exception = maybe.IsNothing();
5098 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
5099 return maybe;
5100}
5101
5102Maybe<bool> v8::Object::HasPrivate(Local<Context> context, Local<Private> key) {
5103 return HasOwnProperty(context, key.UnsafeAs<Name>());
5104}

5125
5126template <typename Getter, typename Setter, typename Data>
5127static Maybe<bool> ObjectSetAccessor(Local<Context> context, Object* self,
5128 Local<Name> name, Getter getter,
5129 Setter setter, Data data,
5130 PropertyAttribute attributes,
5131 bool replace_on_access,
5132 SideEffectType getter_side_effect_type,
5133 SideEffectType setter_side_effect_type) {
5134 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
5135 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT(i_isolate, context, Object, SetAccessor, i::HandleScope);
5136 if (!IsJSObject(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(self))) return Just(false);
5137 auto obj = i::Cast<i::JSObject>(Utils::OpenHandle(self));
5138 i::DirectHandle<i::AccessorInfo> info = MakeAccessorInfo(
5139 i_isolate, name, getter, setter, data, replace_on_access);
5140 info->set_getter_side_effect_type(getter_side_effect_type);
5141 info->set_setter_side_effect_type(setter_side_effect_type);
5142 if (info.is_null()) return Nothing<bool>();
5143 bool fast = obj->HasFastProperties();
5144 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> result;
5145
5146 i::DirectHandle<i::Name> accessor_name(info->name(), i_isolate);
5147 i::PropertyAttributes attrs = static_cast<i::PropertyAttributes>(attributes);
5148 has_exception = !i::JSObject::SetAccessor(obj, accessor_name, info, attrs)
5149 .ToHandle(&result);
5150 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
5151 if (i::IsUndefined(*result, i_isolate)) return Just(false);
5152 if (fast) {
5153 i::JSObject::MigrateSlowToFast(obj, 0, "APISetAccessor");
5154 }
5155 return Just(true);
5156}
5157
5158void Object::SetAccessorProperty(Local<Name> name, Local<Function> getter,
5159 Local<Function> setter,
5160 PropertyAttribute attributes) {
5161 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5162 i::Isolate* i_isolate = self->GetIsolate();
5163 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
5164 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
5165 if (!IsJSObject(*self)) return;
5166 i::DirectHandle<i::JSReceiver> getter_i =
5167 v8::Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*getter);
5168 i::DirectHandle<i::JSAny> setter_i =
5169 v8::Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*setter, true);
5170 if (setter_i.is_null()) setter_i = i_isolate->factory()->null_value();
5171
5172 i::PropertyDescriptor desc;
5173 desc.set_enumerable(!(attributes & v8::DontEnum));
5174 desc.set_configurable(!(attributes & v8::DontDelete));
5175 desc.set_get(getter_i);
5176 desc.set_set(setter_i);
5177
5178 auto name_i = v8::Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*name);
5179 // DefineOwnProperty might still throw if the receiver is a JSProxy and it
5180 // might fail if the receiver is non-extensible or already has this property
5181 // as non-configurable.
5182 Maybe<bool> success = i::JSReceiver::DefineOwnProperty(
5183 i_isolate, self, name_i, &desc, Just(i::kDontThrow));
5184 USE(success);
5185}
5186
5187Maybe<bool> Object::SetNativeDataProperty(
5188 v8::Local<v8::Context> context, v8::Local<Name> name,
5189 AccessorNameGetterCallback getter, AccessorNameSetterCallback setter,
5190 v8::Local<Value> data, PropertyAttribute attributes,
5191 SideEffectType getter_side_effect_type,
5192 SideEffectType setter_side_effect_type) {
5193 return ObjectSetAccessor(context, this, name, getter, setter, data,
5194 attributes, false, getter_side_effect_type,
5195 setter_side_effect_type);
5196}
5197
5198Maybe<bool> Object::SetLazyDataProperty(
5199 v8::Local<v8::Context> context, v8::Local<Name> name,
5200 AccessorNameGetterCallback getter, v8::Local<Value> data,
5201 PropertyAttribute attributes, SideEffectType getter_side_effect_type,
5202 SideEffectType setter_side_effect_type) {
5203 return ObjectSetAccessor(context, this, name, getter,
5204 static_cast<AccessorNameSetterCallback>(nullptr),
5205 data, attributes, true, getter_side_effect_type,
5206 setter_side_effect_type);
5207}

5286
5287MaybeLocal<Value> v8::Object::GetRealNamedPropertyInPrototypeChain(
5288 Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key) {
5289 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, Object, GetRealNamedPropertyInPrototypeChain);
5290 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5291 if (!IsJSObject(*self)) return MaybeLocal<Value>();
5292 auto key_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
5293 i::PrototypeIterator iter(i_isolate, self);
5294 if (iter.IsAtEnd()) return MaybeLocal<Value>();
5295 i::DirectHandle<i::JSReceiver> proto =
5296 i::PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent<i::JSReceiver>(iter);
5297 i::PropertyKey lookup_key(i_isolate, key_obj);
5298 i::LookupIterator it(i_isolate, self, lookup_key, proto,
5299 i::LookupIterator::PROTOTYPE_CHAIN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
5300 Local<Value> result;
5301 has_exception = !ToLocal<Value>(i::Object::GetProperty(&it), &result);
5302 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Value);
5303 if (!it.IsFound()) return MaybeLocal<Value>();
5304 RETURN_ESCAPED(result);
5305}

5307Maybe<PropertyAttribute>
5308v8::Object::GetRealNamedPropertyAttributesInPrototypeChain(
5309 Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key) {
5310 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
5311 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Object,
5312 GetRealNamedPropertyAttributesInPrototypeChain, i::HandleScope);
5313 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5314 if (!IsJSObject(*self)) return Nothing<PropertyAttribute>();
5315 auto key_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
5316 i::PrototypeIterator iter(i_isolate, self);
5317 if (iter.IsAtEnd()) return Nothing<PropertyAttribute>();
5318 i::DirectHandle<i::JSReceiver> proto =
5319 i::PrototypeIterator::GetCurrent<i::JSReceiver>(iter);
5320 i::PropertyKey lookup_key(i_isolate, key_obj);
5321 i::LookupIterator it(i_isolate, self, lookup_key, proto,
5322 i::LookupIterator::PROTOTYPE_CHAIN_SKIP_INTERCEPTOR);
5323 Maybe<i::PropertyAttributes> result =
5324 i::JSReceiver::GetPropertyAttributes(&it);
5325 has_exception = result.IsNothing();
5326 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(PropertyAttribute);
5327 if (!it.IsFound()) return Nothing<PropertyAttribute>();
5328 if (result.FromJust() == i::ABSENT) return Just(None);
5329 return Just(static_cast<PropertyAttribute>(result.FromJust()));
5330}

5432namespace {
5433V8_INLINE void* GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderDataInCreationContextImpl(
5434 i::DirectHandle<i::JSReceiver> object,
5435 i::IsolateForSandbox i_isolate_for_sandbox, int index) {
5436 const char* location =
5437 "v8::Object::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderDataInCreationContext()";
5438 auto maybe_context = object->GetCreationContext();
5439 if (!maybe_context.has_value()) return nullptr;
5440
5441 // The code below mostly mimics Context::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData()
5442 // but it doesn't try to expand the EmbedderDataArray instance.
5443 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5444 i::Tagged<i::NativeContext> native_context = maybe_context.value();
5445
5446 // This macro requires a real Isolate while |i_isolate_for_sandbox| might be
5447 // nullptr if the V8 sandbox is not enabled.
5448 DCHECK_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(native_context->GetIsolate());
5449
5450 // TODO(ishell): remove cast once embedder_data slot has a proper type.
5451 i::Tagged<i::EmbedderDataArray> data =
5452 i::Cast<i::EmbedderDataArray>(native_context->embedder_data());
5453 if (V8_LIKELY(static_cast<unsigned>(index) <
5454 static_cast<unsigned>(data->length()))) {
5455 void* result;
5456 Utils::ApiCheck(i::EmbedderDataSlot(data, index)
5457 .ToAlignedPointer(i_isolate_for_sandbox, &result),
5458 location, "Pointer is not aligned");
5459 return result;
5460 }
5461 // Bad index, report an API error.
5462 Utils::ApiCheck(index >= 0, location, "Negative index");
5463 Utils::ApiCheck(index < i::EmbedderDataArray::kMaxLength, location,
5464 "Index too large");
5465 return nullptr;
5466}
5467} // namespace

5524MaybeLocal<Value> Object::CallAsFunction(Local<Context> context,
5525 Local<Value> recv, int argc,
5526 Local<Value> argv[]) {
5527 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
5528 TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.Execute");
5529 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Object, CallAsFunction, InternalEscapableScope);
5530 i::TimerEventScope<i::TimerEventExecute> timer_scope(i_isolate);
5531 i::NestedTimedHistogramScope execute_timer(i_isolate->counters()->execute(),
5532 i_isolate);
5533 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5534 auto recv_obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*recv);
5535 auto args = PrepareArguments(argc, argv);
5536 Local<Value> result;
5537 has_exception = !ToLocal<Value>(
5538 i::Execution::Call(i_isolate, self, recv_obj, args), &result);
5539 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Value);
5540 RETURN_ESCAPED(result);
5541}

5579
5580MaybeLocal<Object> Function::NewInstanceWithSideEffectType(
5581 Local<Context> context, int argc, v8::Local<v8::Value> argv[],
5582 SideEffectType side_effect_type) const {
5583 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
5584 TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.Execute");
5585 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Function, NewInstance, InternalEscapableScope);
5586 i::TimerEventScope<i::TimerEventExecute> timer_scope(i_isolate);
5587 i::NestedTimedHistogramScope execute_timer(i_isolate->counters()->execute(),
5588 i_isolate);
5589 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5590 bool should_set_has_no_side_effect =
5591 side_effect_type == SideEffectType::kHasNoSideEffect &&
5592 i_isolate->should_check_side_effects();
5593 if (should_set_has_no_side_effect) {
5594 CHECK(IsJSFunction(*self) &&
5595 i::Cast<i::JSFunction>(*self)->shared()->IsApiFunction());
5596 i::Tagged<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> func_data =
5597 i::Cast<i::JSFunction>(*self)->shared()->api_func_data();
5598 if (func_data->has_callback(i_isolate)) {
5599 if (func_data->has_side_effects()) {
5600 i_isolate->debug()->IgnoreSideEffectsOnNextCallTo(
5601 handle(func_data, i_isolate));
5602 }
5603 }
5604 }
5605 auto args = PrepareArguments(argc, argv);
5606 Local<Object> result;
5607 has_exception =
5608 !ToLocal<Object>(i::Execution::New(i_isolate, self, self, args), &result);
5609 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Object);
5610 RETURN_ESCAPED(result);
5611}

5620 i::TimerEventScope<i::TimerEventExecute> timer_scope(i_isolate);
5621 i::NestedTimedHistogramScope execute_timer(i_isolate->counters()->execute(),
5622 i_isolate);

5624 Utils::ApiCheck(!self.is_null(), "v8::Function::Call",

5630 i::Execution::Call(i_isolate, self, recv_obj, args), &result);

5633}

5763
5764bool Function::Experimental_IsNopFunction() const {
5765 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5766 if (!IsJSFunction(*self)) return false;
5767 auto sfi = i::Cast<i::JSFunction>(*self)->shared();
5768 i::Isolate* i_isolate = self->GetIsolate();
5769 i::IsCompiledScope is_compiled_scope(sfi->is_compiled_scope(i_isolate));
5770 if (!is_compiled_scope.is_compiled() &&
5771 !i::Compiler::Compile(i_isolate, i::handle(sfi, i_isolate),
5772 i::Compiler::CLEAR_EXCEPTION, &is_compiled_scope)) {
5773 return false;
5774 }
5775 DCHECK(is_compiled_scope.is_compiled());
5776 // Since |sfi| can be GC'ed, we get it again.
5777 sfi = i::Cast<i::JSFunction>(*self)->shared();
5778 if (!sfi->HasBytecodeArray()) return false;
5779 i::Handle<i::BytecodeArray> bytecode_array(sfi->GetBytecodeArray(i_isolate),
5780 i_isolate);
5781 i::interpreter::BytecodeArrayIterator it(bytecode_array, 0);
5782 if (it.current_bytecode() != i::interpreter::Bytecode::kLdaUndefined) {
5783 return false;
5784 }
5785 it.Advance();
5786 DCHECK(!it.done());
5787 if (it.current_bytecode() != i::interpreter::Bytecode::kReturn) return false;
5788 it.Advance();
5789 DCHECK(it.done());
5790 return true;
5791}

5800 &result);
5801 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(String);
5802 RETURN_ESCAPED(Local<String>::Cast(result));
5803}

5812
5813bool String::IsOneByte() const {
5814 return Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this)->IsOneByteRepresentation();
5815}
5816
5817// Helpers for ContainsOnlyOneByteHelper
5818template <size_t size>
5819struct OneByteMask;
5820template <>
5821struct OneByteMask<4> {
5822 static const uint32_t value = 0xFF00FF00;
5823};
5824template <>
5825struct OneByteMask<8> {
5826 static const uint64_t value = 0xFF00'FF00'FF00'FF00;
5827};
5828static const uintptr_t kOneByteMask = OneByteMask<sizeof(uintptr_t)>::value;
5829static const uintptr_t kAlignmentMask = sizeof(uintptr_t) - 1;
5830static inline bool Unaligned(const uint16_t* chars) {
5831 return reinterpret_cast<const uintptr_t>(chars) & kAlignmentMask;
5832}
5833
5834static inline const uint16_t* Align(const uint16_t* chars) {
5835 return reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(chars) &
5836 ~kAlignmentMask);
5837}
5838
5839class ContainsOnlyOneByteHelper {
5840 public:
5841 ContainsOnlyOneByteHelper() : is_one_byte_(true) {}
5842 ContainsOnlyOneByteHelper(const ContainsOnlyOneByteHelper&) = delete;
5843 ContainsOnlyOneByteHelper& operator=(const ContainsOnlyOneByteHelper&) =
5844 delete;
5845 bool Check(i::Tagged<i::String> string) {
5846 i::Tagged<i::ConsString> cons_string =
5847 i::String::VisitFlat(this, string, 0);
5848 if (cons_string.is_null()) return is_one_byte_;
5849 return CheckCons(cons_string);
5850 }
5851 void VisitOneByteString(const uint8_t* chars, int length) {
5852 // Nothing to do.
5853 }
5854 void VisitTwoByteString(const uint16_t* chars, int length) {
5855 // Accumulated bits.
5856 uintptr_t acc = 0;
5857 // Align to uintptr_t.
5858 const uint16_t* end = chars + length;
5859 while (Unaligned(chars) && chars != end) {
5860 acc |= *chars++;
5861 }
5862 // Read word aligned in blocks,
5863 // checking the return value at the end of each block.
5864 const uint16_t* aligned_end = Align(end);
5865 const int increment = sizeof(uintptr_t) / sizeof(uint16_t);
5866 const int inner_loops = 16;
5867 while (chars + inner_loops * increment < aligned_end) {
5868 for (int i = 0; i < inner_loops; i++) {
5869 acc |= *reinterpret_cast<const uintptr_t*>(chars);
5870 chars += increment;
5871 }
5872 // Check for early return.
5873 if ((acc & kOneByteMask) != 0) {
5874 is_one_byte_ = false;
5875 return;
5876 }
5877 }
5878 // Read the rest.
5879 while (chars != end) {
5880 acc |= *chars++;
5881 }
5882 // Check result.
5883 if ((acc & kOneByteMask) != 0) is_one_byte_ = false;
5884 }
5885
5886 private:
5887 bool CheckCons(i::Tagged<i::ConsString> cons_string) {
5888 while (true) {
5889 // Check left side if flat.
5890 i::Tagged<i::String> left = cons_string->first();
5891 i::Tagged<i::ConsString> left_as_cons =
5892 i::String::VisitFlat(this, left, 0);
5893 if (!is_one_byte_) return false;
5894 // Check right side if flat.
5895 i::Tagged<i::String> right = cons_string->second();
5896 i::Tagged<i::ConsString> right_as_cons =
5897 i::String::VisitFlat(this, right, 0);
5898 if (!is_one_byte_) return false;
5899 // Standard recurse/iterate trick.
5900 if (!left_as_cons.is_null() && !right_as_cons.is_null()) {
5901 if (left->length() < right->length()) {
5902 CheckCons(left_as_cons);
5903 cons_string = right_as_cons;
5904 } else {
5905 CheckCons(right_as_cons);
5906 cons_string = left_as_cons;
5907 }
5908 // Check fast return.
5909 if (!is_one_byte_) return false;
5910 continue;
5911 }
5912 // Descend left in place.
5913 if (!left_as_cons.is_null()) {
5914 cons_string = left_as_cons;
5915 continue;
5916 }
5917 // Descend right in place.
5918 if (!right_as_cons.is_null()) {
5919 cons_string = right_as_cons;
5920 continue;
5921 }
5922 // Terminate.
5923 break;
5924 }
5925 return is_one_byte_;
5926 }
5927 bool is_one_byte_;
5928};
5929
5930bool String::ContainsOnlyOneByte() const {
5931 auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5932 if (str->IsOneByteRepresentation()) return true;
5933 ContainsOnlyOneByteHelper helper;
5934 return helper.Check(*str);
5935}
5936
5937int String::Utf8Length(Isolate* v8_isolate) const {
5938 auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5939 str = i::String::Flatten(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate), str);
5940 int length = str->length();
5941 if (length == 0) return 0;
5942 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
5943 i::String::FlatContent flat = str->GetFlatContent(no_gc);
5944 DCHECK(flat.IsFlat());
5945 int utf8_length = 0;
5946 if (flat.IsOneByte()) {
5947 for (uint8_t c : flat.ToOneByteVector()) {
5948 utf8_length += c >> 7;
5949 }
5950 utf8_length += length;
5951 } else {
5952 int last_character = unibrow::Utf16::kNoPreviousCharacter;
5953 for (uint16_t c : flat.ToUC16Vector()) {
5954 utf8_length += unibrow::Utf8::Length(c, last_character);
5955 last_character = c;
5956 }
5957 }
5958 return utf8_length;
5959}
5960
5961size_t String::Utf8LengthV2(Isolate* v8_isolate) const {
5962 auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
5963 return i::String::Utf8Length(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate), str);
5964}
5965
5966namespace {
5967// Writes the flat content of a string to a buffer. This is done in two phases.
5968// The first phase calculates a pessimistic estimate (writable_length) on how
5969// many code units can be safely written without exceeding the buffer capacity
5970// and without leaving at a lone surrogate. The estimated number of code units
5971// is then written out in one go, and the reported byte usage is used to
5972// correct the estimate. This is repeated until the estimate becomes <= 0 or
5973// all code units have been written out. The second phase writes out code
5974// units until the buffer capacity is reached, would be exceeded by the next
5975// unit, or all code units have been written out.
5976template <typename Char>
5977static int WriteUtf8Impl(base::Vector<const Char> string, char* write_start,
5978 int write_capacity, int options,
5979 int* utf16_chars_read_out) {
5980 bool write_null = !(options & v8::String::NO_NULL_TERMINATION);
5981 bool replace_invalid_utf8 = (options & v8::String::REPLACE_INVALID_UTF8);
5982 char* current_write = write_start;
5983 const Char* read_start = string.begin();
5984 int read_index = 0;
5985 int read_length = string.length();
5986 int prev_char = unibrow::Utf16::kNoPreviousCharacter;
5987 // Do a fast loop where there is no exit capacity check.
5988 // Need enough space to write everything but one character.
5989 static_assert(unibrow::Utf16::kMaxExtraUtf8BytesForOneUtf16CodeUnit == 3);
5990 static const int kMaxSizePerChar = sizeof(Char) == 1 ? 2 : 3;
5991 while (read_index < read_length) {
5992 int up_to = read_length;
5993 if (write_capacity != -1) {
5994 int remaining_capacity =
5995 write_capacity - static_cast<int>(current_write - write_start);
5996 int writable_length =
5997 (remaining_capacity - kMaxSizePerChar) / kMaxSizePerChar;
5998 // Need to drop into slow loop.
5999 if (writable_length <= 0) break;
6000 up_to = std::min(up_to, read_index + writable_length);
6001 }
6002 // Write the characters to the stream.
6003 if (sizeof(Char) == 1) {
6004 // Simply memcpy if we only have ASCII characters.
6005 uint8_t char_mask = 0;
6006 for (int i = read_index; i < up_to; i++) char_mask |= read_start[i];
6007 if ((char_mask & 0x80) == 0) {
6008 int copy_length = up_to - read_index;
6009 memcpy(current_write, read_start + read_index, copy_length);
6010 current_write += copy_length;
6011 read_index = up_to;
6012 } else {
6013 for (; read_index < up_to; read_index++) {
6014 current_write += unibrow::Utf8::EncodeOneByte(
6015 current_write, static_cast<uint8_t>(read_start[read_index]));
6016 DCHECK(write_capacity == -1 ||
6017 (current_write - write_start) <= write_capacity);
6018 }
6019 }
6020 } else {
6021 for (; read_index < up_to; read_index++) {
6022 uint16_t character = read_start[read_index];
6023 current_write += unibrow::Utf8::Encode(current_write, character,
6024 prev_char, replace_invalid_utf8);
6025 prev_char = character;
6026 DCHECK(write_capacity == -1 ||
6027 (current_write - write_start) <= write_capacity);
6028 }
6029 }
6030 }
6031 if (read_index < read_length) {
6032 DCHECK_NE(-1, write_capacity);
6033 // Aborted due to limited capacity. Check capacity on each iteration.
6034 int remaining_capacity =
6035 write_capacity - static_cast<int>(current_write - write_start);
6036 DCHECK_GE(remaining_capacity, 0);
6037 for (; read_index < read_length && remaining_capacity > 0; read_index++) {
6038 uint32_t character = read_start[read_index];
6039 int written = 0;
6040 // We can't use a local buffer here because Encode needs to modify
6041 // previous characters in the stream. We know, however, that
6042 // exactly one character will be advanced.
6043 if (unibrow::Utf16::IsSurrogatePair(prev_char, character)) {
6044 written = unibrow::Utf8::Encode(current_write, character, prev_char,
6045 replace_invalid_utf8);
6046 DCHECK_EQ(written, 1);
6047 } else {
6048 // Use a scratch buffer to check the required characters.
6049 char temp_buffer[unibrow::Utf8::kMaxEncodedSize];
6050 // Encoding a surrogate pair to Utf8 always takes 4 bytes.
6051 static const int kSurrogatePairEncodedSize =
6052 static_cast<int>(unibrow::Utf8::kMaxEncodedSize);
6053 // For REPLACE_INVALID_UTF8, catch the case where we cut off in the
6054 // middle of a surrogate pair. Abort before encoding the pair instead.
6055 if (replace_invalid_utf8 &&
6056 remaining_capacity < kSurrogatePairEncodedSize &&
6057 unibrow::Utf16::IsLeadSurrogate(character) &&
6058 read_index + 1 < read_length &&
6059 unibrow::Utf16::IsTrailSurrogate(read_start[read_index + 1])) {
6060 write_null = false;
6061 break;
6062 }
6063 // Can't encode using prev_char as gcc has array bounds issues.
6064 written = unibrow::Utf8::Encode(temp_buffer, character,
6065 unibrow::Utf16::kNoPreviousCharacter,
6066 replace_invalid_utf8);
6067 if (written > remaining_capacity) {
6068 // Won't fit. Abort and do not null-terminate the result.
6069 write_null = false;
6070 break;
6071 }
6072 // Copy over the character from temp_buffer.
6073 for (int i = 0; i < written; i++) current_write[i] = temp_buffer[i];
6074 }
6075
6076 current_write += written;
6077 remaining_capacity -= written;
6078 prev_char = character;
6079 }
6080 }
6081
6082 // Write out number of utf16 characters written to the stream.
6083 if (utf16_chars_read_out != nullptr) *utf16_chars_read_out = read_index;
6084
6085 // Only null-terminate if there's space.
6086 if (write_null && (write_capacity == -1 ||
6087 (current_write - write_start) < write_capacity)) {
6088 *current_write++ = '\0';
6089 }
6090 return static_cast<int>(current_write - write_start);
6091}
6092} // anonymous namespace
6093
6094int String::WriteUtf8(Isolate* v8_isolate, char* buffer, int capacity,
6095 int* nchars_ref, int options) const {
6096 auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6097 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
6098 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, String, WriteUtf8);
6099 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
6100 str = i::String::Flatten(i_isolate, str);
6101 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6102 i::String::FlatContent content = str->GetFlatContent(no_gc);
6103 if (content.IsOneByte()) {
6104 return WriteUtf8Impl<uint8_t>(content.ToOneByteVector(), buffer, capacity,
6105 options, nchars_ref);
6106 } else {
6107 return WriteUtf8Impl<uint16_t>(content.ToUC16Vector(), buffer, capacity,
6108 options, nchars_ref);
6109 }
6110}
6111
6112template <typename CharType>
6113static inline int WriteHelper(i::Isolate* i_isolate, const String* string,
6114 CharType* buffer, int start, int length,
6115 int options) {
6116 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, String, Write);
6117 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
6118 DCHECK(start >= 0 && length >= -1);
6119 auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(string);
6120 int end = start + length;
6121 if ((length == -1) || (static_cast<uint32_t>(length) > str->length() - start))
6122 end = str->length();
6123 if (end < 0) return 0;
6124 int write_length = end - start;
6125 if (start < end) i::String::WriteToFlat(*str, buffer, start, write_length);
6126 if (!(options & String::NO_NULL_TERMINATION) &&
6127 (length == -1 || write_length < length)) {
6128 buffer[write_length] = '\0';
6129 }
6130 return write_length;
6131}
6132
6133int String::WriteOneByte(Isolate* v8_isolate, uint8_t* buffer, int start,
6134 int length, int options) const {
6135 return WriteHelper(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate), this, buffer,
6136 start, length, options);
6137}
6138
6139int String::Write(Isolate* v8_isolate, uint16_t* buffer, int start, int length,
6140 int options) const {
6141 return WriteHelper(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate), this, buffer,
6142 start, length, options);
6143}
6144
6145template <typename CharType>
6146static inline void WriteHelperV2(i::Isolate* i_isolate, const String* string,
6147 CharType* buffer, uint32_t offset,
6148 uint32_t length, int flags) {
6149 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, String, Write);
6150 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
6151
6152 DCHECK_LE(length, string->Length());
6153 DCHECK_LE(offset, string->Length() - length);
6154
6155 auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(string);
6156 i::String::WriteToFlat(*str, buffer, offset, length);
6157 if (flags & String::WriteFlags::kNullTerminate) {
6158 buffer[length] = '\0';
6159 }
6160}
6161
6162void String::WriteV2(Isolate* v8_isolate, uint32_t offset, uint32_t length,
6163 uint16_t* buffer, int flags) const {
6164 WriteHelperV2(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate), this, buffer, offset,
6165 length, flags);
6166}
6167
6168void String::WriteOneByteV2(Isolate* v8_isolate, uint32_t offset,
6169 uint32_t length, uint8_t* buffer, int flags) const {
6170 DCHECK(IsOneByte());
6171 WriteHelperV2(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate), this, buffer, offset,
6172 length, flags);
6173}
6174
6175size_t String::WriteUtf8V2(Isolate* v8_isolate, char* buffer, size_t capacity,
6176 int flags) const {
6177 auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6178 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
6179 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, String, WriteUtf8);
6180 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
6181 i::String::Utf8EncodingFlags i_flags;
6182 if (flags & String::WriteFlags::kNullTerminate) {
6183 i_flags |= i::String::Utf8EncodingFlag::kNullTerminate;
6184 }
6185 if (flags & String::WriteFlags::kReplaceInvalidUtf8) {
6186 i_flags |= i::String::Utf8EncodingFlag::kReplaceInvalid;
6187 }
6188 return i::String::WriteUtf8(i_isolate, str, buffer, capacity, i_flags);
6189}

6191namespace {
6192
6193bool HasExternalStringResource(i::Tagged<i::String> string) {
6194 return i::StringShape(string).IsExternal() ||
6195 string->HasExternalForwardingIndex(kAcquireLoad);
6196}
6197
6198v8::String::ExternalStringResourceBase* GetExternalResourceFromForwardingTable(
6199 i::Tagged<i::String> string, uint32_t raw_hash, bool* is_one_byte) {
6200 DCHECK(i::String::IsExternalForwardingIndex(raw_hash));
6201 const int index = i::String::ForwardingIndexValueBits::decode(raw_hash);
6202 // Note that with a shared heap the main and worker isolates all share the
6203 // same forwarding table.
6204 auto resource =
6205 i::Isolate::Current()->string_forwarding_table()->GetExternalResource(
6206 index, is_one_byte);
6207 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(resource);
6208 return resource;
6209}
6210
6211} // namespace
6212
6213bool v8::String::IsExternal() const {
6214 return HasExternalStringResource(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this));
6215}
6216
6217bool v8::String::IsExternalTwoByte() const {
6218 auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6219 if (i::StringShape(*str).IsExternalTwoByte()) return true;
6220 uint32_t raw_hash_field = str->raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad);
6221 if (i::String::IsExternalForwardingIndex(raw_hash_field)) {
6222 bool is_one_byte;
6223 GetExternalResourceFromForwardingTable(*str, raw_hash_field, &is_one_byte);
6224 return !is_one_byte;
6225 }
6226 return false;
6227}
6228
6229bool v8::String::IsExternalOneByte() const {
6230 auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6231 if (i::StringShape(*str).IsExternalOneByte()) return true;
6232 uint32_t raw_hash_field = str->raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad);
6233 if (i::String::IsExternalForwardingIndex(raw_hash_field)) {
6234 bool is_one_byte;
6235 GetExternalResourceFromForwardingTable(*str, raw_hash_field, &is_one_byte);
6236 return is_one_byte;
6237 }
6238 return false;
6239}
6240
6241Local<v8::String> v8::String::InternalizeString(Isolate* v8_isolate) {
6242 auto* isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
6243 auto str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6244 return Utils::ToLocal(isolate->factory()->InternalizeString(str));
6245}
6246
6247void v8::String::VerifyExternalStringResource(
6248 v8::String::ExternalStringResource* value) const {
6249 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6250 i::Tagged<i::String> str = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6251 const v8::String::ExternalStringResource* expected;
6252
6253 if (i::IsThinString(str)) {
6254 str = i::Cast<i::ThinString>(str)->actual();
6255 }
6256
6257 if (i::StringShape(str).IsExternalTwoByte()) {
6258 const void* resource = i::Cast<i::ExternalTwoByteString>(str)->resource();
6259 expected = reinterpret_cast<const ExternalStringResource*>(resource);
6260 } else {
6261 uint32_t raw_hash_field = str->raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad);
6262 if (i::String::IsExternalForwardingIndex(raw_hash_field)) {
6263 bool is_one_byte;
6264 auto resource = GetExternalResourceFromForwardingTable(
6265 str, raw_hash_field, &is_one_byte);
6266 if (!is_one_byte) {
6267 expected = reinterpret_cast<const ExternalStringResource*>(resource);
6268 }
6269 } else {
6270 expected = nullptr;
6271 }
6272 }
6273 CHECK_EQ(expected, value);
6274}
6275
6276void v8::String::VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(
6277 v8::String::ExternalStringResourceBase* value, Encoding encoding) const {
6278 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6279 i::Tagged<i::String> str = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6280 const v8::String::ExternalStringResourceBase* expected;
6281 Encoding expectedEncoding;
6282
6283 if (i::IsThinString(str)) {
6284 str = i::Cast<i::ThinString>(str)->actual();
6285 }
6286
6287 if (i::StringShape(str).IsExternalOneByte()) {
6288 const void* resource = i::Cast<i::ExternalOneByteString>(str)->resource();
6289 expected = reinterpret_cast<const ExternalStringResourceBase*>(resource);
6290 expectedEncoding = ONE_BYTE_ENCODING;
6291 } else if (i::StringShape(str).IsExternalTwoByte()) {
6292 const void* resource = i::Cast<i::ExternalTwoByteString>(str)->resource();
6293 expected = reinterpret_cast<const ExternalStringResourceBase*>(resource);
6294 expectedEncoding = TWO_BYTE_ENCODING;
6295 } else {
6296 uint32_t raw_hash_field = str->raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad);
6297 if (i::String::IsExternalForwardingIndex(raw_hash_field)) {
6298 bool is_one_byte;
6299 expected = GetExternalResourceFromForwardingTable(str, raw_hash_field,
6300 &is_one_byte);
6301 expectedEncoding = is_one_byte ? ONE_BYTE_ENCODING : TWO_BYTE_ENCODING;
6302 } else {
6303 expected = nullptr;
6304 expectedEncoding = str->IsOneByteRepresentation() ? ONE_BYTE_ENCODING
6305 : TWO_BYTE_ENCODING;
6306 }
6307 }
6308 CHECK_EQ(expected, value);
6309 CHECK_EQ(expectedEncoding, encoding);
6310}
6311
6312String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResourceSlow() const {
6313 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6314 i::Tagged<i::String> str = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6315
6316 if (i::IsThinString(str)) {
6317 str = i::Cast<i::ThinString>(str)->actual();
6318 }
6319
6320 if (i::StringShape(str).IsExternalTwoByte()) {
6321 Isolate* isolate = i::Internals::GetIsolateForSandbox(str.ptr());
6322 i::Address value =
6323 i::Internals::ReadExternalPointerField<i::kExternalStringResourceTag>(
6324 isolate, str.ptr(), i::Internals::kStringResourceOffset);
6325 return reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
6326 } else {
6327 uint32_t raw_hash_field = str->raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad);
6328 if (i::String::IsExternalForwardingIndex(raw_hash_field)) {
6329 bool is_one_byte;
6330 auto resource = GetExternalResourceFromForwardingTable(
6331 str, raw_hash_field, &is_one_byte);
6332 if (!is_one_byte) {
6333 return reinterpret_cast<ExternalStringResource*>(resource);
6334 }
6335 }
6336 }
6337 return nullptr;
6338}

6357
6358String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBaseSlow(
6359 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
6360 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6361 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = nullptr;
6362 i::Tagged<i::String> str = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6363
6364 if (i::IsThinString(str)) {
6365 str = i::Cast<i::ThinString>(str)->actual();
6366 }
6367
6368 internal::Address string = str.ptr();
6369 int type = i::Internals::GetInstanceType(string) &
6370 i::Internals::kStringRepresentationAndEncodingMask;
6371 *encoding_out =
6372 static_cast<Encoding>(type & i::Internals::kStringEncodingMask);
6373 if (i::StringShape(str).IsExternalOneByte() ||
6374 i::StringShape(str).IsExternalTwoByte()) {
6375 Isolate* isolate = i::Internals::GetIsolateForSandbox(string);
6376 i::Address value =
6377 i::Internals::ReadExternalPointerField<i::kExternalStringResourceTag>(
6378 isolate, string, i::Internals::kStringResourceOffset);
6379 resource = reinterpret_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
6380 } else {
6381 uint32_t raw_hash_field = str->raw_hash_field();
6382 if (i::String::IsExternalForwardingIndex(raw_hash_field)) {
6383 bool is_one_byte;
6384 resource = GetExternalResourceFromForwardingTable(str, raw_hash_field,
6385 &is_one_byte);
6386 *encoding_out = is_one_byte ? Encoding::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING
6387 : Encoding::TWO_BYTE_ENCODING;
6388 }
6389 }
6390 return resource;
6391}
6392
6393const v8::String::ExternalOneByteStringResource*
6394v8::String::GetExternalOneByteStringResource() const {
6395 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6396 i::Tagged<i::String> str = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6397 if (i::StringShape(str).IsExternalOneByte()) {
6398 return i::Cast<i::ExternalOneByteString>(str)->resource();
6399 } else if (i::IsThinString(str)) {
6400 str = i::Cast<i::ThinString>(str)->actual();
6401 if (i::StringShape(str).IsExternalOneByte()) {
6402 return i::Cast<i::ExternalOneByteString>(str)->resource();
6403 }
6404 }
6405 uint32_t raw_hash_field = str->raw_hash_field(kAcquireLoad);
6406 if (i::String::IsExternalForwardingIndex(raw_hash_field)) {
6407 bool is_one_byte;
6408 auto resource = GetExternalResourceFromForwardingTable(str, raw_hash_field,
6409 &is_one_byte);
6410 if (is_one_byte) {
6411 return reinterpret_cast<ExternalOneByteStringResource*>(resource);
6412 }
6413 }
6414 return nullptr;
6415}

6467int v8::Object::InternalFieldCount() const {
6468 auto self = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6469 if (!IsJSObject(self)) return 0;
6470 return i::Cast<i::JSObject>(self)->GetEmbedderFieldCount();
6471}
6472
6473static V8_INLINE bool InternalFieldOK(i::DirectHandle<i::JSReceiver> obj,
6474 int index, const char* location) {
6475 return Utils::ApiCheck(
6476 IsJSObject(*obj) &&
6477 (index < i::Cast<i::JSObject>(*obj)->GetEmbedderFieldCount()),
6478 location, "Internal field out of bounds");
6479}
6480
6481Local<Data> v8::Object::SlowGetInternalField(int index) {
6482 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6483 const char* location = "v8::Object::GetInternalField()";
6484 if (!InternalFieldOK(obj, index, location)) return Local<Value>();
6485 i::Isolate* isolate = obj->GetIsolate();
6486 return ToApiHandle<Data>(i::direct_handle(
6487 i::Cast<i::JSObject>(*obj)->GetEmbedderField(index), isolate));
6488}
6489
6490void v8::Object::SetInternalField(int index, v8::Local<Data> value) {
6491 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6492 const char* location = "v8::Object::SetInternalField()";
6493 if (!InternalFieldOK(obj, index, location)) return;
6494 auto val = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
6495 i::Cast<i::JSObject>(obj)->SetEmbedderField(index, *val);
6496}
6497
6498void* v8::Object::SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(v8::Isolate* isolate,
6499 int index) {
6500 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6501 const char* location = "v8::Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField()";
6502 if (!InternalFieldOK(obj, index, location)) return nullptr;
6503 void* result;
6504 Utils::ApiCheck(
6505 i::EmbedderDataSlot(i::Cast<i::JSObject>(*obj), index)
6506 .ToAlignedPointer(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate), &result),
6507 location, "Unaligned pointer");
6508 return result;
6509}
