6511void* v8::Object::SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
6512 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6513 const char* location = "v8::Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField()";
6514 if (!InternalFieldOK(obj, index, location)) return nullptr;
6515 void* result;
6516 Utils::ApiCheck(i::EmbedderDataSlot(i::Cast<i::JSObject>(*obj), index)
6517 .ToAlignedPointer(obj->GetIsolate(), &result),
6518 location, "Unaligned pointer");
6519 return result;
6520}
6521
6522void v8::Object::SetAlignedPointerInInternalField(int index, void* value) {
6523 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6524 const char* location = "v8::Object::SetAlignedPointerInInternalField()";
6525 if (!InternalFieldOK(obj, index, location)) return;
6526
6527 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6528 Utils::ApiCheck(i::EmbedderDataSlot(i::Cast<i::JSObject>(*obj), index)
6529 .store_aligned_pointer(obj->GetIsolate(), *obj, value),
6530 location, "Unaligned pointer");
6531 DCHECK_EQ(value, GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index));
6532}
6533
6534void v8::Object::SetAlignedPointerInInternalFields(int argc, int indices[],
6535 void* values[]) {
6536 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
6537 if (!IsJSObject(*obj)) return;
6538 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
6539 const char* location = "v8::Object::SetAlignedPointerInInternalFields()";
6540 auto js_obj = i::Cast<i::JSObject>(*obj);
6541 int nof_embedder_fields = js_obj->GetEmbedderFieldCount();
6542 for (int i = 0; i < argc; i++) {
6543 int index = indices[i];
6544 if (!Utils::ApiCheck(index < nof_embedder_fields, location,
6545 "Internal field out of bounds")) {
6546 return;
6547 }
6548 void* value = values[i];
6549 Utils::ApiCheck(i::EmbedderDataSlot(js_obj, index)
6550 .store_aligned_pointer(obj->GetIsolate(), *obj, value),
6551 location, "Unaligned pointer");
6552 DCHECK_EQ(value, GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index));
6553 }
6554}

6558 CppHeapPointerTagRange tag_range) {
6559 DCHECK_LE(tag_range.lower_bound, tag_range.upper_bound);
6560 return i::JSApiWrapper(
6561 i::Cast<i::JSObject>(i::Tagged<i::Object>(wrapper_obj)))
6562 .GetCppHeapWrappable(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate), tag_range);
6563}
6564
6565// static
6566void v8::Object::Wrap(v8::Isolate* isolate, i::Address wrapper_obj,
6567 CppHeapPointerTag tag, void* wrappable) {
6568 return i::JSApiWrapper(
6569 i::Cast<i::JSObject>(i::Tagged<i::Object>(wrapper_obj)))
6570 .SetCppHeapWrappable(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate), wrappable,
6571 tag);
6572}

6576void v8::V8::InitializePlatform(Platform* platform) {
6577 i::V8::InitializePlatform(platform);
6578}
6579
6580void v8::V8::DisposePlatform() { i::V8::DisposePlatform(); }
6581
6582bool v8::V8::Initialize(const int build_config) {
6583 const bool kEmbedderPointerCompression =
6584 (build_config & kPointerCompression) != 0;
6585 if (kEmbedderPointerCompression != COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
6586 FATAL(
6587 "Embedder-vs-V8 build configuration mismatch. On embedder side "
6588 "pointer compression is %s while on V8 side it's %s.",
6589 kEmbedderPointerCompression ? "ENABLED" : "DISABLED",
6590 COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL ? "ENABLED" : "DISABLED");
6591 }
6592
6593 const int kEmbedderSmiValueSize = (build_config & k31BitSmis) ? 31 : 32;
6594 if (kEmbedderSmiValueSize != internal::kSmiValueSize) {
6595 FATAL(
6596 "Embedder-vs-V8 build configuration mismatch. On embedder side "
6597 "Smi value size is %d while on V8 side it's %d.",
6598 kEmbedderSmiValueSize, internal::kSmiValueSize);
6599 }
6600
6601 const bool kEmbedderSandbox = (build_config & kSandbox) != 0;
6602 if (kEmbedderSandbox != V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL) {
6603 FATAL(
6604 "Embedder-vs-V8 build configuration mismatch. On embedder side "
6605 "sandbox is %s while on V8 side it's %s.",
6606 kEmbedderSandbox ? "ENABLED" : "DISABLED",
6607 V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL ? "ENABLED" : "DISABLED");
6608 }
6609
6610 const bool kEmbedderTargetOsIsAndroid =
6611 (build_config & kTargetOsIsAndroid) != 0;
6612#ifdef V8_TARGET_OS_ANDROID
6613 const bool kV8TargetOsIsAndroid = true;
6614#else
6615 const bool kV8TargetOsIsAndroid = false;
6616#endif
6617 if (kEmbedderTargetOsIsAndroid != kV8TargetOsIsAndroid) {
6618 FATAL(
6619 "Embedder-vs-V8 build configuration mismatch. On embedder side "
6620 "target OS is %s while on V8 side it's %s.",
6621 kEmbedderTargetOsIsAndroid ? "Android" : "not Android",
6622 kV8TargetOsIsAndroid ? "Android" : "not Android");
6623 }
6624
6625 const bool kEmbedderEnableChecks = (build_config & kEnableChecks) != 0;
6626#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
6627 const bool kV8EnableChecks = true;
6628#else
6629 const bool kV8EnableChecks = false;
6630#endif
6631 if (kEmbedderEnableChecks != kV8EnableChecks) {
6632 FATAL(
6633 "Embedder-vs-V8 build configuration mismatch. On embedder side "
6634 "V8_ENABLE_CHECKS is %s while on V8 side it's %s.",
6635 kEmbedderEnableChecks ? "ENABLED" : "DISABLED",
6636 kV8EnableChecks ? "ENABLED" : "DISABLED");
6637 }
6638
6639 i::V8::Initialize();
6640 return true;
6641}

6797
6798template <typename ObjectType>
6799struct InvokeBootstrapper;
6800
6801template <>
6802struct InvokeBootstrapper<i::NativeContext> {
6803 i::DirectHandle<i::NativeContext> Invoke(
6804 i::Isolate* i_isolate,
6805 i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::JSGlobalProxy> maybe_global_proxy,
6806 v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template,
6807 v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions, size_t context_snapshot_index,
6808 i::DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback embedder_fields_deserializer,
6809 v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue) {
6810 return i_isolate->bootstrapper()->CreateEnvironment(
6811 maybe_global_proxy, global_proxy_template, extensions,
6812 context_snapshot_index, embedder_fields_deserializer, microtask_queue);
6813 }
6814};
6815
6816template <>
6817struct InvokeBootstrapper<i::JSGlobalProxy> {
6818 i::DirectHandle<i::JSGlobalProxy> Invoke(
6819 i::Isolate* i_isolate,
6820 i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::JSGlobalProxy> maybe_global_proxy,
6821 v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_proxy_template,
6822 v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions, size_t context_snapshot_index,
6823 i::DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback embedder_fields_deserializer,
6824 v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue) {
6825 USE(extensions);
6826 USE(context_snapshot_index);
6827 return i_isolate->bootstrapper()->NewRemoteContext(maybe_global_proxy,
6828 global_proxy_template);
6829 }
6830};
6831
6832template <typename ObjectType>
6833static i::DirectHandle<ObjectType> CreateEnvironment(
6834 i::Isolate* i_isolate, v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions,
6835 v8::MaybeLocal<ObjectTemplate> maybe_global_template,
6836 v8::MaybeLocal<Value> maybe_global_proxy, size_t context_snapshot_index,
6837 i::DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback embedder_fields_deserializer,
6838 v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue) {
6839 i::DirectHandle<ObjectType> result;
6840
6841 {
6842 ENTER_V8_FOR_NEW_CONTEXT(i_isolate);
6843 v8::Local<ObjectTemplate> proxy_template;
6844 i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> proxy_constructor;
6845 i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> global_constructor;
6846 i::DirectHandle<i::UnionOf<i::Undefined, i::InterceptorInfo>>
6847 named_interceptor(i_isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
6848 i::DirectHandle<i::UnionOf<i::Undefined, i::InterceptorInfo>>
6849 indexed_interceptor(i_isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
6850
6851 if (!maybe_global_template.IsEmpty()) {
6852 v8::Local<v8::ObjectTemplate> global_template =
6853 maybe_global_template.ToLocalChecked();
6854 // Make sure that the global_template has a constructor.
6855 global_constructor = EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, *global_template);
6856
6857 // Create a fresh template for the global proxy object.
6858 proxy_template =
6859 ObjectTemplate::New(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
6860 proxy_constructor = EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, *proxy_template);
6861
6862 // Set the global template to be the prototype template of
6863 // global proxy template.
6864 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetPrototypeTemplate(
6865 i_isolate, proxy_constructor,
6866 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*global_template));
6867
6868 proxy_template->SetInternalFieldCount(
6869 global_template->InternalFieldCount());
6870
6871 // Migrate security handlers from global_template to
6872 // proxy_template. Temporarily removing access check
6873 // information from the global template.
6874 if (!IsUndefined(global_constructor->GetAccessCheckInfo(), i_isolate)) {
6875 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetAccessCheckInfo(
6876 i_isolate, proxy_constructor,
6877 direct_handle(global_constructor->GetAccessCheckInfo(), i_isolate));
6878 proxy_constructor->set_needs_access_check(
6879 global_constructor->needs_access_check());
6880 global_constructor->set_needs_access_check(false);
6881 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetAccessCheckInfo(
6882 i_isolate, global_constructor,
6883 i_isolate->factory()->undefined_value());
6884 }
6885
6886 // Same for other interceptors. If the global constructor has
6887 // interceptors, we need to replace them temporarily with noop
6888 // interceptors, so the map is correctly marked as having interceptors,
6889 // but we don't invoke any.
6890 if (!IsUndefined(global_constructor->GetNamedPropertyHandler(),
6891 i_isolate)) {
6892 named_interceptor = direct_handle(
6893 global_constructor->GetNamedPropertyHandler(), i_isolate);
6894 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetNamedPropertyHandler(
6895 i_isolate, global_constructor,
6896 i_isolate->factory()->noop_interceptor_info());
6897 }
6898 if (!IsUndefined(global_constructor->GetIndexedPropertyHandler(),
6899 i_isolate)) {
6900 indexed_interceptor = direct_handle(
6901 global_constructor->GetIndexedPropertyHandler(), i_isolate);
6902 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetIndexedPropertyHandler(
6903 i_isolate, global_constructor,
6904 i_isolate->factory()->noop_interceptor_info());
6905 }
6906 }
6907
6908 i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::JSGlobalProxy> maybe_proxy;
6909 if (!maybe_global_proxy.IsEmpty()) {
6910 maybe_proxy = i::Cast<i::JSGlobalProxy>(
6911 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*maybe_global_proxy.ToLocalChecked()));
6912 }
6913 // Create the environment.
6914 InvokeBootstrapper<ObjectType> invoke;
6915 result = invoke.Invoke(i_isolate, maybe_proxy, proxy_template, extensions,
6916 context_snapshot_index, embedder_fields_deserializer,
6917 microtask_queue);
6918
6919 // Restore the access check info and interceptors on the global template.
6920 if (!maybe_global_template.IsEmpty()) {
6921 DCHECK(!global_constructor.is_null());
6922 DCHECK(!proxy_constructor.is_null());
6923 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetAccessCheckInfo(
6924 i_isolate, global_constructor,
6925 i::direct_handle(proxy_constructor->GetAccessCheckInfo(), i_isolate));
6926 global_constructor->set_needs_access_check(
6927 proxy_constructor->needs_access_check());
6928 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetNamedPropertyHandler(
6929 i_isolate, global_constructor, named_interceptor);
6930 i::FunctionTemplateInfo::SetIndexedPropertyHandler(
6931 i_isolate, global_constructor, indexed_interceptor);
6932 }
6933 }
6934 // Leave V8.
6935
6936 return result;
6937}
6938
6939Local<Context> NewContext(
6940 v8::Isolate* external_isolate, v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions,
6941 v8::MaybeLocal<ObjectTemplate> global_template,
6942 v8::MaybeLocal<Value> global_object, size_t context_snapshot_index,
6943 i::DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback embedder_fields_deserializer,
6944 v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue) {
6945 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(external_isolate);
6946 // TODO(jkummerow): This is for crbug.com/713699. Remove it if it doesn't
6947 // fail.
6948 // Sanity-check that the isolate is initialized and usable.
6949 CHECK(IsCode(i_isolate->builtins()->code(i::Builtin::kIllegal)));
6950
6951 TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.NewContext");
6952 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, Context, New);
6953 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
6954 ExtensionConfiguration no_extensions;
6955 if (extensions == nullptr) extensions = &no_extensions;
6956 i::DirectHandle<i::NativeContext> env = CreateEnvironment<i::NativeContext>(
6957 i_isolate, extensions, global_template, global_object,
6958 context_snapshot_index, embedder_fields_deserializer, microtask_queue);
6959 if (env.is_null()) return Local<Context>();
6960 return Utils::ToLocal(scope.CloseAndEscape(env));
6961}
6962
6963Local<Context> v8::Context::New(
6964 v8::Isolate* external_isolate, v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions,
6965 v8::MaybeLocal<ObjectTemplate> global_template,
6966 v8::MaybeLocal<Value> global_object,
6967 v8::DeserializeInternalFieldsCallback internal_fields_deserializer,
6968 v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue,
6969 v8::DeserializeContextDataCallback context_callback_deserializer,
6970 v8::DeserializeAPIWrapperCallback api_wrapper_deserializer) {
6971 return NewContext(
6972 external_isolate, extensions, global_template, global_object, 0,
6973 i::DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback(internal_fields_deserializer,
6974 context_callback_deserializer,
6975 api_wrapper_deserializer),
6976 microtask_queue);
6977}
6978
6979MaybeLocal<Context> v8::Context::FromSnapshot(
6980 v8::Isolate* external_isolate, size_t context_snapshot_index,
6981 v8::DeserializeInternalFieldsCallback internal_fields_deserializer,
6982 v8::ExtensionConfiguration* extensions, MaybeLocal<Value> global_object,
6983 v8::MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue,
6984 v8::DeserializeContextDataCallback context_callback_deserializer,
6985 v8::DeserializeAPIWrapperCallback api_wrapper_deserializer) {
6986 size_t index_including_default_context = context_snapshot_index + 1;
6987 if (!i::Snapshot::HasContextSnapshot(
6988 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(external_isolate),
6989 index_including_default_context)) {
6990 return MaybeLocal<Context>();
6991 }
6992 return NewContext(
6993 external_isolate, extensions, MaybeLocal<ObjectTemplate>(), global_object,
6994 index_including_default_context,
6995 i::DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback(internal_fields_deserializer,
6996 context_callback_deserializer,
6997 api_wrapper_deserializer),
6998 microtask_queue);
6999}
7000
7001MaybeLocal<Object> v8::Context::NewRemoteContext(
7002 v8::Isolate* external_isolate, v8::Local<ObjectTemplate> global_template,
7003 v8::MaybeLocal<v8::Value> global_object) {
7004 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(external_isolate);
7005 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, Context, NewRemoteContext);
7006 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
7007 i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> global_constructor =
7008 EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, *global_template);
7009 Utils::ApiCheck(global_constructor->needs_access_check(),
7010 "v8::Context::NewRemoteContext",
7011 "Global template needs to have access checks enabled");
7012 i::DirectHandle<i::AccessCheckInfo> access_check_info(
7013 i::Cast<i::AccessCheckInfo>(global_constructor->GetAccessCheckInfo()),
7014 i_isolate);
7015 Utils::ApiCheck(
7016 access_check_info->named_interceptor() != i::Tagged<i::Object>(),
7017 "v8::Context::NewRemoteContext",
7018 "Global template needs to have access check handlers");
7019 i::DirectHandle<i::JSObject> global_proxy =
7020 CreateEnvironment<i::JSGlobalProxy>(
7021 i_isolate, nullptr, global_template, global_object, 0,
7022 i::DeserializeEmbedderFieldsCallback(), nullptr);
7023 if (global_proxy.is_null()) {
7024 if (i_isolate->has_exception()) i_isolate->clear_exception();
7025 return MaybeLocal<Object>();
7026 }
7027 return Utils::ToLocal(scope.CloseAndEscape(global_proxy));
7028}
7029
7030void v8::Context::SetSecurityToken(Local<Value> token) {
7031 auto env = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7032 auto token_handle = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*token);
7033 env->set_security_token(*token_handle);
7034}
7035
7036void v8::Context::UseDefaultSecurityToken() {
7037 auto env = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7038 env->set_security_token(env->global_object());
7039}
7040
7041Local<Value> v8::Context::GetSecurityToken() {
7042 auto env = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7043 i::Isolate* i_isolate = env->GetIsolate();
7044 i::Tagged<i::Object> security_token = env->security_token();
7045 return Utils::ToLocal(i::direct_handle(security_token, i_isolate));
7046}
7047
7048namespace {
7049
7050bool MayContainObjectsToFreeze(i::InstanceType obj_type) {
7051 if (i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsString(obj_type)) return false;
7052 // SharedFunctionInfo is cross-context so it shouldn't be frozen.
7053 if (i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsSharedFunctionInfo(obj_type)) return false;
7054 return true;
7055}
7056
7057bool RequiresEmbedderSupportToFreeze(i::InstanceType obj_type) {
7058 DCHECK(i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSReceiver(obj_type));
7059
7060 return (i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSApiObject(obj_type) ||
7061 i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSExternalObject(obj_type) ||
7062 i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSAPIObjectWithEmbedderSlots(obj_type));
7063}
7064
7065bool IsJSReceiverSafeToFreeze(i::InstanceType obj_type) {
7066 DCHECK(i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSReceiver(obj_type));
7067
7068 switch (obj_type) {
7069 case i::JS_OBJECT_TYPE:
7070 case i::JS_GLOBAL_OBJECT_TYPE:
7071 case i::JS_GLOBAL_PROXY_TYPE:
7072 case i::JS_PRIMITIVE_WRAPPER_TYPE:
7073 case i::JS_FUNCTION_TYPE:
7074 /* Function types */
7075 case i::BIGINT64_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
7076 case i::BIGUINT64_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
7077 case i::FLOAT16_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
7078 case i::FLOAT32_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
7079 case i::FLOAT64_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
7080 case i::INT16_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
7081 case i::INT32_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
7082 case i::INT8_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
7083 case i::UINT16_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
7084 case i::UINT32_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
7085 case i::UINT8_CLAMPED_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
7086 case i::UINT8_TYPED_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
7087 case i::JS_ARRAY_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
7088 case i::JS_PROMISE_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
7089 case i::JS_REG_EXP_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
7090 case i::JS_CLASS_CONSTRUCTOR_TYPE:
7091 /* Prototype Types */
7092 case i::JS_ARRAY_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
7093 case i::JS_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
7094 case i::JS_MAP_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
7095 case i::JS_OBJECT_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
7096 case i::JS_PROMISE_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
7097 case i::JS_REG_EXP_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
7098 case i::JS_SET_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
7099 case i::JS_SET_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
7100 case i::JS_STRING_ITERATOR_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
7101 case i::JS_TYPED_ARRAY_PROTOTYPE_TYPE:
7102 /* */
7103 case i::JS_ARRAY_TYPE:
7104 return true;
7105#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
7106 case i::WASM_ARRAY_TYPE:
7107 case i::WASM_STRUCT_TYPE:
7108 case i::WASM_TAG_OBJECT_TYPE:
7109#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
7110 case i::JS_PROXY_TYPE:
7111 return true;
7112 // These types are known not to freeze.
7113 case i::JS_MAP_KEY_ITERATOR_TYPE:
7114 case i::JS_MAP_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
7115 case i::JS_MAP_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
7116 case i::JS_SET_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
7117 case i::JS_SET_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE:
7118 case i::JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE:
7119 case i::JS_ASYNC_FUNCTION_OBJECT_TYPE:
7120 case i::JS_ASYNC_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE:
7121 case i::JS_ARRAY_ITERATOR_TYPE: {
7122 return false;
7123 }
7124 default:
7125 // TODO(behamilton): Handle any types that fall through here.
7126 return false;
7127 }
7128}
7129
7130class ObjectVisitorDeepFreezer : i::ObjectVisitor {
7131 public:
7132 explicit ObjectVisitorDeepFreezer(i::Isolate* isolate,
7133 Context::DeepFreezeDelegate* delegate)
7134 : isolate_(isolate),
7135 delegate_(delegate),
7136 objects_to_freeze_(isolate),
7137 lazy_accessor_pairs_to_freeze_(isolate) {}
7138
7139 bool DeepFreeze(i::DirectHandle<i::Context> context) {
7140 bool success = VisitObject(i::Cast<i::HeapObject>(*context));
7141 if (success) {
7142 success = InstantiateAndVisitLazyAccessorPairs();
7143 }
7144 DCHECK_EQ(success, !error_.has_value());
7145 if (!success) {
7146 THROW_NEW_ERROR_RETURN_VALUE(
7147 isolate_, NewTypeError(error_->msg_id, error_->name), false);
7148 }
7149 for (const auto& obj : objects_to_freeze_) {
7150 MAYBE_RETURN_ON_EXCEPTION_VALUE(
7151 isolate_,
7152 i::JSReceiver::SetIntegrityLevel(isolate_, obj, i::FROZEN,
7153 i::kThrowOnError),
7154 false);
7155 }
7156 return true;
7157 }
7158
7159 void VisitPointers(i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> host, i::ObjectSlot start,
7160 i::ObjectSlot end) final {
7161 VisitPointersImpl(start, end);
7162 }
7163 void VisitPointers(i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> host, i::MaybeObjectSlot start,
7164 i::MaybeObjectSlot end) final {
7165 VisitPointersImpl(start, end);
7166 }
7167 void VisitMapPointer(i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> host) final {
7168 VisitPointer(host, host->map_slot());
7169 }
7170 void VisitInstructionStreamPointer(i::Tagged<i::Code> host,
7171 i::InstructionStreamSlot slot) final {}
7172 void VisitCustomWeakPointers(i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> host,
7173 i::ObjectSlot start, i::ObjectSlot end) final {}
7174
7175 private:
7176 struct ErrorInfo {
7177 i::MessageTemplate msg_id;
7178 i::DirectHandle<i::String> name;
7179 };
7180
7181 template <typename TSlot>
7182 void VisitPointersImpl(TSlot start, TSlot end) {
7183 for (TSlot current = start; current < end; ++current) {
7184 typename TSlot::TObject object = current.load(isolate_);
7185 i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> heap_object;
7186 if (object.GetHeapObjectIfStrong(&heap_object)) {
7187 if (!VisitObject(heap_object)) {
7188 return;
7189 }
7190 }
7191 }
7192 }
7193
7194 bool FreezeEmbedderObjectAndVisitChildren(i::DirectHandle<i::JSObject> obj) {
7195 DCHECK(delegate_);
7196 LocalVector<Object> children(reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(isolate_));
7197 if (!delegate_->FreezeEmbedderObjectAndGetChildren(Utils::ToLocal(obj),
7198 children)) {
7199 return false;
7200 }
7201 for (auto child : children) {
7202 if (!VisitObject(
7203 *Utils::OpenDirectHandle<Object, i::JSReceiver>(child))) {
7204 return false;
7205 }
7206 }
7207 return true;
7208 }
7209
7210 bool VisitObject(i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> obj) {
7211 DCHECK(!obj.is_null());
7212 if (error_.has_value()) {
7213 return false;
7214 }
7215
7216 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
7217 i::InstanceType obj_type = obj->map()->instance_type();
7218
7219 // Skip common types that can't contain items to freeze.
7220 if (!MayContainObjectsToFreeze(obj_type)) {
7221 return true;
7222 }
7223
7224 if (!done_list_.insert(obj).second) {
7225 // If we couldn't insert (because it is already in the set) then we're
7226 // done.
7227 return true;
7228 }
7229
7230 if (i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsAccessorPair(obj_type)) {
7231 // For AccessorPairs we need to ensure that the functions they point to
7232 // have been instantiated into actual JavaScript objects that can be
7233 // frozen. If they haven't then we need to save them to instantiate
7234 // (and recurse) before freezing.
7235 i::Tagged<i::AccessorPair> accessor_pair = i::Cast<i::AccessorPair>(obj);
7236 if (i::IsFunctionTemplateInfo(accessor_pair->getter()) ||
7237 IsFunctionTemplateInfo(accessor_pair->setter())) {
7238 i::DirectHandle<i::AccessorPair> lazy_accessor_pair(accessor_pair,
7239 isolate_);
7240 lazy_accessor_pairs_to_freeze_.push_back(lazy_accessor_pair);
7241 }
7242 } else if (i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsContext(obj_type)) {
7243 // For contexts we need to ensure that all accessible locals are const.
7244 // If not they could be replaced to bypass freezing.
7245 i::Tagged<i::ScopeInfo> scope_info =
7246 i::Cast<i::Context>(obj)->scope_info();
7247 for (auto it : i::ScopeInfo::IterateLocalNames(scope_info, no_gc)) {
7248 if (!IsImmutableLexicalVariableMode(
7249 scope_info->ContextLocalMode(it->index()))) {
7250 DCHECK(!error_.has_value());
7251 error_ = ErrorInfo{i::MessageTemplate::kCannotDeepFreezeValue,
7252 i::direct_handle(it->name(), isolate_)};
7253 return false;
7254 }
7255 }
7256 } else if (i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSReceiver(obj_type)) {
7257 i::DirectHandle<i::JSReceiver> receiver(i::Cast<i::JSReceiver>(obj),
7258 isolate_);
7259 if (RequiresEmbedderSupportToFreeze(obj_type)) {
7260 auto js_obj = i::Cast<i::JSObject>(receiver);
7261
7262 // External objects don't have slots but still need to be processed by
7263 // the embedder.
7264 if (i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSExternalObject(obj_type) ||
7265 js_obj->GetEmbedderFieldCount() > 0) {
7266 if (!delegate_) {
7267 DCHECK(!error_.has_value());
7268 error_ =
7269 ErrorInfo{i::MessageTemplate::kCannotDeepFreezeObject,
7270 i::direct_handle(receiver->class_name(), isolate_)};
7271 return false;
7272 }
7273
7274 // Handle embedder specific types and any v8 children it wants to
7275 // freeze.
7276 if (!FreezeEmbedderObjectAndVisitChildren(js_obj)) {
7277 return false;
7278 }
7279 } else {
7280 DCHECK_EQ(js_obj->GetEmbedderFieldCount(), 0);
7281 }
7282 } else {
7283 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
7284 i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSObject(obj_type),
7285 i::Cast<i::JSObject>(*receiver)->GetEmbedderFieldCount() == 0);
7286 if (!IsJSReceiverSafeToFreeze(obj_type)) {
7287 DCHECK(!error_.has_value());
7288 error_ =
7289 ErrorInfo{i::MessageTemplate::kCannotDeepFreezeObject,
7290 i::direct_handle(receiver->class_name(), isolate_)};
7291 return false;
7292 }
7293 }
7294
7295 // Save this to freeze after we are done. Freezing triggers garbage
7296 // collection which doesn't work well with this visitor pattern, so we
7297 // delay it until after.
7298 objects_to_freeze_.push_back(receiver);
7299
7300 } else {
7301 DCHECK(!i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsAccessorPair(obj_type));
7302 DCHECK(!i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsContext(obj_type));
7303 DCHECK(!i::InstanceTypeChecker::IsJSReceiver(obj_type));
7304 }
7305
7306 DCHECK(!error_.has_value());
7307 i::VisitObject(isolate_, obj, this);
7308 // Iterate sets error_ on failure. We should propagate errors.
7309 return !error_.has_value();
7310 }
7311
7312 bool InstantiateAndVisitLazyAccessorPairs() {
7313 i::DirectHandle<i::NativeContext> native_context =
7314 isolate_->native_context();
7315
7316 i::DirectHandleVector<i::AccessorPair> lazy_accessor_pairs_to_freeze(
7317 isolate_);
7318 std::swap(lazy_accessor_pairs_to_freeze, lazy_accessor_pairs_to_freeze_);
7319
7320 for (const auto& accessor_pair : lazy_accessor_pairs_to_freeze) {
7321 i::AccessorPair::GetComponent(isolate_, native_context, accessor_pair,
7322 i::ACCESSOR_GETTER);
7323 i::AccessorPair::GetComponent(isolate_, native_context, accessor_pair,
7324 i::ACCESSOR_SETTER);
7325 VisitObject(*accessor_pair);
7326 }
7327 // Ensure no new lazy accessor pairs were discovered.
7328 CHECK_EQ(lazy_accessor_pairs_to_freeze_.size(), 0);
7329 return true;
7330 }
7331
7332 i::Isolate* isolate_;
7333 Context::DeepFreezeDelegate* delegate_;
7334 std::unordered_set<i::Tagged<i::Object>, i::Object::Hasher> done_list_;
7335 i::DirectHandleVector<i::JSReceiver> objects_to_freeze_;
7336 i::DirectHandleVector<i::AccessorPair> lazy_accessor_pairs_to_freeze_;
7337 std::optional<ErrorInfo> error_;
7338};
7339
7340} // namespace
7341
7342Maybe<void> Context::DeepFreeze(DeepFreezeDelegate* delegate) {
7343 auto env = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7344 i::Isolate* i_isolate = env->GetIsolate();
7345
7346 // TODO(behamilton): Incorporate compatibility improvements similar to NodeJS:
7347 // https://github.com/nodejs/node/blob/main/lib/internal/freeze_intrinsics.js
7348 // These need to be done before freezing.
7349
7350 Local<Context> context = Utils::ToLocal(env);
7351 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT(i_isolate, context, Context, DeepFreeze, i::HandleScope);
7352 ObjectVisitorDeepFreezer vfreezer(i_isolate, delegate);
7353 has_exception = !vfreezer.DeepFreeze(env);
7354
7355 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(void);
7356 return JustVoid();
7357}

7371void Context::SetMicrotaskQueue(v8::MicrotaskQueue* queue) {
7372 auto context = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7373 i::Isolate* i_isolate = context->GetIsolate();
7374 Utils::ApiCheck(i::IsNativeContext(*context),
7375 "v8::Context::SetMicrotaskQueue",
7376 "Must be called on a native context");
7377 i::HandleScopeImplementer* impl = i_isolate->handle_scope_implementer();
7378 Utils::ApiCheck(!context->microtask_queue()->IsRunningMicrotasks(),
7379 "v8::Context::SetMicrotaskQueue",
7380 "Must not be running microtasks");
7381 Utils::ApiCheck(context->microtask_queue()->GetMicrotasksScopeDepth() == 0,
7382 "v8::Context::SetMicrotaskQueue",
7383 "Must not have microtask scope pushed");
7384 Utils::ApiCheck(impl->EnteredContextCount() == 0,
7385 "v8::Context::SetMicrotaskQueue()",
7386 "Cannot set Microtask Queue with an entered context");
7387 context->set_microtask_queue(i_isolate,
7388 static_cast<const i::MicrotaskQueue*>(queue));
7389}

7456
7457void v8::Context::SetPromiseHooks(Local<Function> init_hook,
7458 Local<Function> before_hook,
7459 Local<Function> after_hook,
7460 Local<Function> resolve_hook) {
7461#ifdef V8_ENABLE_JAVASCRIPT_PROMISE_HOOKS
7462 auto context = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7463 i::Isolate* i_isolate = context->GetIsolate();
7464
7465 auto undefined = i_isolate->factory()->undefined_value();
7466 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> init = undefined;
7467 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> before = undefined;
7468 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> after = undefined;
7469 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> resolve = undefined;
7470
7471 bool has_hook = false;
7472
7473 if (!init_hook.IsEmpty()) {
7474 init = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*init_hook);
7475 has_hook = true;
7476 }
7477 if (!before_hook.IsEmpty()) {
7478 before = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*before_hook);
7479 has_hook = true;
7480 }
7481 if (!after_hook.IsEmpty()) {
7482 after = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*after_hook);
7483 has_hook = true;
7484 }
7485 if (!resolve_hook.IsEmpty()) {
7486 resolve = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*resolve_hook);
7487 has_hook = true;
7488 }
7489
7490 i_isolate->SetHasContextPromiseHooks(has_hook);
7491
7492 context->native_context()->set_promise_hook_init_function(*init);
7493 context->native_context()->set_promise_hook_before_function(*before);
7494 context->native_context()->set_promise_hook_after_function(*after);
7495 context->native_context()->set_promise_hook_resolve_function(*resolve);
7496#else // V8_ENABLE_JAVASCRIPT_PROMISE_HOOKS
7497 Utils::ApiCheck(false, "v8::Context::SetPromiseHook",
7498 "V8 was compiled without JavaScript Promise hooks");
7499#endif // V8_ENABLE_JAVASCRIPT_PROMISE_HOOKS
7500}

7506 return Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this)
7507 ->native_context()
7508 ->HasTemplateLiteralObject(i::Cast<i::JSArray>(i_object));

7530namespace {
7531i::ValueHelper::InternalRepresentationType GetSerializedDataFromFixedArray(
7532 i::Isolate* i_isolate, i::Tagged<i::FixedArray> list, size_t index) {
7533 if (index < static_cast<size_t>(list->length())) {
7534 int int_index = static_cast<int>(index);
7535 i::Tagged<i::Object> object = list->get(int_index);
7536 if (!IsTheHole(object, i_isolate)) {
7537 list->set_the_hole(i_isolate, int_index);
7538 // Shrink the list so that the last element is not the hole (unless it's
7539 // the first element, because we don't want to end up with a non-canonical
7540 // empty FixedArray).
7541 int last = list->length() - 1;
7542 while (last >= 0 && list->is_the_hole(i_isolate, last)) last--;
7543 if (last != -1) list->RightTrim(i_isolate, last + 1);
7544 return i::Handle<i::Object>(object, i_isolate).repr();
7545 }
7546 }
7547 return i::ValueHelper::kEmpty;
7548}
7549} // anonymous namespace
7550
7551i::ValueHelper::InternalRepresentationType Context::GetDataFromSnapshotOnce(
7552 size_t index) {
7553 auto context = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7554 i::Isolate* i_isolate = context->GetIsolate();
7555 auto list = i::Cast<i::FixedArray>(context->serialized_objects());
7556 return GetSerializedDataFromFixedArray(i_isolate, list, index);
7557}

7567}

7605
7606MaybeLocal<v8::Object> FunctionTemplate::NewRemoteInstance() {
7607 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7608 i::Isolate* i_isolate = self->GetIsolateChecked();
7609 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, FunctionTemplate, NewRemoteInstance);
7610 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
7611 i::DirectHandle<i::FunctionTemplateInfo> constructor =
7612 EnsureConstructor(i_isolate, *InstanceTemplate());
7613 Utils::ApiCheck(constructor->needs_access_check(),
7614 "v8::FunctionTemplate::NewRemoteInstance",
7615 "InstanceTemplate needs to have access checks enabled");
7616 i::DirectHandle<i::AccessCheckInfo> access_check_info(
7617 i::Cast<i::AccessCheckInfo>(constructor->GetAccessCheckInfo()),
7618 i_isolate);
7619 Utils::ApiCheck(
7620 access_check_info->named_interceptor() != i::Tagged<i::Object>(),
7621 "v8::FunctionTemplate::NewRemoteInstance",
7622 "InstanceTemplate needs to have access check handlers");
7623 i::DirectHandle<i::JSObject> object;
7624 if (!i::ApiNatives::InstantiateRemoteObject(
7625 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*InstanceTemplate()))
7626 .ToHandle(&object)) {
7627 return MaybeLocal<Object>();
7628 }
7629 return Utils::ToLocal(scope.CloseAndEscape(object));
7630}
7631
7632bool FunctionTemplate::HasInstance(v8::Local<v8::Value> value) {
7633 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7634 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
7635 if (i::IsJSObject(*obj) && self->IsTemplateFor(i::Cast<i::JSObject>(*obj))) {
7636 return true;
7637 }
7638 if (i::IsJSGlobalProxy(*obj)) {
7639 // If it's a global proxy, then test with the global object. Note that the
7640 // inner global object may not necessarily be a JSGlobalObject.
7641 auto jsobj = i::Cast<i::JSObject>(*obj);
7642 i::PrototypeIterator iter(jsobj->GetIsolate(), jsobj->map());
7643 // The global proxy should always have a prototype, as it is a bug to call
7644 // this on a detached JSGlobalProxy.
7645 DCHECK(!iter.IsAtEnd());
7646 return self->IsTemplateFor(iter.GetCurrent<i::JSObject>());
7647 }
7648 return false;
7649}

7651bool FunctionTemplate::IsLeafTemplateForApiObject(
7652 v8::Local<v8::Value> value) const {
7653 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
7654 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7655 i::Tagged<i::Object> object = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
7656 return self->IsLeafTemplateForApiObject(object);
7657}
7658
7659Local<External> v8::External::New(Isolate* v8_isolate, void* value) {
7660 static_assert(sizeof(value) == sizeof(i::Address));
7661 // Nullptr is not allowed here because serialization/deserialization of
7662 // nullptr external api references is not possible as nullptr is used as an
7663 // external_references table terminator, see v8::SnapshotCreator()
7664 // constructors.
7665 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(value);
7666 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
7667 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, External, New);
7668 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
7669 i::DirectHandle<i::JSObject> external =
7670 i_isolate->factory()->NewExternal(value);
7671 return Utils::ExternalToLocal(external);
7672}
7673
7674void* External::Value() const {
7675 return i::Cast<i::JSExternalObject>(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this))->value();
7676}

7678// anonymous namespace for string creation helper functions
7679namespace {
7680
7681inline int StringLength(const char* string) {
7682 size_t len = strlen(string);
7683 CHECK_GE(i::kMaxInt, len);
7684 return static_cast<int>(len);
7685}
7686
7687inline int StringLength(const uint8_t* string) {
7688 return StringLength(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(string));
7689}
7690
7691inline int StringLength(const uint16_t* string) {
7692 size_t length = 0;
7693 while (string[length] != '\0') length++;
7694 CHECK_GE(i::kMaxInt, length);
7695 return static_cast<int>(length);
7696}
7697
7698V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT
7699inline i::MaybeHandle<i::String> NewString(i::Factory* factory,
7700 NewStringType type,
7701 base::Vector<const char> string) {
7702 if (type == NewStringType::kInternalized) {
7703 return factory->InternalizeUtf8String(string);
7704 }
7705 return factory->NewStringFromUtf8(string);
7706}
7707
7708V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT
7709inline i::MaybeHandle<i::String> NewString(i::Factory* factory,
7710 NewStringType type,
7711 base::Vector<const uint8_t> string) {
7712 if (type == NewStringType::kInternalized) {
7713 return factory->InternalizeString(string);
7714 }
7715 return factory->NewStringFromOneByte(string);
7716}
7717
7718V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT
7719inline i::MaybeHandle<i::String> NewString(
7720 i::Factory* factory, NewStringType type,
7721 base::Vector<const uint16_t> string) {
7722 if (type == NewStringType::kInternalized) {
7723 return factory->InternalizeString(string);
7724 }
7725 return factory->NewStringFromTwoByte(string);
7726}

7728static_assert(v8::String::kMaxLength == i::String::kMaxLength);

7732// TODO(dcarney): throw a context free exception.
7733#define NEW_STRING(v8_isolate, class_name, function_name, Char, data, type, \
7734 length) \
7735 MaybeLocal<String> result; \
7736 if (length == 0) { \
7737 result = String::Empty(v8_isolate); \
7738 } else if (length > 0 && \
7739 static_cast<uint32_t>(length) > i::String::kMaxLength) { \
7740 result = MaybeLocal<String>(); \
7741 } else { \
7742 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(v8_isolate); \
7743 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate); \
7744 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, class_name, function_name); \
7745 if (length < 0) length = StringLength(data); \
7746 i::DirectHandle<i::String> handle_result = \
7747 NewString(i_isolate->factory(), type, \
7748 base::Vector<const Char>(data, length)) \
7749 .ToHandleChecked(); \
7750 result = Utils::ToLocal(handle_result); \
7751 }
7752
7753Local<String> String::NewFromUtf8Literal(Isolate* v8_isolate,
7754 const char* literal,
7755 NewStringType type, int length) {
7756 DCHECK_LE(length, i::String::kMaxLength);
7757 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
7758 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
7759 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, String, NewFromUtf8Literal);
7760 i::DirectHandle<i::String> handle_result =
7761 NewString(i_isolate->factory(), type,
7762 base::Vector<const char>(literal, length))
7763 .ToHandleChecked();
7764 return Utils::ToLocal(handle_result);
7765}
7766
7767MaybeLocal<String> String::NewFromUtf8(Isolate* v8_isolate, const char* data,
7768 NewStringType type, int length) {
7769 NEW_STRING(v8_isolate, String, NewFromUtf8, char, data, type, length);
7770 return result;
7771}
7772
7773MaybeLocal<String> String::NewFromOneByte(Isolate* v8_isolate,
7774 const uint8_t* data,
7775 NewStringType type, int length) {
7776 NEW_STRING(v8_isolate, String, NewFromOneByte, uint8_t, data, type, length);
7777 return result;
7778}
7779
7780MaybeLocal<String> String::NewFromTwoByte(Isolate* v8_isolate,
7781 const uint16_t* data,
7782 NewStringType type, int length) {
7783 NEW_STRING(v8_isolate, String, NewFromTwoByte, uint16_t, data, type, length);
7784 return result;
7785}
7786
7787Local<String> v8::String::Concat(Isolate* v8_isolate, Local<String> left,
7788 Local<String> right) {
7789 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
7790 auto left_string = Utils::OpenHandle(*left);
7791 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
7792 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, String, Concat);
7793 auto right_string = Utils::OpenHandle(*right);
7794 // If we are steering towards a range error, do not wait for the error to be
7795 // thrown, and return the null handle instead.
7796 if (left_string->length() + right_string->length() > i::String::kMaxLength) {
7797 return Local<String>();
7798 }
7799 i::DirectHandle<i::String> result =
7800 i_isolate->factory()
7801 ->NewConsString(left_string, right_string)
7802 .ToHandleChecked();
7803 return Utils::ToLocal(result);
7804}
7805
7806MaybeLocal<String> v8::String::NewExternalTwoByte(
7807 Isolate* v8_isolate, v8::String::ExternalStringResource* resource) {
7808 CHECK(resource && resource->data());
7809 // TODO(dcarney): throw a context free exception.
7810 if (resource->length() > static_cast<size_t>(i::String::kMaxLength)) {
7811 return MaybeLocal<String>();
7812 }
7813 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
7814 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
7815 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, String, NewExternalTwoByte);
7816 if (resource->length() > 0) {
7817 i::DirectHandle<i::String> string =
7818 i_isolate->factory()
7819 ->NewExternalStringFromTwoByte(resource)
7820 .ToHandleChecked();
7821 return Utils::ToLocal(string);
7822 } else {
7823 // The resource isn't going to be used, free it immediately.
7824 resource->Unaccount(v8_isolate);
7825 resource->Dispose();
7826 return Utils::ToLocal(i_isolate->factory()->empty_string());
7827 }
7828}
7829
7830MaybeLocal<String> v8::String::NewExternalOneByte(
7831 Isolate* v8_isolate, v8::String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* resource) {
7832 CHECK_NOT_NULL(resource);
7833 // TODO(dcarney): throw a context free exception.
7834 if (resource->length() > static_cast<size_t>(i::String::kMaxLength)) {
7835 return MaybeLocal<String>();
7836 }
7837 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
7838 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
7839 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, String, NewExternalOneByte);
7840 if (resource->length() == 0) {
7841 // The resource isn't going to be used, free it immediately.
7842 resource->Unaccount(v8_isolate);
7843 resource->Dispose();
7844 return Utils::ToLocal(i_isolate->factory()->empty_string());
7845 }
7846 CHECK_NOT_NULL(resource->data());
7847 i::DirectHandle<i::String> string =
7848 i_isolate->factory()
7849 ->NewExternalStringFromOneByte(resource)
7850 .ToHandleChecked();
7851 return Utils::ToLocal(string);
7852}
7853
7854bool v8::String::MakeExternal(v8::String::ExternalStringResource* resource) {
7855 v8::Isolate* isolate = reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i::Isolate::Current());
7856 return MakeExternal(isolate, resource);
7857}
7858
7859bool v8::String::MakeExternal(Isolate* isolate,
7860 v8::String::ExternalStringResource* resource) {
7861 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
7862
7863 i::Tagged<i::String> obj = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7864
7865 if (i::IsThinString(obj)) {
7866 obj = i::Cast<i::ThinString>(obj)->actual();
7867 }
7868
7869 if (!obj->SupportsExternalization(Encoding::TWO_BYTE_ENCODING)) {
7870 return false;
7871 }
7872
7873 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
7874 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
7875
7876 CHECK(resource && resource->data());
7877
7878 bool result = obj->MakeExternal(i_isolate, resource);
7879 DCHECK_IMPLIES(result, HasExternalStringResource(obj));
7880 return result;
7881}
7882
7883bool v8::String::MakeExternal(
7884 v8::String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* resource) {
7885 v8::Isolate* isolate = reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i::Isolate::Current());
7886 return MakeExternal(isolate, resource);
7887}

7889bool v8::String::MakeExternal(
7890 Isolate* isolate, v8::String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* resource) {
7891 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
7892
7893 i::Tagged<i::String> obj = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
7894
7895 if (i::IsThinString(obj)) {
7896 obj = i::Cast<i::ThinString>(obj)->actual();
7897 }
7898
7899 if (!obj->SupportsExternalization(Encoding::ONE_BYTE_ENCODING)) {
7900 return false;
7901 }
7902
7903 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
7904 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
7905
7906 CHECK(resource && resource->data());
7907
7908 bool result = obj->MakeExternal(i_isolate, resource);
7909 DCHECK_IMPLIES(result, HasExternalStringResource(obj));
7910 return result;
7911}

7939namespace {
7940
7941// TODO(v8:7569): This is a workaround for the Handle vs MaybeHandle difference
7942// in the return types of the different Add functions:
7943// OrderedNameDictionary::Add returns MaybeHandle, NameDictionary::Add returns
7944// Handle.
7945template <typename T>
7946i::Handle<T> ToHandle(i::Handle<T> h) {
7947 return h;
7948}
7949template <typename T>
7950i::Handle<T> ToHandle(i::MaybeHandle<T> h) {
7951 return h.ToHandleChecked();
7952}
7953
7954template <typename T>
7955i::DirectHandle<T> ToHandle(i::DirectHandle<T> h) {
7956 return h;
7957}
7958template <typename T>
7959i::DirectHandle<T> ToHandle(i::MaybeDirectHandle<T> h) {
7960 return h.ToHandleChecked();
7961}
7962
7963template <typename Dictionary>
7964void AddPropertiesAndElementsToObject(
7965 i::Isolate* i_isolate, i::DirectHandle<Dictionary>& properties,
7966 i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArrayBase>& elements, Local<Name>* names,
7967 Local<Value>* values, size_t length) {
7968 for (size_t i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
7969 auto name = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*names[i]);
7970 auto value = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*values[i]);
7971
7972 // See if the {name} is a valid array index, in which case we need to
7973 // add the {name}/{value} pair to the {elements}, otherwise they end
7974 // up in the {properties} backing store.
7975 uint32_t index;
7976 if (name->AsArrayIndex(&index)) {
7977 // If this is the first element, allocate a proper
7978 // dictionary elements backing store for {elements}.
7979 if (!IsNumberDictionary(*elements)) {
7980 elements =
7981 i::NumberDictionary::New(i_isolate, static_cast<int>(length));
7982 }
7983 elements = i::NumberDictionary::Set(
7984 i_isolate, i::Cast<i::NumberDictionary>(elements), index, value);
7985 } else {
7986 // Internalize the {name} first.
7987 name = i_isolate->factory()->InternalizeName(name);
7988 i::InternalIndex const entry = properties->FindEntry(i_isolate, name);
7989 if (entry.is_not_found()) {
7990 // Add the {name}/{value} pair as a new entry.
7991 properties = ToHandle(Dictionary::Add(
7992 i_isolate, properties, name, value, i::PropertyDetails::Empty()));
7993 } else {
7994 // Overwrite the {entry} with the {value}.
7995 properties->ValueAtPut(entry, *value);
7996 }
7997 }
7998 }
7999}
8000
8001} // namespace
8002
8003Local<v8::Object> v8::Object::New(Isolate* v8_isolate,
8004 Local<Value> prototype_or_null,
8005 Local<Name>* names, Local<Value>* values,
8006 size_t length) {
8007 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
8008 i::DirectHandle<i::JSPrototype> proto;
8009 if (!Utils::ApiCheck(
8010 i::TryCast(Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*prototype_or_null), &proto),
8011 "v8::Object::New", "prototype must be null or object")) {
8012 return Local<v8::Object>();
8013 }
8014 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, Object, New);
8015 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
8016
8017 i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArrayBase> elements =
8018 i_isolate->factory()->empty_fixed_array();
8019
8020 // We assume that this API is mostly used to create objects with named
8021 // properties, and so we default to creating a properties backing store
8022 // large enough to hold all of them, while we start with no elements
8023 // (see http://bit.ly/v8-fast-object-create-cpp for the motivation).
8024 if (V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL) {
8025 i::DirectHandle<i::SwissNameDictionary> properties =
8026 i_isolate->factory()->NewSwissNameDictionary(static_cast<int>(length));
8027 AddPropertiesAndElementsToObject(i_isolate, properties, elements, names,
8028 values, length);
8029 i::DirectHandle<i::JSObject> obj =
8030 i_isolate->factory()->NewSlowJSObjectWithPropertiesAndElements(
8031 proto, properties, elements);
8032 return Utils::ToLocal(obj);
8033 } else {
8034 i::DirectHandle<i::NameDictionary> properties =
8035 i::NameDictionary::New(i_isolate, static_cast<int>(length));
8036 AddPropertiesAndElementsToObject(i_isolate, properties, elements, names,
8037 values, length);
8038 i::DirectHandle<i::JSObject> obj =
8039 i_isolate->factory()->NewSlowJSObjectWithPropertiesAndElements(
8040 proto, properties, elements);
8041 return Utils::ToLocal(obj);
8042 }
8043}

8140
8141MaybeLocal<v8::Value> v8::Date::New(Local<Context> context, double time) {
8142 if (std::isnan(time)) {
8143 // Introduce only canonical NaN value into the VM, to avoid signaling NaNs.
8144 time = std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
8145 }
8146 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, Date, New);
8147 Local<Value> result;
8148 has_exception =
8149 !ToLocal<Value>(i::JSDate::New(i_isolate->date_function(),
8150 i_isolate->date_function(), time),
8151 &result);
8152 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Value);
8153 RETURN_ESCAPED(result);
8154}
8155
8156MaybeLocal<Value> v8::Date::Parse(Local<Context> context, Local<String> value) {
8157 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, Date, Parse);
8158 auto string = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value);
8159 double time = ParseDateTimeString(i_isolate, string);
8160
8161 Local<Value> result;
8162 has_exception =
8163 !ToLocal<Value>(i::JSDate::New(i_isolate->date_function(),
8164 i_isolate->date_function(), time),
8165 &result);
8166
8167 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Value)
8168 RETURN_ESCAPED(result);
8169}
8170
8171double v8::Date::ValueOf() const {
8172 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8173 auto jsdate = i::Cast<i::JSDate>(obj);
8174 return jsdate->value();
8175}

8177v8::Local<v8::String> v8::Date::ToISOString() const {
8178 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8179 auto jsdate = i::Cast<i::JSDate>(obj);
8180 i::Isolate* i_isolate = jsdate->GetIsolate();
8181 i::DateBuffer buffer =
8182 i::ToDateString(jsdate->value(), i_isolate->date_cache(),
8183 i::ToDateStringMode::kISODateAndTime);
8184 i::DirectHandle<i::String> str =
8185 i_isolate->factory()
8186 ->NewStringFromUtf8(base::VectorOf(buffer))
8187 .ToHandleChecked();
8188 return Utils::ToLocal(str);
8189}

8227MaybeLocal<v8::RegExp> v8::RegExp::NewWithBacktrackLimit(
8228 Local<Context> context, Local<String> pattern, Flags flags,
8229 uint32_t backtrack_limit) {
8230 Utils::ApiCheck(i::Smi::IsValid(backtrack_limit),
8231 "v8::RegExp::NewWithBacktrackLimit",
8232 "backtrack_limit is too large or too small");
8233 Utils::ApiCheck(backtrack_limit != i::JSRegExp::kNoBacktrackLimit,
8234 "v8::RegExp::NewWithBacktrackLimit",
8235 "Must set backtrack_limit");
8236 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, RegExp, New);
8237 Local<v8::RegExp> result;
8238 has_exception = !ToLocal<RegExp>(
8239 i::JSRegExp::New(i_isolate, Utils::OpenHandle(*pattern),
8240 static_cast<i::JSRegExp::Flags>(flags), backtrack_limit),
8241 &result);
8242 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(RegExp);
8243 RETURN_ESCAPED(result);
8244}

8266
8267v8::RegExp::Flags v8::RegExp::GetFlags() const {
8268 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8269 return RegExp::Flags(static_cast<int>(obj->flags()));
8270}
8271
8272MaybeLocal<v8::Object> v8::RegExp::Exec(Local<Context> context,
8273 Local<v8::String> subject) {
8274 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, RegExp, Exec);
8275
8276 auto regexp = Utils::OpenHandle(this);
8277 auto subject_string = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*subject);
8278
8279 // TODO(jgruber): RegExpUtils::RegExpExec was not written with efficiency in
8280 // mind. It fetches the 'exec' property and then calls it through JSEntry.
8281 // Unfortunately, this is currently the only full implementation of
8282 // RegExp.prototype.exec available in C++.
8283 Local<v8::Object> result;
8284 has_exception = !ToLocal<Object>(
8285 i::RegExpUtils::RegExpExec(i_isolate, regexp, subject_string,
8286 i_isolate->factory()->undefined_value()),
8287 &result);
8288
8289 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Object);
8290 RETURN_ESCAPED(result);
8291}

8293Local<v8::Array> v8::Array::New(Isolate* v8_isolate, int length) {
8294 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
8295 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, Array, New);
8296 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
8297 int real_length = length > 0 ? length : 0;
8298 i::DirectHandle<i::JSArray> obj =
8299 i_isolate->factory()->NewJSArray(real_length);
8300 i::DirectHandle<i::Number> length_obj =
8301 i_isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromInt(real_length);
8302 obj->set_length(*length_obj);
8303 return Utils::ToLocal(obj);
8304}
8305
8306Local<v8::Array> v8::Array::New(Isolate* v8_isolate, Local<Value>* elements,
8307 size_t length) {
8308 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
8309 i::Factory* factory = i_isolate->factory();
8310 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, Array, New);
8311 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
8312 int len = static_cast<int>(length);
8313
8314 i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArray> result = factory->NewFixedArray(len);
8315 for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
8316 auto element = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*elements[i]);
8317 result->set(i, *element);
8318 }
8319
8320 return Utils::ToLocal(
8321 factory->NewJSArrayWithElements(result, i::PACKED_ELEMENTS, len));
8322}
8323
8324// static
8325MaybeLocal<v8::Array> v8::Array::New(
8326 Local<Context> context, size_t length,
8327 std::function<MaybeLocal<v8::Value>()> next_value_callback) {
8328 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, Array, New);
8329 // We should never see an exception here as V8 will not create an
8330 // exception and the callback is invoked by the embedder where the exception
8331 // is already scheduled.
8332 USE(has_exception);
8333 i::Factory* factory = i_isolate->factory();
8334 const int len = static_cast<int>(length);
8335 i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArray> backing = factory->NewFixedArray(len);
8336 v8::Local<v8::Value> value;
8337 for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
8338 MaybeLocal<v8::Value> maybe_value = next_value_callback();
8339 // The embedder may signal to abort creation on exception via an empty
8340 // local.
8341 if (!maybe_value.ToLocal(&value)) {
8342 CHECK(i_isolate->has_exception());
8343 return {};
8344 }
8345 backing->set(i, *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value));
8346 }
8347 RETURN_ESCAPED(Utils::ToLocal(
8348 factory->NewJSArrayWithElements(backing, i::PACKED_ELEMENTS, len)));
8349}

8352
8353uint32_t GetLength(Tagged<JSArray> array) {
8354 Tagged<Number> length = array->length();
8355 if (IsSmi(length)) return Smi::ToInt(length);
8356 return static_cast<uint32_t>(Object::NumberValue(length));
8357}

8359} // namespace internal
8360
8361uint32_t v8::Array::Length() const {
8362 return i::GetLength(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this));
8363}

8365namespace internal {
8366
8367bool CanUseFastIteration(Isolate* isolate, DirectHandle<JSArray> array) {
8368 if (IsCustomElementsReceiverMap(array->map())) return false;
8369 if (array->GetElementsAccessor()->HasAccessors(*array)) return false;
8370 if (!JSObject::PrototypeHasNoElements(isolate, *array)) return false;
8371 return true;
8372}
8373
8374enum class FastIterateResult {
8375 kException = static_cast<int>(v8::Array::CallbackResult::kException),
8376 kBreak = static_cast<int>(v8::Array::CallbackResult::kBreak),
8377 kSlowPath,
8378 kFinished,
8379};
8380
8381FastIterateResult FastIterateArray(DirectHandle<JSArray> array,
8382 Isolate* isolate,
8383 v8::Array::IterationCallback callback,
8384 void* callback_data) {
8385 // Instead of relying on callers to check condition, this function returns
8386 // {kSlowPath} for situations it can't handle.
8387 // Most code paths below don't allocate, and rely on {callback} not allocating
8388 // either, but this isn't enforced with {DisallowHeapAllocation} to allow
8389 // embedders to allocate error objects before terminating the iteration.
8390 // Since {callback} must not allocate anyway, we can get away with fake
8391 // handles, reducing per-element overhead.
8392 if (!CanUseFastIteration(isolate, array)) return FastIterateResult::kSlowPath;
8393 using Result = v8::Array::CallbackResult;
8394 DisallowJavascriptExecution no_js(isolate);
8395 uint32_t length = GetLength(*array);
8396 if (length == 0) return FastIterateResult::kFinished;
8397 switch (array->GetElementsKind()) {
8398 case PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS:
8399 case PACKED_ELEMENTS:
8400 case PACKED_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
8401 case PACKED_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
8402 case PACKED_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS: {
8403 Tagged<FixedArray> elements = Cast<FixedArray>(array->elements());
8404 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
8405 Tagged<Object> element = elements->get(static_cast<int>(i));
8406 // TODO(13270): When we switch to CSS, we can pass {element} to
8407 // the callback directly, without {fake_handle}.
8408 IndirectHandle<Object> fake_handle(
8409 reinterpret_cast<Address*>(&element));
8410 Result result = callback(i, Utils::ToLocal(fake_handle), callback_data);
8411 if (result != Result::kContinue) {
8412 return static_cast<FastIterateResult>(result);
8413 }
8414 DCHECK(CanUseFastIteration(isolate, array));
8415 }
8416 return FastIterateResult::kFinished;
8417 }
8418 case HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS:
8419 case HOLEY_FROZEN_ELEMENTS:
8420 case HOLEY_SEALED_ELEMENTS:
8421 case HOLEY_NONEXTENSIBLE_ELEMENTS:
8422 case HOLEY_ELEMENTS: {
8423 Tagged<FixedArray> elements = Cast<FixedArray>(array->elements());
8424 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
8425 Tagged<Object> element = elements->get(static_cast<int>(i));
8426 // TODO(13270): When we switch to CSS, we can pass {element} to
8427 // the callback directly, without {fake_handle}.
8428 auto fake_handle =
8429 IsTheHole(element)
8430 ? isolate->factory()->undefined_value()
8431 : IndirectHandle<Object>(reinterpret_cast<Address*>(&element));
8432 Result result = callback(i, Utils::ToLocal(fake_handle), callback_data);
8433 if (result != Result::kContinue) {
8434 return static_cast<FastIterateResult>(result);
8435 }
8436 DCHECK(CanUseFastIteration(isolate, array));
8437 }
8438 return FastIterateResult::kFinished;
8439 }
8440 case HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS:
8441 case PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS: {
8442 DCHECK_NE(length, 0); // Cast to FixedDoubleArray would be invalid.
8443 DirectHandle<FixedDoubleArray> elements(
8444 Cast<FixedDoubleArray>(array->elements()), isolate);
8445 FOR_WITH_HANDLE_SCOPE(isolate, uint32_t, i = 0, i, i < length, i++, {
8446 DirectHandle<Object> value =
8447 elements->is_the_hole(i)
8448 ? Handle<Object>(isolate->factory()->undefined_value())
8449 : isolate->factory()->NewNumber(elements->get_scalar(i));
8450 Result result = callback(i, Utils::ToLocal(value), callback_data);
8451 if (result != Result::kContinue) {
8452 return static_cast<FastIterateResult>(result);
8453 }
8454 DCHECK(CanUseFastIteration(isolate, array));
8455 });
8456 return FastIterateResult::kFinished;
8457 }
8458 case DICTIONARY_ELEMENTS: {
8459 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
8460 Tagged<NumberDictionary> dict = array->element_dictionary();
8461 struct Entry {
8462 uint32_t index;
8463 InternalIndex entry;
8464 };
8465 std::vector<Entry> sorted;
8466 sorted.reserve(dict->NumberOfElements());
8467 ReadOnlyRoots roots(isolate);
8468 for (InternalIndex i : dict->IterateEntries()) {
8469 Tagged<Object> key = dict->KeyAt(isolate, i);
8470 if (!dict->IsKey(roots, key)) continue;
8471 uint32_t index =
8472 static_cast<uint32_t>(Object::NumberValue(Cast<Number>(key)));
8473 sorted.push_back({index, i});
8474 }
8475 std::sort(
8476 sorted.begin(), sorted.end(),
8477 [](const Entry& a, const Entry& b) { return a.index < b.index; });
8478 for (const Entry& entry : sorted) {
8479 Tagged<Object> value = dict->ValueAt(entry.entry);
8480 // TODO(13270): When we switch to CSS, we can pass {element} to
8481 // the callback directly, without {fake_handle}.
8482 IndirectHandle<Object> fake_handle(reinterpret_cast<Address*>(&value));
8483 Result result =
8484 callback(entry.index, Utils::ToLocal(fake_handle), callback_data);
8485 if (result != Result::kContinue) {
8486 return static_cast<FastIterateResult>(result);
8487 }
8488 SLOW_DCHECK(CanUseFastIteration(isolate, array));
8489 }
8490 return FastIterateResult::kFinished;
8491 }
8492 case NO_ELEMENTS:
8493 return FastIterateResult::kFinished;
8494 case FAST_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
8495 case SLOW_SLOPPY_ARGUMENTS_ELEMENTS:
8496 // Probably not worth implementing. Take the slow path.
8497 return FastIterateResult::kSlowPath;
8498 case WASM_ARRAY_ELEMENTS:
8499 case FAST_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
8500 case SLOW_STRING_WRAPPER_ELEMENTS:
8501 case SHARED_ARRAY_ELEMENTS:
8502#define TYPED_ARRAY_CASE(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) case TYPE##_ELEMENTS:
8503 TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
8504 RAB_GSAB_TYPED_ARRAYS(TYPED_ARRAY_CASE)
8505#undef TYPED_ARRAY_CASE
8506 // These are never used by v8::Array instances.
8507 UNREACHABLE();
8508 }
8509}
8510
8511} // namespace internal
8512
8513Maybe<void> v8::Array::Iterate(Local<Context> context,
8514 v8::Array::IterationCallback callback,
8515 void* callback_data) {
8516 auto array = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8517 i::Isolate* isolate = array->GetIsolate();
8518 i::FastIterateResult fast_result =
8519 i::FastIterateArray(array, isolate, callback, callback_data);
8520 if (fast_result == i::FastIterateResult::kException) return Nothing<void>();
8521 // Early breaks and completed iteration both return successfully.
8522 if (fast_result != i::FastIterateResult::kSlowPath) return JustVoid();
8523
8524 // Slow path: retrieving elements could have side effects.
8525 ENTER_V8(isolate, context, Array, Iterate, i::HandleScope);
8526 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < i::GetLength(*array); ++i) {
8527 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> element;
8528 has_exception =
8529 !i::JSReceiver::GetElement(isolate, array, i).ToHandle(&element);
8530 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(void);
8531 using Result = v8::Array::CallbackResult;
8532 Result result = callback(i, Utils::ToLocal(element), callback_data);
8533 if (result == Result::kException) return Nothing<void>();
8534 if (result == Result::kBreak) return JustVoid();
8535 }
8536 return JustVoid();
8537}
8538
8539v8::TypecheckWitness::TypecheckWitness(Isolate* isolate)
8540#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DIRECT_HANDLE
8541 // An empty local suffices.
8542 : cached_map_()
8543#else
8544 // We need to reserve a handle that we can patch later.
8545 // We initialize it with something that cannot compare equal to any map.
8546 : cached_map_(v8::Number::New(isolate, 1))
8547#endif
8548{
8549}
8550
8551void v8::TypecheckWitness::Update(Local<Value> baseline) {
8552 i::Tagged<i::Object> obj = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*baseline);
8553#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DIRECT_HANDLE
8554 if (IsSmi(obj)) {
8555 cached_map_ = Local<Data>();
8556 } else {
8557 i::Tagged<i::HeapObject> map = i::Cast<i::HeapObject>(obj)->map();
8558 cached_map_ = Local<Data>::FromAddress(map->ptr());
8559 }
8560#else
8561 i::Tagged<i::Object> map = i::Smi::zero();
8562 if (!IsSmi(obj)) map = i::Cast<i::HeapObject>(obj)->map();
8563 // Design overview: in the {TypecheckWitness} constructor, we create
8564 // a single handle for the witness value. Whenever {Update} is called, we
8565 // make this handle point at the fresh baseline/witness; the intention is
8566 // to allow having short-lived HandleScopes (e.g. in {FastIterateArray}
8567 // above) while a {TypecheckWitness} is alive: it therefore cannot hold
8568 // on to one of the short-lived handles.
8569 // Calling {OpenIndirectHandle} on the {cached_map_} only serves to
8570 // "reinterpret_cast" it to an {i::IndirectHandle} on which we can call
8571 // {PatchValue}.
8572 auto cache = Utils::OpenIndirectHandle(*cached_map_);
8573 cache.PatchValue(map);
8574#endif
8575}

8651namespace {
8652
8653enum class MapAsArrayKind {
8654 kEntries = i::JS_MAP_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE,
8655 kKeys = i::JS_MAP_KEY_ITERATOR_TYPE,
8656 kValues = i::JS_MAP_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE
8657};
8658
8659enum class SetAsArrayKind {
8660 kEntries = i::JS_SET_KEY_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE,
8661 kValues = i::JS_SET_VALUE_ITERATOR_TYPE
8662};
8663
8664i::Handle<i::JSArray> MapAsArray(i::Isolate* i_isolate,
8665 i::Tagged<i::Object> table_obj, int offset,
8666 MapAsArrayKind kind) {
8667 i::Factory* factory = i_isolate->factory();
8668 i::DirectHandle<i::OrderedHashMap> table(
8669 i::Cast<i::OrderedHashMap>(table_obj), i_isolate);
8670 const bool collect_keys =
8671 kind == MapAsArrayKind::kEntries || kind == MapAsArrayKind::kKeys;
8672 const bool collect_values =
8673 kind == MapAsArrayKind::kEntries || kind == MapAsArrayKind::kValues;
8674 int capacity = table->UsedCapacity();
8675 int max_length =
8676 (capacity - offset) * ((collect_keys && collect_values) ? 2 : 1);
8677 i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArray> result = factory->NewFixedArray(max_length);
8678 int result_index = 0;
8679 {
8680 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
8681 i::Tagged<i::Hole> hash_table_hole =
8682 i::ReadOnlyRoots(i_isolate).hash_table_hole_value();
8683 for (int i = offset; i < capacity; ++i) {
8684 i::InternalIndex entry(i);
8685 i::Tagged<i::Object> key = table->KeyAt(entry);
8686 if (key == hash_table_hole) continue;
8687 if (collect_keys) result->set(result_index++, key);
8688 if (collect_values) result->set(result_index++, table->ValueAt(entry));
8689 }
8690 }
8691 DCHECK_GE(max_length, result_index);
8692 if (result_index == 0) return factory->NewJSArray(0);
8693 result->RightTrim(i_isolate, result_index);
8694 return factory->NewJSArrayWithElements(result, i::PACKED_ELEMENTS,
8695 result_index);
8696}
8697
8698} // namespace
8699
8700Local<Array> Map::AsArray() const {
8701 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8702 i::Isolate* i_isolate = obj->GetIsolate();
8703 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, Map, AsArray);
8704 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
8705 return Utils::ToLocal(
8706 MapAsArray(i_isolate, obj->table(), 0, MapAsArrayKind::kEntries));
8707}

8767
8768namespace {
8769i::Handle<i::JSArray> SetAsArray(i::Isolate* i_isolate,
8770 i::Tagged<i::Object> table_obj, int offset,
8771 SetAsArrayKind kind) {
8772 i::Factory* factory = i_isolate->factory();
8773 i::DirectHandle<i::OrderedHashSet> table(
8774 i::Cast<i::OrderedHashSet>(table_obj), i_isolate);
8775 // Elements skipped by |offset| may already be deleted.
8776 int capacity = table->UsedCapacity();
8777 const bool collect_key_values = kind == SetAsArrayKind::kEntries;
8778 int max_length = (capacity - offset) * (collect_key_values ? 2 : 1);
8779 if (max_length == 0) return factory->NewJSArray(0);
8780 i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArray> result = factory->NewFixedArray(max_length);
8781 int result_index = 0;
8782 {
8783 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
8784 i::Tagged<i::Hole> hash_table_hole =
8785 i::ReadOnlyRoots(i_isolate).hash_table_hole_value();
8786 for (int i = offset; i < capacity; ++i) {
8787 i::InternalIndex entry(i);
8788 i::Tagged<i::Object> key = table->KeyAt(entry);
8789 if (key == hash_table_hole) continue;
8790 result->set(result_index++, key);
8791 if (collect_key_values) result->set(result_index++, key);
8792 }
8793 }
8794 DCHECK_GE(max_length, result_index);
8795 if (result_index == 0) return factory->NewJSArray(0);
8796 result->RightTrim(i_isolate, result_index);
8797 return factory->NewJSArrayWithElements(result, i::PACKED_ELEMENTS,
8798 result_index);
8799}
8800} // namespace
8801
8802Local<Array> Set::AsArray() const {
8803 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8804 i::Isolate* i_isolate = obj->GetIsolate();
8805 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, Set, AsArray);
8806 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
8807 return Utils::ToLocal(
8808 SetAsArray(i_isolate, obj->table(), 0, SetAsArrayKind::kValues));
8809}

8811MaybeLocal<Promise::Resolver> Promise::Resolver::New(Local<Context> context) {
8812 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, Promise_Resolver, New);
8813 Local<Promise::Resolver> result;
8814 has_exception = !ToLocal<Promise::Resolver>(
8815 i_isolate->factory()->NewJSPromise(), &result);
8816 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Promise::Resolver);
8817 RETURN_ESCAPED(result);
8818}
8819
8820Local<Promise> Promise::Resolver::GetPromise() {
8821 auto promise = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8822 return Local<Promise>::Cast(Utils::ToLocal(promise));
8823}
8824
8825Maybe<bool> Promise::Resolver::Resolve(Local<Context> context,
8826 Local<Value> value) {
8827 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
8828 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Promise_Resolver, Resolve, i::HandleScope);
8829 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8830 auto promise = i::Cast<i::JSPromise>(self);
8831
8832 if (promise->status() != Promise::kPending) {
8833 return Just(true);
8834 }
8835
8836 has_exception =
8837 i::JSPromise::Resolve(promise, Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value)).is_null();
8838 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
8839 return Just(true);
8840}
8841
8842Maybe<bool> Promise::Resolver::Reject(Local<Context> context,
8843 Local<Value> value) {
8844 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
8845 ENTER_V8(i_isolate, context, Promise_Resolver, Reject, i::HandleScope);
8846 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8847 auto promise = i::Cast<i::JSPromise>(self);
8848
8849 if (promise->status() != Promise::kPending) {
8850 return Just(true);
8851 }
8852
8853 has_exception =
8854 i::JSPromise::Reject(promise, Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value)).is_null();
8855 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
8856 return Just(true);
8857}
8858
8859MaybeLocal<Promise> Promise::Catch(Local<Context> context,
8860 Local<Function> handler) {
8861 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, Promise, Catch);
8862 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8863 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> args[] = {i_isolate->factory()->undefined_value(),
8864 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*handler)};
8865 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> result;
8866 // Do not call the built-in Promise.prototype.catch!
8867 // v8::Promise should not call out to a monkeypatched Promise.prototype.then
8868 // as the implementation of Promise.prototype.catch does.
8869 has_exception =
8870 !i::Execution::CallBuiltin(i_isolate, i_isolate->promise_then(), self,
8871 base::VectorOf(args))
8872 .ToHandle(&result);
8873 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Promise);
8874 RETURN_ESCAPED(Local<Promise>::Cast(Utils::ToLocal(result)));
8875}
8876
8877MaybeLocal<Promise> Promise::Then(Local<Context> context,
8878 Local<Function> handler) {
8879 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, Promise, Then);
8880 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8881 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> args[] = {Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*handler)};
8882 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> result;
8883 has_exception =
8884 !i::Execution::CallBuiltin(i_isolate, i_isolate->promise_then(), self,
8885 base::VectorOf(args))
8886 .ToHandle(&result);
8887 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Promise);
8888 RETURN_ESCAPED(Local<Promise>::Cast(Utils::ToLocal(result)));
8889}
8890
8891MaybeLocal<Promise> Promise::Then(Local<Context> context,
8892 Local<Function> on_fulfilled,
8893 Local<Function> on_rejected) {
8894 PREPARE_FOR_EXECUTION(context, Promise, Then);
8895 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8896 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> args[] = {Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*on_fulfilled),
8897 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*on_rejected)};
8898 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> result;
8899 has_exception =
8900 !i::Execution::CallBuiltin(i_isolate, i_isolate->promise_then(), self,
8901 base::VectorOf(args))
8902 .ToHandle(&result);
8903 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION(Promise);
8904 RETURN_ESCAPED(Local<Promise>::Cast(Utils::ToLocal(result)));
8905}
8906
8907bool Promise::HasHandler() const {
8908 i::Tagged<i::JSReceiver> promise = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8909 i::Isolate* i_isolate = promise->GetIsolate();
8910 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, Promise, HasRejectHandler);
8911 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
8912 if (!IsJSPromise(promise)) return false;
8913 return i::Cast<i::JSPromise>(promise)->has_handler();
8914}
8915
8916Local<Value> Promise::Result() {
8917 auto promise = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8918 i::Isolate* i_isolate = promise->GetIsolate();
8919 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, Promise, Result);
8920 auto js_promise = i::Cast<i::JSPromise>(promise);
8921 Utils::ApiCheck(js_promise->status() != kPending, "v8_Promise_Result",
8922 "Promise is still pending");
8923 return Utils::ToLocal(i::direct_handle(js_promise->result(), i_isolate));
8924}
8925
8926Promise::PromiseState Promise::State() {
8927 auto promise = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
8928 API_RCS_SCOPE(promise->GetIsolate(), Promise, Status);
8929 auto js_promise = i::Cast<i::JSPromise>(promise);
8930 return static_cast<PromiseState>(js_promise->status());
8931}

8937void Promise::MarkAsSilent() {
8938 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this)->set_is_silent(true);
8939}

8974CompiledWasmModule::CompiledWasmModule(
8975 std::shared_ptr<internal::wasm::NativeModule> native_module,
8976 const char* source_url, size_t url_length)
8977 : native_module_(std::move(native_module)),
8978 source_url_(source_url, url_length) {
8979 CHECK_NOT_NULL(native_module_);
8980}
8981
8982OwnedBuffer CompiledWasmModule::Serialize() {
8983#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
8984 TRACE_EVENT0("v8.wasm", "wasm.SerializeModule");
8985 i::wasm::WasmSerializer wasm_serializer(native_module_.get());
8986 size_t buffer_size = wasm_serializer.GetSerializedNativeModuleSize();
8987 std::unique_ptr<uint8_t[]> buffer(new uint8_t[buffer_size]);
8988 if (!wasm_serializer.SerializeNativeModule({buffer.get(), buffer_size}))
8989 return {};
8990 return {std::move(buffer), buffer_size};
8991#else
8992 UNREACHABLE();
8993#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
8994}
8995
8996MemorySpan<const uint8_t> CompiledWasmModule::GetWireBytesRef() {
8997#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
8998 base::Vector<const uint8_t> bytes_vec = native_module_->wire_bytes();
8999 return {bytes_vec.begin(), bytes_vec.size()};
9000#else
9001 UNREACHABLE();
9002#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
9003}

9005Local<ArrayBuffer> v8::WasmMemoryObject::Buffer() {

9007 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
9008 i::Isolate* i_isolate = obj->GetIsolate();
9009 return Utils::ToLocal(i::direct_handle(obj->array_buffer(), i_isolate));
9010#else
9011 UNREACHABLE();
9012#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
9013}
9014
9015CompiledWasmModule WasmModuleObject::GetCompiledModule() {
9016#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
9017 auto obj = i::Cast<i::WasmModuleObject>(Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this));
9018 auto url = i::direct_handle(i::Cast<i::String>(obj->script()->name()),
9019 obj->GetIsolate());
9020 size_t length;
9021 std::unique_ptr<char[]> cstring = url->ToCString(&length);
9022 return CompiledWasmModule(std::move(obj->shared_native_module()),
9023 cstring.get(), length);
9024#else
9025 UNREACHABLE();
9026#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
9027}
9028
9029MaybeLocal<WasmModuleObject> WasmModuleObject::FromCompiledModule(
9030 Isolate* v8_isolate, const CompiledWasmModule& compiled_module) {
9031#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
9032 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9033 i::DirectHandle<i::WasmModuleObject> module_object =
9034 i::wasm::GetWasmEngine()->ImportNativeModule(
9035 i_isolate, compiled_module.native_module_,
9036 base::VectorOf(compiled_module.source_url()));
9037 return Utils::ToLocal(module_object);
9038#else
9039 UNREACHABLE();
9040#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
9041}
9042
9043MaybeLocal<WasmModuleObject> WasmModuleObject::Compile(
9044 Isolate* v8_isolate, MemorySpan<const uint8_t> wire_bytes) {
9045#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
9046 base::OwnedVector<const uint8_t> bytes = base::OwnedCopyOf(wire_bytes);
9047 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9048 if (!i::wasm::IsWasmCodegenAllowed(i_isolate, i_isolate->native_context())) {
9049 return MaybeLocal<WasmModuleObject>();
9050 }
9051 i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::WasmModuleObject> maybe_compiled;
9052 {
9053 i::wasm::ErrorThrower thrower(i_isolate, "WasmModuleObject::Compile()");
9054 auto enabled_features =
9055 i::wasm::WasmEnabledFeatures::FromIsolate(i_isolate);
9056 // TODO(14179): Provide an API method that supports compile options.
9057 maybe_compiled = i::wasm::GetWasmEngine()->SyncCompile(
9058 i_isolate, enabled_features, i::wasm::CompileTimeImports{}, &thrower,
9059 std::move(bytes));
9060 }
9061 CHECK_EQ(maybe_compiled.is_null(), i_isolate->has_exception());
9062 if (maybe_compiled.is_null()) {
9063 return MaybeLocal<WasmModuleObject>();
9064 }
9065 return Utils::ToLocal(maybe_compiled.ToHandleChecked());
9066#else
9067 Utils::ApiCheck(false, "WasmModuleObject::Compile",
9068 "WebAssembly support is not enabled");
9069 UNREACHABLE();
9070#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
9071}

9074Local<WasmMemoryMapDescriptor> WasmMemoryMapDescriptor::New(
9075 v8::Isolate* v8_isolate, WasmMemoryMapDescriptor::WasmFileDescriptor fd) {
9076#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY

9079 i::Handle<i::WasmMemoryMapDescriptor> result =
9080 i::WasmMemoryMapDescriptor::NewFromFileDescriptor(i_isolate, fd);
9081 return Utils::ToLocal(result);
9082#else
9083 Utils::ApiCheck(false, "WasmMemoryMapDescriptor::New",
9084 "WebAssembly support is not enabled");
9085 UNREACHABLE();
9086#endif
9087}
9088
9089void* v8::ArrayBuffer::Allocator::Reallocate(void* data, size_t old_length,
9090 size_t new_length) {
9091 if (old_length == new_length) return data;
9092 uint8_t* new_data =
9093 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(AllocateUninitialized(new_length));
9094 if (new_data == nullptr) return nullptr;
9095 size_t bytes_to_copy = std::min(old_length, new_length);
9096 memcpy(new_data, data, bytes_to_copy);
9097 if (new_length > bytes_to_copy) {
9098 memset(new_data + bytes_to_copy, 0, new_length - bytes_to_copy);
9099 }
9100 Free(data, old_length);
9101 return new_data;
9102}

9106 return new ArrayBufferAllocator();
9107}

9118std::shared_ptr<i::BackingStore> ToInternal(
9119 std::shared_ptr<i::BackingStoreBase> backing_store) {
9120 return std::static_pointer_cast<i::BackingStore>(backing_store);
9121}

9123
9124Maybe<bool> v8::ArrayBuffer::Detach(v8::Local<v8::Value> key) {
9125 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
9126 i::Isolate* i_isolate = obj->GetIsolate();
9127 Utils::ApiCheck(obj->is_detachable(), "v8::ArrayBuffer::Detach",
9128 "Only detachable ArrayBuffers can be detached");
9129 Local<Context> context =
9130 reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate)->GetCurrentContext();
9131 // TODO(verwaest): Remove this case after forcing the embedder to enter the
9132 // context.
9133 if (context.IsEmpty()) {
9134 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
9135 if (key.IsEmpty()) {
9136 i::JSArrayBuffer::Detach(obj).Check();
9137 } else {
9138 auto i_key = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
9139 constexpr bool kForceForWasmMemory = false;
9140 i::JSArrayBuffer::Detach(obj, kForceForWasmMemory, i_key).Check();
9141 }
9142 return Just(true);
9143 }
9144 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT(i_isolate, context, ArrayBuffer, Detach, i::HandleScope);
9145 if (!key.IsEmpty()) {
9146 auto i_key = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
9147 constexpr bool kForceForWasmMemory = false;
9148 has_exception =
9149 i::JSArrayBuffer::Detach(obj, kForceForWasmMemory, i_key).IsNothing();
9150 } else {
9151 has_exception = i::JSArrayBuffer::Detach(obj).IsNothing();
9152 }
9153 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
9154 return Just(true);
9155}
9156
9157void v8::ArrayBuffer::Detach() { Detach(Local<Value>()).Check(); }
9158
9159void v8::ArrayBuffer::SetDetachKey(v8::Local<v8::Value> key) {
9160 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
9161 auto i_key = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*key);
9162 obj->set_detach_key(*i_key);
9163}
