9173namespace {
9174i::InitializedFlag GetInitializedFlag(
9175 BackingStoreInitializationMode initialization_mode) {
9176 switch (initialization_mode) {
9177 case BackingStoreInitializationMode::kUninitialized:
9178 return i::InitializedFlag::kUninitialized;
9179 case BackingStoreInitializationMode::kZeroInitialized:
9180 return i::InitializedFlag::kZeroInitialized;
9181 }
9182 UNREACHABLE();
9183}
9184} // namespace
9185
9186MaybeLocal<ArrayBuffer> v8::ArrayBuffer::MaybeNew(
9187 Isolate* isolate, size_t byte_length,
9188 BackingStoreInitializationMode initialization_mode) {
9189 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
9190 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, ArrayBuffer, MaybeNew);
9191 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
9192 i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::JSArrayBuffer> result =
9193 i_isolate->factory()->NewJSArrayBufferAndBackingStore(
9194 byte_length, GetInitializedFlag(initialization_mode));
9195
9196 i::DirectHandle<i::JSArrayBuffer> array_buffer;
9197 if (!result.ToHandle(&array_buffer)) {
9198 return MaybeLocal<ArrayBuffer>();
9199 }
9200
9201 return Utils::ToLocal(array_buffer);
9202}
9203
9204Local<ArrayBuffer> v8::ArrayBuffer::New(
9205 Isolate* v8_isolate, size_t byte_length,
9206 BackingStoreInitializationMode initialization_mode) {
9207 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9208 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, ArrayBuffer, New);
9209 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
9210 i::MaybeDirectHandle<i::JSArrayBuffer> result =
9211 i_isolate->factory()->NewJSArrayBufferAndBackingStore(
9212 byte_length, GetInitializedFlag(initialization_mode));
9213
9214 i::DirectHandle<i::JSArrayBuffer> array_buffer;
9215 if (!result.ToHandle(&array_buffer)) {
9216 i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(i_isolate, "v8::ArrayBuffer::New");
9217 }
9218
9219 return Utils::ToLocal(array_buffer);
9220}
9221
9222Local<ArrayBuffer> v8::ArrayBuffer::New(
9223 Isolate* v8_isolate, std::shared_ptr<BackingStore> backing_store) {
9224 CHECK_IMPLIES(backing_store->ByteLength() != 0,
9225 backing_store->Data() != nullptr);
9226 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9227 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, ArrayBuffer, New);
9228 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
9229 std::shared_ptr<i::BackingStore> i_backing_store(
9230 ToInternal(std::move(backing_store)));
9231 Utils::ApiCheck(
9232 !i_backing_store->is_shared(), "v8_ArrayBuffer_New",
9233 "Cannot construct ArrayBuffer with a BackingStore of SharedArrayBuffer");
9234 i::DirectHandle<i::JSArrayBuffer> obj =
9235 i_isolate->factory()->NewJSArrayBuffer(std::move(i_backing_store));
9236 return Utils::ToLocal(obj);
9237}
9238
9239std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore> v8::ArrayBuffer::NewBackingStore(
9240 Isolate* v8_isolate, size_t byte_length,
9241 BackingStoreInitializationMode initialization_mode) {
9242 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9243 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, ArrayBuffer, NewBackingStore);
9244 CHECK_LE(byte_length, i::JSArrayBuffer::kMaxByteLength);
9245 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
9246 std::unique_ptr<i::BackingStoreBase> backing_store =
9247 i::BackingStore::Allocate(i_isolate, byte_length,
9248 i::SharedFlag::kNotShared,
9249 GetInitializedFlag(initialization_mode));
9250 if (!backing_store) {
9251 i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(i_isolate,
9252 "v8::ArrayBuffer::NewBackingStore");
9253 }
9254 return std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore>(
9255 static_cast<v8::BackingStore*>(backing_store.release()));
9256}
9257
9258std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore> v8::ArrayBuffer::NewBackingStore(
9259 void* data, size_t byte_length, v8::BackingStore::DeleterCallback deleter,
9260 void* deleter_data) {
9261 CHECK_LE(byte_length, i::JSArrayBuffer::kMaxByteLength);
9262#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
9263 Utils::ApiCheck(!data || i::Sandbox::current()->Contains(data),
9264 "v8_ArrayBuffer_NewBackingStore",
9265 "When the V8 Sandbox is enabled, ArrayBuffer backing stores "
9266 "must be allocated inside the sandbox address space. Please "
9267 "use an appropriate ArrayBuffer::Allocator to allocate these "
9268 "buffers, or disable the sandbox.");
9269#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
9270
9271 std::unique_ptr<i::BackingStoreBase> backing_store =
9272 i::BackingStore::WrapAllocation(data, byte_length, deleter, deleter_data,
9273 i::SharedFlag::kNotShared);
9274 return std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore>(
9275 static_cast<v8::BackingStore*>(backing_store.release()));
9276}
9277
9278// static
9279std::unique_ptr<BackingStore> v8::ArrayBuffer::NewResizableBackingStore(
9280 size_t byte_length, size_t max_byte_length) {
9281 Utils::ApiCheck(byte_length <= max_byte_length,
9282 "v8::ArrayBuffer::NewResizableBackingStore",
9283 "Cannot construct resizable ArrayBuffer, byte_length must be "
9284 "<= max_byte_length");
9285 Utils::ApiCheck(
9286 byte_length <= i::JSArrayBuffer::kMaxByteLength,
9287 "v8::ArrayBuffer::NewResizableBackingStore",
9288 "Cannot construct resizable ArrayBuffer, requested length is too big");
9289
9290 size_t page_size, initial_pages, max_pages;
9291 if (i::JSArrayBuffer::GetResizableBackingStorePageConfiguration(
9292 nullptr, byte_length, max_byte_length, i::kDontThrow, &page_size,
9293 &initial_pages, &max_pages)
9294 .IsNothing()) {
9295 i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(nullptr,
9296 "v8::ArrayBuffer::NewResizableBackingStore");
9297 }
9298 std::unique_ptr<i::BackingStoreBase> backing_store =
9299 i::BackingStore::TryAllocateAndPartiallyCommitMemory(
9300 nullptr, byte_length, max_byte_length, page_size, initial_pages,
9301 max_pages, i::WasmMemoryFlag::kNotWasm, i::SharedFlag::kNotShared);
9302 if (!backing_store) {
9303 i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(nullptr,
9304 "v8::ArrayBuffer::NewResizableBackingStore");
9305 }
9306 return std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore>(
9307 static_cast<v8::BackingStore*>(backing_store.release()));
9308}
9309
9310Local<ArrayBuffer> v8::ArrayBufferView::Buffer() {
9311 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
9312 i::Isolate* i_isolate = obj->GetIsolate();
9313 if (i::IsJSDataView(*obj)) {
9314 i::DirectHandle<i::JSDataView> data_view(i::Cast<i::JSDataView>(*obj),
9315 i_isolate);
9316 DCHECK(IsJSArrayBuffer(data_view->buffer()));
9317 return Utils::ToLocal(i::direct_handle(
9318 i::Cast<i::JSArrayBuffer>(data_view->buffer()), i_isolate));
9319 } else if (i::IsJSRabGsabDataView(*obj)) {
9320 i::DirectHandle<i::JSRabGsabDataView> data_view(
9321 i::Cast<i::JSRabGsabDataView>(*obj), i_isolate);
9322 DCHECK(IsJSArrayBuffer(data_view->buffer()));
9323 return Utils::ToLocal(i::direct_handle(
9324 i::Cast<i::JSArrayBuffer>(data_view->buffer()), i_isolate));
9325 } else {
9326 DCHECK(IsJSTypedArray(*obj));
9327 return Utils::ToLocal(i::Cast<i::JSTypedArray>(*obj)->GetBuffer());
9328 }
9329}
9330
9331size_t v8::ArrayBufferView::CopyContents(void* dest, size_t byte_length) {
9332 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
9333 size_t bytes_to_copy = std::min(byte_length, self->byte_length());
9334 if (bytes_to_copy) {
9335 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
9336 const char* source;
9337 if (i::IsJSTypedArray(*self)) {
9338 i::Tagged<i::JSTypedArray> array = i::Cast<i::JSTypedArray>(*self);
9339 source = reinterpret_cast<char*>(array->DataPtr());
9340 } else {
9341 DCHECK(i::IsJSDataView(*self) || i::IsJSRabGsabDataView(*self));
9342 i::Tagged<i::JSDataViewOrRabGsabDataView> data_view =
9343 i::Cast<i::JSDataViewOrRabGsabDataView>(*self);
9344 source = reinterpret_cast<char*>(data_view->data_pointer());
9345 }
9346 memcpy(dest, source, bytes_to_copy);
9347 }
9348 return bytes_to_copy;
9349}
9350
9351v8::MemorySpan<uint8_t> v8::ArrayBufferView::GetContents(
9352 v8::MemorySpan<uint8_t> storage) {
9353 internal::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
9354 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
9355 if (self->WasDetached()) {
9356 return {};
9357 }
9358 if (internal::IsJSTypedArray(*self)) {
9359 i::Tagged<i::JSTypedArray> typed_array = i::Cast<i::JSTypedArray>(*self);
9360 if (typed_array->is_on_heap()) {
9361 // The provided storage does not have enough capacity for the content of
9362 // the TypedArray.
9363 size_t bytes_to_copy = self->byte_length();
9364 CHECK_LE(bytes_to_copy, storage.size());
9365 const uint8_t* source =
9366 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(typed_array->DataPtr());
9367 memcpy(reinterpret_cast<void*>(storage.data()), source, bytes_to_copy);
9368 return {storage.data(), bytes_to_copy};
9369 }
9370 // The TypedArray already has off-heap storage, just return a view on it.
9371 return {reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(typed_array->DataPtr()),
9372 typed_array->GetByteLength()};
9373 }
9374 if (i::IsJSDataView(*self)) {
9375 i::Tagged<i::JSDataView> data_view = i::Cast<i::JSDataView>(*self);
9376 return {reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(data_view->data_pointer()),
9377 data_view->byte_length()};
9378 }
9379 // Other types of ArrayBufferView always have an off-heap storage.
9380 DCHECK(i::IsJSRabGsabDataView(*self));
9381 i::Tagged<i::JSRabGsabDataView> data_view =
9382 i::Cast<i::JSRabGsabDataView>(*self);
9383 return {reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(data_view->data_pointer()),
9384 data_view->GetByteLength()};
9385}
9386
9387bool v8::ArrayBufferView::HasBuffer() const {
9388 auto self = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
9389 if (!IsJSTypedArray(*self)) return true;
9390 auto typed_array = i::Cast<i::JSTypedArray>(self);
9391 return !typed_array->is_on_heap();
9392}
9393
9394size_t v8::ArrayBufferView::ByteOffset() {
9395 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
9396 return obj->WasDetached() ? 0 : obj->byte_offset();
9397}
9398
9399size_t v8::ArrayBufferView::ByteLength() {
9400 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
9401 i::Tagged<i::JSArrayBufferView> obj = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
9402 if (obj->WasDetached()) {
9403 return 0;
9404 }
9405 if (i::IsJSTypedArray(obj)) {
9406 return i::Cast<i::JSTypedArray>(obj)->GetByteLength();
9407 }
9408 if (i::IsJSDataView(obj)) {
9409 return i::Cast<i::JSDataView>(obj)->byte_length();
9410 }
9411 return i::Cast<i::JSRabGsabDataView>(obj)->GetByteLength();
9412}
9413
9414size_t v8::TypedArray::Length() {
9415 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
9416 i::Tagged<i::JSTypedArray> obj = *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
9417 return obj->WasDetached() ? 0 : obj->GetLength();
9418}
9419
9420static_assert(v8::TypedArray::kMaxByteLength == i::JSTypedArray::kMaxByteLength,
9421 "v8::TypedArray::kMaxByteLength must match "
9422 "i::JSTypedArray::kMaxByteLength");
9423
9424#define TYPED_ARRAY_NEW(Type, type, TYPE, ctype) \

9426 size_t byte_offset, size_t length) { \
9427 i::Isolate* i_isolate = \
9428 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*array_buffer)->GetIsolate(); \
9429 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, Type##Array, New); \
9430 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate); \
9431 if (!Utils::ApiCheck(length <= kMaxLength, \
9432 "v8::" #Type \
9433 "Array::New(Local<ArrayBuffer>, size_t, size_t)", \
9434 "length exceeds max allowed value")) { \
9435 return Local<Type##Array>(); \
9436 } \
9437 auto buffer = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*array_buffer); \
9438 i::DirectHandle<i::JSTypedArray> obj = \
9439 i_isolate->factory()->NewJSTypedArray(i::kExternal##Type##Array, \
9440 buffer, byte_offset, length); \
9441 return Utils::ToLocal##Type##Array(obj); \
9442 } \
9443 Local<Type##Array> Type##Array::New( \
9444 Local<SharedArrayBuffer> shared_array_buffer, size_t byte_offset, \
9445 size_t length) { \
9446 i::Isolate* i_isolate = \
9447 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*shared_array_buffer)->GetIsolate(); \
9448 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, Type##Array, New); \
9449 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate); \
9450 if (!Utils::ApiCheck( \
9451 length <= kMaxLength, \
9452 "v8::" #Type \
9453 "Array::New(Local<SharedArrayBuffer>, size_t, size_t)", \
9454 "length exceeds max allowed value")) { \
9455 return Local<Type##Array>(); \
9456 } \
9457 auto buffer = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*shared_array_buffer); \
9458 i::DirectHandle<i::JSTypedArray> obj = \
9459 i_isolate->factory()->NewJSTypedArray(i::kExternal##Type##Array, \
9460 buffer, byte_offset, length); \
9461 return Utils::ToLocal##Type##Array(obj); \
9462 }

9465#undef TYPED_ARRAY_NEW

9538
9539Local<SharedArrayBuffer> v8::SharedArrayBuffer::New(
9540 Isolate* v8_isolate, size_t byte_length,
9541 BackingStoreInitializationMode initialization_mode) {
9542 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9543 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, SharedArrayBuffer, New);
9544 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
9545
9546 std::unique_ptr<i::BackingStore> backing_store =
9547 i::BackingStore::Allocate(i_isolate, byte_length, i::SharedFlag::kShared,
9548 GetInitializedFlag(initialization_mode));
9549
9550 if (!backing_store) {
9551 // TODO(jbroman): It may be useful in the future to provide a MaybeLocal
9552 // version that throws an exception or otherwise does not crash.
9553 i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(i_isolate, "v8::SharedArrayBuffer::New");
9554 }
9555
9556 i::DirectHandle<i::JSArrayBuffer> obj =
9557 i_isolate->factory()->NewJSSharedArrayBuffer(std::move(backing_store));
9558 return Utils::ToLocalShared(obj);
9559}
9560
9561Local<SharedArrayBuffer> v8::SharedArrayBuffer::New(
9562 Isolate* v8_isolate, std::shared_ptr<BackingStore> backing_store) {
9563 CHECK_IMPLIES(backing_store->ByteLength() != 0,
9564 backing_store->Data() != nullptr);
9565 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9566 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, SharedArrayBuffer, New);
9567 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
9568 std::shared_ptr<i::BackingStore> i_backing_store(ToInternal(backing_store));
9569 Utils::ApiCheck(
9570 i_backing_store->is_shared(), "v8::SharedArrayBuffer::New",
9571 "Cannot construct SharedArrayBuffer with BackingStore of ArrayBuffer");
9572 i::DirectHandle<i::JSArrayBuffer> obj =
9573 i_isolate->factory()->NewJSSharedArrayBuffer(std::move(i_backing_store));
9574 return Utils::ToLocalShared(obj);
9575}
9576
9577std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore> v8::SharedArrayBuffer::NewBackingStore(
9578 Isolate* v8_isolate, size_t byte_length,
9579 BackingStoreInitializationMode initialization_mode) {
9580 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9581 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, SharedArrayBuffer, NewBackingStore);
9582 Utils::ApiCheck(
9583 byte_length <= i::JSArrayBuffer::kMaxByteLength,
9584 "v8::SharedArrayBuffer::NewBackingStore",
9585 "Cannot construct SharedArrayBuffer, requested length is too big");
9586 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
9587 std::unique_ptr<i::BackingStoreBase> backing_store =
9588 i::BackingStore::Allocate(i_isolate, byte_length, i::SharedFlag::kShared,
9589 GetInitializedFlag(initialization_mode));
9590 if (!backing_store) {
9591 i::V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(i_isolate,
9592 "v8::SharedArrayBuffer::NewBackingStore");
9593 }
9594 return std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore>(
9595 static_cast<v8::BackingStore*>(backing_store.release()));
9596}
9597
9598std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore> v8::SharedArrayBuffer::NewBackingStore(
9599 void* data, size_t byte_length, v8::BackingStore::DeleterCallback deleter,
9600 void* deleter_data) {
9601 CHECK_LE(byte_length, i::JSArrayBuffer::kMaxByteLength);
9602 std::unique_ptr<i::BackingStoreBase> backing_store =
9603 i::BackingStore::WrapAllocation(data, byte_length, deleter, deleter_data,
9604 i::SharedFlag::kShared);
9605 return std::unique_ptr<v8::BackingStore>(
9606 static_cast<v8::BackingStore*>(backing_store.release()));
9607}

9676
9677Local<Number> v8::Number::New(Isolate* v8_isolate, double value) {
9678 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9679 DCHECK_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
9680 if (std::isnan(value)) {
9681 // Introduce only canonical NaN value into the VM, to avoid signaling NaNs.
9682 value = std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
9683 }
9684 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> result = i_isolate->factory()->NewNumber(value);
9685 return Utils::NumberToLocal(result);
9686}
9687
9688Local<Integer> v8::Integer::New(Isolate* v8_isolate, int32_t value) {
9689 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9690 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
9691 if (i::Smi::IsValid(value)) {
9692 return Utils::IntegerToLocal(
9693 i::DirectHandle<i::Object>(i::Smi::FromInt(value), i_isolate));
9694 }
9695 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> result = i_isolate->factory()->NewNumber(value);
9696 return Utils::IntegerToLocal(result);
9697}
9698
9699Local<Integer> v8::Integer::NewFromUnsigned(Isolate* v8_isolate,
9700 uint32_t value) {
9701 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
9702 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
9703 bool fits_into_int32_t = (value & (1 << 31)) == 0;
9704 if (fits_into_int32_t) {
9705 return Integer::New(v8_isolate, static_cast<int32_t>(value));
9706 }
9707 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> result = i_isolate->factory()->NewNumber(value);
9708 return Utils::IntegerToLocal(result);
9709}

9725MaybeLocal<BigInt> v8::BigInt::NewFromWords(Local<Context> context,
9726 int sign_bit, int word_count,
9727 const uint64_t* words) {
9728 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
9729 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT(i_isolate, context, BigInt, NewFromWords,
9730 InternalEscapableScope);

9732 i::BigInt::FromWords64(i_isolate, sign_bit, word_count, words);

9749
9750void BigInt::ToWordsArray(int* sign_bit, int* word_count,
9751 uint64_t* words) const {
9752 // TODO(saelo): consider migrating the public API to also use uint32_t or
9753 // size_t for length and count values.
9754 uint32_t unsigned_word_count = *word_count;
9755 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this)->ToWordsArray64(sign_bit, &unsigned_word_count,
9756 words);
9757 *word_count = base::checked_cast<int>(unsigned_word_count);
9758}
9759
9760int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryImpl(
9761 int64_t change_in_bytes) {
9762 // Try to check for unreasonably large or small values from the embedder.
9763 static constexpr int64_t kMaxReasonableBytes = int64_t(1) << 60;
9764 static constexpr int64_t kMinReasonableBytes = -kMaxReasonableBytes;
9765 static_assert(kMaxReasonableBytes >= i::JSArrayBuffer::kMaxByteLength);
9766 CHECK(kMinReasonableBytes <= change_in_bytes &&
9767 change_in_bytes < kMaxReasonableBytes);
9768
9769 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
9770 const uint64_t amount =
9771 i_isolate->heap()->UpdateExternalMemory(change_in_bytes);
9772
9773 if (change_in_bytes <= 0) {
9774 return amount;
9775 }
9776
9777 if (amount > i_isolate->heap()->external_memory_limit_for_interrupt()) {
9778 HandleExternalMemoryInterrupt();
9779 }
9780 return amount;
9781}
9782
9783void Isolate::HandleExternalMemoryInterrupt() {
9784 i::Heap* heap = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this)->heap();
9785 if (heap->gc_state() != i::Heap::NOT_IN_GC) return;
9786 heap->HandleExternalMemoryInterrupt();
9787}
9788
9789IsolateGroup::IsolateGroup(i::IsolateGroup*&& isolate_group)
9790 : isolate_group_(isolate_group) {
9791 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(isolate_group_);
9792}
9793
9794IsolateGroup::~IsolateGroup() {
9795 if (isolate_group_) {
9796 isolate_group_->Release();
9797#ifdef DEBUG
9798 isolate_group_ = nullptr;
9799#endif
9800 }
9801}
9802
9803// static
9804IsolateGroup IsolateGroup::GetDefault() {
9805 return IsolateGroup(i::IsolateGroup::AcquireDefault());
9806}
9807
9808// static
9809bool IsolateGroup::CanCreateNewGroups() {
9810 return i::IsolateGroup::CanCreateNewGroups();
9811}
9812
9813// static
9814IsolateGroup IsolateGroup::Create() {
9815 return IsolateGroup(i::IsolateGroup::New());
9816}
9817
9818IsolateGroup::IsolateGroup(IsolateGroup&& other) {
9819 isolate_group_ = other.isolate_group_;
9820 other.isolate_group_ = nullptr;
9821}
9822
9823IsolateGroup& v8::IsolateGroup::operator=(IsolateGroup&& other) {
9824 if (this == &other) {
9825 return *this;
9826 }
9827
9828 if (isolate_group_) {
9829 isolate_group_->Release();
9830 }
9831 isolate_group_ = other.isolate_group_;
9832 other.isolate_group_ = nullptr;
9833 return *this;
9834}
9835
9836HeapProfiler* Isolate::GetHeapProfiler() {
9837 i::HeapProfiler* heap_profiler =
9838 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this)->heap_profiler();
9839 return reinterpret_cast<HeapProfiler*>(heap_profiler);
9840}

9862v8::Local<v8::Context> Isolate::GetCurrentContext() {
9863 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
9864 i::Tagged<i::Context> context = i_isolate->context();
9865 if (context.is_null()) return Local<Context>();
9866 i::Tagged<i::NativeContext> native_context = context->native_context();
9867 return Utils::ToLocal(i::direct_handle(native_context, i_isolate));
9868}

9870// TODO(ishell): rename back to GetEnteredContext().
9871v8::Local<v8::Context> Isolate::GetEnteredOrMicrotaskContext() {
9872 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
9873 i::DirectHandle<i::NativeContext> last =
9874 i_isolate->handle_scope_implementer()->LastEnteredContext();
9875 if (last.is_null()) return Local<Context>();
9876 return Utils::ToLocal(last);
9877}

9884
9885v8::MaybeLocal<v8::Data> Isolate::GetCurrentHostDefinedOptions() {
9886 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
9887 i::DirectHandle<i::Script> script;
9888 if (!i_isolate->CurrentReferrerScript().ToHandle(&script)) {
9889 return MaybeLocal<v8::Data>();
9890 }
9891 return ToApiHandle<Data>(
9892 i::direct_handle(script->host_defined_options(), i_isolate));
9893}
9894
9895v8::Local<Value> Isolate::ThrowError(v8::Local<v8::String> message) {
9896 return ThrowException(v8::Exception::Error(message));
9897}
9898
9899v8::Local<Value> Isolate::ThrowException(v8::Local<v8::Value> value) {
9900 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
9901 ENTER_V8_BASIC(i_isolate);
9902 i_isolate->clear_internal_exception();
9903 // If we're passed an empty handle, we throw an undefined exception
9904 // to deal more gracefully with out of memory situations.
9905 if (value.IsEmpty()) {
9906 i_isolate->Throw(i::ReadOnlyRoots(i_isolate).undefined_value());
9907 } else {
9908 i_isolate->Throw(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*value));
9909 }
9910 return v8::Undefined(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
9911}
9912
9913bool Isolate::HasPendingException() {
9914 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
9915 if (i_isolate->has_exception()) {
9916 return true;
9917 }
9918 v8::TryCatch* try_catch_handler =
9919 i_isolate->thread_local_top()->try_catch_handler_;
9920 return try_catch_handler && try_catch_handler->HasCaught();
9921}

10003bool Isolate::IsExecutionTerminating() {
10004 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10005#ifdef DEBUG
10006 // This method might be called on a thread that's not bound to any Isolate
10007 // and thus pointer compression schemes might have cage base value unset.
10008 // Read-only roots accessors contain type DCHECKs which require access to
10009 // V8 heap in order to check the object type. So, allow heap access here
10010 // to let the checks work.
10011 i::PtrComprCageAccessScope ptr_compr_cage_access_scope(i_isolate);
10012#endif // DEBUG
10013 return i_isolate->is_execution_terminating();
10014}

10035
10036void Isolate::RequestGarbageCollectionForTesting(GarbageCollectionType type) {
10037 Utils::ApiCheck(i::v8_flags.expose_gc,
10038 "v8::Isolate::RequestGarbageCollectionForTesting",
10039 "Must use --expose-gc");
10040 if (type == kMinorGarbageCollection) {
10041 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this)->heap()->CollectGarbage(
10042 i::NEW_SPACE, i::GarbageCollectionReason::kTesting,
10043 kGCCallbackFlagForced);
10044 } else {
10045 DCHECK_EQ(kFullGarbageCollection, type);
10046 reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this)->heap()->PreciseCollectAllGarbage(
10047 i::GCFlag::kNoFlags, i::GarbageCollectionReason::kTesting,
10048 kGCCallbackFlagForced);
10049 }
10050}
10051
10052void Isolate::RequestGarbageCollectionForTesting(GarbageCollectionType type,
10053 StackState stack_state) {
10054 std::optional<i::EmbedderStackStateScope> stack_scope;
10055 if (type == kFullGarbageCollection) {
10056 stack_scope.emplace(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this)->heap(),
10057 i::EmbedderStackStateOrigin::kExplicitInvocation,
10058 stack_state);
10059 }
10060 RequestGarbageCollectionForTesting(type);
10061}

10092
10093Isolate::CreateParams::CreateParams() = default;
10094
10095Isolate::CreateParams::~CreateParams() = default;
10096
10097// static
10098// This is separate so that tests can provide a different |isolate|.
10099void Isolate::Initialize(Isolate* v8_isolate,
10100 const v8::Isolate::CreateParams& params) {
10101 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
10102 TRACE_EVENT_CALL_STATS_SCOPED(i_isolate, "v8", "V8.IsolateInitialize");
10103 if (auto allocator = params.array_buffer_allocator_shared) {
10104 CHECK(params.array_buffer_allocator == nullptr ||
10105 params.array_buffer_allocator == allocator.get());
10106 i_isolate->set_array_buffer_allocator(allocator.get());
10107 i_isolate->set_array_buffer_allocator_shared(std::move(allocator));
10108 } else {
10109 CHECK_NOT_NULL(params.array_buffer_allocator);
10110 i_isolate->set_array_buffer_allocator(params.array_buffer_allocator);
10111 }
10112 if (params.snapshot_blob != nullptr) {
10113 i_isolate->set_snapshot_blob(params.snapshot_blob);
10114 } else {
10115 i_isolate->set_snapshot_blob(i::Snapshot::DefaultSnapshotBlob());
10116 }
10117
10118 if (params.fatal_error_callback) {
10119 v8_isolate->SetFatalErrorHandler(params.fatal_error_callback);
10120 }
10121
10122#if __clang__
10123#pragma clang diagnostic push
10124#pragma clang diagnostic ignored "-Wdeprecated-declarations"
10125#endif
10126 if (params.oom_error_callback) {
10127 v8_isolate->SetOOMErrorHandler(params.oom_error_callback);
10128 }
10129#if __clang__
10130#pragma clang diagnostic pop
10131#endif
10132
10133 if (params.counter_lookup_callback) {
10134 v8_isolate->SetCounterFunction(params.counter_lookup_callback);
10135 }
10136
10137 if (params.create_histogram_callback) {
10138 v8_isolate->SetCreateHistogramFunction(params.create_histogram_callback);
10139 }
10140
10141 if (params.add_histogram_sample_callback) {
10142 v8_isolate->SetAddHistogramSampleFunction(
10143 params.add_histogram_sample_callback);
10144 }
10145
10146 i_isolate->set_api_external_references(params.external_references);
10147 i_isolate->set_allow_atomics_wait(params.allow_atomics_wait);
10148
10149 i_isolate->heap()->ConfigureHeap(params.constraints, params.cpp_heap);
10150 if (params.constraints.stack_limit() != nullptr) {
10151 uintptr_t limit =
10152 reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(params.constraints.stack_limit());
10153 i_isolate->stack_guard()->SetStackLimit(limit);
10154 }
10155
10156 // TODO(v8:2487): Once we got rid of Isolate::Current(), we can remove this.
10157 Isolate::Scope isolate_scope(v8_isolate);
10158 if (i_isolate->snapshot_blob() == nullptr) {
10159 FATAL(
10160 "V8 snapshot blob was not set during initialization. This can mean "
10161 "that the snapshot blob file is corrupted or missing.");
10162 }
10163 if (!i::Snapshot::Initialize(i_isolate)) {
10164 // If snapshot data was provided and we failed to deserialize it must
10165 // have been corrupted.
10166 FATAL(
10167 "Failed to deserialize the V8 snapshot blob. This can mean that the "
10168 "snapshot blob file is corrupted or missing.");
10169 }
10170
10171 {
10172 // Set up code event handlers. Needs to be after i::Snapshot::Initialize
10173 // because that is where we add the isolate to WasmEngine.
10174 auto code_event_handler = params.code_event_handler;
10175 if (code_event_handler) {
10176 v8_isolate->SetJitCodeEventHandler(kJitCodeEventEnumExisting,
10177 code_event_handler);
10178 }
10179 }
10180
10181 i_isolate->set_embedder_wrapper_type_index(
10182 params.embedder_wrapper_type_index);
10183 i_isolate->set_embedder_wrapper_object_index(
10184 params.embedder_wrapper_object_index);
10185
10186 if (!i::V8::GetCurrentPlatform()
10187 ->GetForegroundTaskRunner(v8_isolate)
10188 ->NonNestableTasksEnabled()) {
10189 FATAL(
10190 "The current platform's foreground task runner does not have "
10191 "non-nestable tasks enabled. The embedder must provide one.");
10192 }
10193}
10194
10195Isolate* Isolate::New(const Isolate::CreateParams& params) {
10196 return Isolate::New(IsolateGroup::GetDefault(), params);
10197}
10198
10199Isolate* Isolate::New(const IsolateGroup& group,
10200 const Isolate::CreateParams& params) {
10201 Isolate* v8_isolate = Allocate(group);
10202 Initialize(v8_isolate, params);
10203 return v8_isolate;
10204}

10206void Isolate::Dispose() {
10207 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10208 if (!Utils::ApiCheck(!i_isolate->IsInUse(), "v8::Isolate::Dispose()",
10209 "Disposing the isolate that is entered by a thread")) {
10210 return;
10211 }
10212 i::Isolate::Delete(i_isolate);
10213}

10286
10287Isolate::DisallowJavascriptExecutionScope::DisallowJavascriptExecutionScope(
10288 Isolate* v8_isolate,
10289 Isolate::DisallowJavascriptExecutionScope::OnFailure on_failure)
10290 : v8_isolate_(v8_isolate), on_failure_(on_failure) {
10291 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
10292 switch (on_failure_) {
10293 case CRASH_ON_FAILURE:
10294 i::DisallowJavascriptExecution::Open(i_isolate, &was_execution_allowed_);
10295 break;
10296 case THROW_ON_FAILURE:
10297 i::ThrowOnJavascriptExecution::Open(i_isolate, &was_execution_allowed_);
10298 break;
10299 case DUMP_ON_FAILURE:
10300 i::DumpOnJavascriptExecution::Open(i_isolate, &was_execution_allowed_);
10301 break;
10302 }
10303}
10304
10305Isolate::DisallowJavascriptExecutionScope::~DisallowJavascriptExecutionScope() {
10306 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate_);
10307 switch (on_failure_) {
10308 case CRASH_ON_FAILURE:
10309 i::DisallowJavascriptExecution::Close(i_isolate, was_execution_allowed_);
10310 break;
10311 case THROW_ON_FAILURE:
10312 i::ThrowOnJavascriptExecution::Close(i_isolate, was_execution_allowed_);
10313 break;
10314 case DUMP_ON_FAILURE:
10315 i::DumpOnJavascriptExecution::Close(i_isolate, was_execution_allowed_);
10316 break;
10317 }
10318}
10319
10320Isolate::AllowJavascriptExecutionScope::AllowJavascriptExecutionScope(
10321 Isolate* v8_isolate)
10322 : v8_isolate_(v8_isolate) {
10323 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
10324 i::AllowJavascriptExecution::Open(i_isolate, &was_execution_allowed_assert_);
10325 i::NoThrowOnJavascriptExecution::Open(i_isolate,
10326 &was_execution_allowed_throws_);
10327 i::NoDumpOnJavascriptExecution::Open(i_isolate, &was_execution_allowed_dump_);
10328}
10329
10330Isolate::AllowJavascriptExecutionScope::~AllowJavascriptExecutionScope() {
10331 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate_);
10332 i::AllowJavascriptExecution::Close(i_isolate, was_execution_allowed_assert_);
10333 i::NoThrowOnJavascriptExecution::Close(i_isolate,
10334 was_execution_allowed_throws_);
10335 i::NoDumpOnJavascriptExecution::Close(i_isolate, was_execution_allowed_dump_);
10336}
10337
10338Isolate::SuppressMicrotaskExecutionScope::SuppressMicrotaskExecutionScope(
10339 Isolate* v8_isolate, MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue)
10340 : i_isolate_(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate)),
10341 microtask_queue_(microtask_queue
10342 ? static_cast<i::MicrotaskQueue*>(microtask_queue)
10343 : i_isolate_->default_microtask_queue()) {
10344 i_isolate_->thread_local_top()->IncrementCallDepth<true>(this);
10345 microtask_queue_->IncrementMicrotasksSuppressions();
10346}
10347
10348Isolate::SuppressMicrotaskExecutionScope::~SuppressMicrotaskExecutionScope() {
10349 microtask_queue_->DecrementMicrotasksSuppressions();
10350 i_isolate_->thread_local_top()->DecrementCallDepth(this);
10351}

10360Local<Value> Isolate::GetContinuationPreservedEmbedderData() {
10361 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10362#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
10363 return ToApiHandle<Object>(i::direct_handle(
10364 i_isolate->isolate_data()->continuation_preserved_embedder_data(),
10365 i_isolate));
10366#else // V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
10367 return v8::Undefined(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(i_isolate));
10368#endif // V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA

10370
10371void Isolate::SetContinuationPreservedEmbedderData(Local<Value> data) {
10372#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
10373 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10374 if (data.IsEmpty())
10375 data = v8::Undefined(reinterpret_cast<v8::Isolate*>(this));
10376 i_isolate->isolate_data()->set_continuation_preserved_embedder_data(
10377 *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*data));
10378#endif // V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
10379}
10380
10381void Isolate::GetHeapStatistics(HeapStatistics* heap_statistics) {
10382 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10383 i::Heap* heap = i_isolate->heap();
10384
10385 heap->FreeMainThreadLinearAllocationAreas();
10386
10387 // The order of acquiring memory statistics is important here. We query in
10388 // this order because of concurrent allocation: 1) used memory 2) comitted
10389 // physical memory 3) committed memory. Therefore the condition used <=
10390 // committed physical <= committed should hold.
10391 heap_statistics->used_global_handles_size_ = heap->UsedGlobalHandlesSize();
10392 heap_statistics->total_global_handles_size_ = heap->TotalGlobalHandlesSize();
10393 DCHECK_LE(heap_statistics->used_global_handles_size_,
10394 heap_statistics->total_global_handles_size_);
10395
10396 heap_statistics->used_heap_size_ = heap->SizeOfObjects();
10397 heap_statistics->total_physical_size_ = heap->CommittedPhysicalMemory();
10398 heap_statistics->total_heap_size_ = heap->CommittedMemory();
10399
10400 heap_statistics->total_available_size_ = heap->Available();
10401
10402 // TODO(dinfuehr): Right now used <= committed physical does not hold. Fix
10403 // this and add DCHECK.
10404 DCHECK_LE(heap_statistics->used_heap_size_,
10405 heap_statistics->total_heap_size_);
10406
10407 heap_statistics->total_heap_size_executable_ =
10408 heap->CommittedMemoryExecutable();
10409 heap_statistics->heap_size_limit_ = heap->MaxReserved();
10410 // TODO(7424): There is no public API for the {WasmEngine} yet. Once such an
10411 // API becomes available we should report the malloced memory separately. For
10412 // now we just add the values, thereby over-approximating the peak slightly.
10413 heap_statistics->malloced_memory_ =
10414 i_isolate->allocator()->GetCurrentMemoryUsage() +
10415 i_isolate->string_table()->GetCurrentMemoryUsage();
10416 // On 32-bit systems backing_store_bytes() might overflow size_t temporarily
10417 // due to concurrent array buffer sweeping.
10418 heap_statistics->external_memory_ =
10419 i_isolate->heap()->backing_store_bytes() < SIZE_MAX
10420 ? static_cast<size_t>(i_isolate->heap()->backing_store_bytes())
10421 : SIZE_MAX;
10422 heap_statistics->peak_malloced_memory_ =
10423 i_isolate->allocator()->GetMaxMemoryUsage();
10424 heap_statistics->number_of_native_contexts_ = heap->NumberOfNativeContexts();
10425 heap_statistics->number_of_detached_contexts_ =
10426 heap->NumberOfDetachedContexts();
10427 heap_statistics->does_zap_garbage_ = i::heap::ShouldZapGarbage();
10428
10429#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
10430 heap_statistics->malloced_memory_ +=
10431 i::wasm::GetWasmEngine()->allocator()->GetCurrentMemoryUsage();
10432 heap_statistics->peak_malloced_memory_ +=
10433 i::wasm::GetWasmEngine()->allocator()->GetMaxMemoryUsage();
10434#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
10435}
10436
10437size_t Isolate::NumberOfHeapSpaces() {
10438 return i::LAST_SPACE - i::FIRST_SPACE + 1;
10439}
10440
10441bool Isolate::GetHeapSpaceStatistics(HeapSpaceStatistics* space_statistics,
10442 size_t index) {
10443 if (!space_statistics) return false;
10444 if (!i::Heap::IsValidAllocationSpace(static_cast<i::AllocationSpace>(index)))
10445 return false;
10446
10447 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10448 i::Heap* heap = i_isolate->heap();
10449
10450 heap->FreeMainThreadLinearAllocationAreas();
10451
10452 i::AllocationSpace allocation_space = static_cast<i::AllocationSpace>(index);
10453 space_statistics->space_name_ = i::ToString(allocation_space);
10454
10455 if (allocation_space == i::RO_SPACE) {
10456 // RO_SPACE memory is shared across all isolates and accounted for
10457 // elsewhere.
10458 space_statistics->space_size_ = 0;
10459 space_statistics->space_used_size_ = 0;
10460 space_statistics->space_available_size_ = 0;
10461 space_statistics->physical_space_size_ = 0;
10462 } else {
10463 i::Space* space = heap->space(static_cast<int>(index));
10464 space_statistics->space_size_ = space ? space->CommittedMemory() : 0;
10465 space_statistics->space_used_size_ = space ? space->SizeOfObjects() : 0;
10466 space_statistics->space_available_size_ = space ? space->Available() : 0;
10467 space_statistics->physical_space_size_ =
10468 space ? space->CommittedPhysicalMemory() : 0;
10469 }
10470 return true;
10471}
10472
10473size_t Isolate::NumberOfTrackedHeapObjectTypes() {
10474 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10475 i::Heap* heap = i_isolate->heap();
10476 return heap->NumberOfTrackedHeapObjectTypes();
10477}
10478
10479bool Isolate::GetHeapObjectStatisticsAtLastGC(
10480 HeapObjectStatistics* object_statistics, size_t type_index) {
10481 if (!object_statistics) return false;
10482 if (V8_LIKELY(!i::TracingFlags::is_gc_stats_enabled())) return false;
10483
10484 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10485 i::Heap* heap = i_isolate->heap();
10486 if (type_index >= heap->NumberOfTrackedHeapObjectTypes()) return false;
10487
10488 const char* object_type;
10489 const char* object_sub_type;
10490 size_t object_count = heap->ObjectCountAtLastGC(type_index);
10491 size_t object_size = heap->ObjectSizeAtLastGC(type_index);
10492 if (!heap->GetObjectTypeName(type_index, &object_type, &object_sub_type)) {
10493 // There should be no objects counted when the type is unknown.
10494 DCHECK_EQ(object_count, 0U);
10495 DCHECK_EQ(object_size, 0U);
10496 return false;
10497 }
10498
10499 object_statistics->object_type_ = object_type;
10500 object_statistics->object_sub_type_ = object_sub_type;
10501 object_statistics->object_count_ = object_count;
10502 object_statistics->object_size_ = object_size;
10503 return true;
10504}
10505
10506bool Isolate::GetHeapCodeAndMetadataStatistics(
10507 HeapCodeStatistics* code_statistics) {
10508 if (!code_statistics) return false;
10509
10510 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10511 i_isolate->heap()->CollectCodeStatistics();
10512
10513 code_statistics->code_and_metadata_size_ =
10514 i_isolate->code_and_metadata_size();
10515 code_statistics->bytecode_and_metadata_size_ =
10516 i_isolate->bytecode_and_metadata_size();
10517 code_statistics->external_script_source_size_ =
10518 i_isolate->external_script_source_size();
10519 code_statistics->cpu_profiler_metadata_size_ =
10520 i::CpuProfiler::GetAllProfilersMemorySize(i_isolate);
10521
10522 return true;
10523}

10539void Isolate::GetStackSample(const RegisterState& state, void** frames,
10540 size_t frames_limit, SampleInfo* sample_info) {
10541 RegisterState regs = state;
10542 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10543 if (i::TickSample::GetStackSample(i_isolate, &regs,
10544 i::TickSample::kSkipCEntryFrame, frames,
10545 frames_limit, sample_info)) {
10546 return;
10547 }
10548 sample_info->frames_count = 0;
10549 sample_info->vm_state = OTHER;
10550 sample_info->external_callback_entry = nullptr;
10551}

10618
10619void Isolate::EnqueueMicrotask(Local<Function> v8_function) {
10620 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10621 auto function = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*v8_function);
10622 i::DirectHandle<i::NativeContext> handler_context;
10623 if (!i::JSReceiver::GetContextForMicrotask(function).ToHandle(
10624 &handler_context))
10625 handler_context = i_isolate->native_context();
10626 MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue = handler_context->microtask_queue();
10627 if (microtask_queue) microtask_queue->EnqueueMicrotask(this, v8_function);
10628}

10632 i_isolate->default_microtask_queue()->EnqueueMicrotask(this, callback, data);
10633}

10693
10694void Isolate::LowMemoryNotification() {
10695 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10696 {
10697 i::NestedTimedHistogramScope idle_notification_scope(
10698 i_isolate->counters()->gc_low_memory_notification());
10699 TRACE_EVENT0("v8", "V8.GCLowMemoryNotification");
10700#ifdef DEBUG
10701 // This method might be called on a thread that's not bound to any Isolate
10702 // and thus pointer compression schemes might have cage base value unset.
10703 // Read-only roots accessors contain type DCHECKs which require access to
10704 // V8 heap in order to check the object type. So, allow heap access here
10705 // to let the checks work.
10706 i::PtrComprCageAccessScope ptr_compr_cage_access_scope(i_isolate);
10707#endif // DEBUG
10708 i_isolate->heap()->CollectAllAvailableGarbage(
10709 i::GarbageCollectionReason::kLowMemoryNotification);
10710 }
10711}
10712
10713int Isolate::ContextDisposedNotification(bool dependant_context) {
10714 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10715#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
10716 if (!dependant_context) {
10717 if (!i_isolate->context().is_null()) {
10718 // We left the current context, we can abort all WebAssembly compilations
10719 // of that context.
10720 // A handle scope for the native context.
10721 i::HandleScope handle_scope(i_isolate);
10722 i::wasm::GetWasmEngine()->DeleteCompileJobsOnContext(
10723 i_isolate->native_context());
10724 }
10725 }
10726#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
10727 i_isolate->AbortConcurrentOptimization(i::BlockingBehavior::kDontBlock);
10728 // TODO(ahaas): move other non-heap activity out of the heap call.
10729 return i_isolate->heap()->NotifyContextDisposed(dependant_context);
10730}

10747void Isolate::MemoryPressureNotification(MemoryPressureLevel level) {

10751 ? i_isolate->thread_manager()->IsLockedByCurrentThread()
10752 : i::ThreadId::Current() == i_isolate->thread_id();

10797void Isolate::GetCodeRange(void** start, size_t* length_in_bytes) {
10798 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10799 const base::AddressRegion& code_region = i_isolate->heap()->code_region();

10802}

10804void Isolate::GetEmbeddedCodeRange(const void** start,
10805 size_t* length_in_bytes) {

10809 *length_in_bytes = d.code_size();
10810}
10811
10812JSEntryStubs Isolate::GetJSEntryStubs() {
10813 JSEntryStubs entry_stubs;
10814
10815 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10816 std::array<std::pair<i::Builtin, JSEntryStub*>, 3> stubs = {
10817 {{i::Builtin::kJSEntry, &entry_stubs.js_entry_stub},
10818 {i::Builtin::kJSConstructEntry, &entry_stubs.js_construct_entry_stub},
10819 {i::Builtin::kJSRunMicrotasksEntry,
10820 &entry_stubs.js_run_microtasks_entry_stub}}};
10821 for (auto& pair : stubs) {
10822 i::Tagged<i::Code> js_entry = i_isolate->builtins()->code(pair.first);
10823 pair.second->code.start =
10824 reinterpret_cast<const void*>(js_entry->instruction_start());
10825 pair.second->code.length_in_bytes = js_entry->instruction_size();
10826 }
10827
10828 return entry_stubs;
10829}
10830
10831size_t Isolate::CopyCodePages(size_t capacity, MemoryRange* code_pages_out) {
10832#if !defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_64_BIT) && !defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM)
10833 // Not implemented on other platforms.
10834 UNREACHABLE();
10835#else
10836
10837 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10838 std::vector<MemoryRange>* code_pages = i_isolate->GetCodePages();
10839
10840 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(code_pages);
10841
10842 // Copy as many elements into the output vector as we can. If the
10843 // caller-provided buffer is not big enough, we fill it, and the caller can
10844 // provide a bigger one next time. We do it this way because allocation is not
10845 // allowed in signal handlers.
10846 size_t limit = std::min(capacity, code_pages->size());
10847 for (size_t i = 0; i < limit; i++) {
10848 code_pages_out[i] = code_pages->at(i);
10849 }
10850 return code_pages->size();
10851#endif
10852}

10902void Isolate::InstallConditionalFeatures(Local<Context> context) {
10903 v8::HandleScope handle_scope(this);
10904 v8::Context::Scope context_scope(context);
10905 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10906 if (i_isolate->is_execution_terminating()) return;
10907 i_isolate->InstallConditionalFeatures(Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*context));
10908 if (i_isolate->has_exception()) return;
10909#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
10910 i::WasmJs::InstallConditionalFeatures(i_isolate,
10911 Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*context));
10912#endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
10913}

10934bool Isolate::IsDead() {
10935 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10936 return i_isolate->IsDead();
10937}
10938
10939bool Isolate::AddMessageListener(MessageCallback that, Local<Value> data) {
10940 return AddMessageListenerWithErrorLevel(that, kMessageError, data);
10941}
10942
10943bool Isolate::AddMessageListenerWithErrorLevel(MessageCallback that,
10944 int message_levels,
10945 Local<Value> data) {
10946 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10947 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
10948 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
10949 i::Handle<i::ArrayList> list = i_isolate->factory()->message_listeners();
10950 i::DirectHandle<i::FixedArray> listener =
10951 i_isolate->factory()->NewFixedArray(3);
10952 i::DirectHandle<i::Foreign> foreign =
10953 i_isolate->factory()->NewForeign<internal::kMessageListenerTag>(
10954 FUNCTION_ADDR(that));
10955 listener->set(0, *foreign);
10956 listener->set(1, data.IsEmpty()
10957 ? i::ReadOnlyRoots(i_isolate).undefined_value()
10958 : *Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*data));
10959 listener->set(2, i::Smi::FromInt(message_levels));
10960 list = i::ArrayList::Add(i_isolate, list, listener);
10961 i_isolate->heap()->SetMessageListeners(*list);
10962 return true;
10963}
10964
10965void Isolate::RemoveMessageListeners(MessageCallback that) {
10966 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(this);
10967 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
10968 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
10969 i::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
10970 i::Tagged<i::ArrayList> listeners = i_isolate->heap()->message_listeners();
10971 for (int i = 0; i < listeners->length(); i++) {
10972 if (i::IsUndefined(listeners->get(i), i_isolate)) {
10973 continue; // skip deleted ones
10974 }
10975 i::Tagged<i::FixedArray> listener =
10976 i::Cast<i::FixedArray>(listeners->get(i));
10977 i::Tagged<i::Foreign> callback_obj = i::Cast<i::Foreign>(listener->get(0));
10978 if (callback_obj->foreign_address<internal::kMessageListenerTag>() ==
10979 FUNCTION_ADDR(that)) {
10980 listeners->set(i, i::ReadOnlyRoots(i_isolate).undefined_value());
10981 }
10982 }
10983}

11068// static
11069std::unique_ptr<MicrotaskQueue> MicrotaskQueue::New(Isolate* v8_isolate,
11070 MicrotasksPolicy policy) {
11071 auto microtask_queue =
11072 i::MicrotaskQueue::New(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate));
11073 microtask_queue->set_microtasks_policy(policy);
11074 std::unique_ptr<MicrotaskQueue> ret(std::move(microtask_queue));
11075 return ret;
11076}
11077
11078MicrotasksScope::MicrotasksScope(Local<Context> v8_context,
11079 MicrotasksScope::Type type)
11080 : MicrotasksScope(v8_context->GetIsolate(), v8_context->GetMicrotaskQueue(),
11081 type) {}
11082
11083MicrotasksScope::MicrotasksScope(Isolate* v8_isolate,
11084 MicrotaskQueue* microtask_queue,
11085 MicrotasksScope::Type type)
11086 : i_isolate_(reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate)),
11087 microtask_queue_(microtask_queue
11088 ? static_cast<i::MicrotaskQueue*>(microtask_queue)
11089 : i_isolate_->default_microtask_queue()),
11090 run_(type == MicrotasksScope::kRunMicrotasks) {
11091 if (run_) microtask_queue_->IncrementMicrotasksScopeDepth();
11092#ifdef DEBUG
11093 if (!run_) microtask_queue_->IncrementDebugMicrotasksScopeDepth();
11094#endif
11095}
11096
11097MicrotasksScope::~MicrotasksScope() {
11098 if (run_) {
11099 microtask_queue_->DecrementMicrotasksScopeDepth();
11100 if (MicrotasksPolicy::kScoped == microtask_queue_->microtasks_policy() &&
11101 !i_isolate_->has_exception()) {
11102 microtask_queue_->PerformCheckpoint(
11103 reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(i_isolate_));
11104 DCHECK_IMPLIES(i_isolate_->has_exception(),
11105 i_isolate_->is_execution_terminating());
11106 }
11107 }
11108#ifdef DEBUG
11109 if (!run_) microtask_queue_->DecrementDebugMicrotasksScopeDepth();
11110#endif
11111}
11112
11113// static
11114void MicrotasksScope::PerformCheckpoint(Isolate* v8_isolate) {
11115 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
11116 auto* microtask_queue = i_isolate->default_microtask_queue();
11117 microtask_queue->PerformCheckpoint(v8_isolate);
11118}
11119
11120// static
11121int MicrotasksScope::GetCurrentDepth(Isolate* v8_isolate) {
11122 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
11123 auto* microtask_queue = i_isolate->default_microtask_queue();
11124 return microtask_queue->GetMicrotasksScopeDepth();
11125}

11127// static
11128bool MicrotasksScope::IsRunningMicrotasks(Isolate* v8_isolate) {

11130 auto* microtask_queue = i_isolate->default_microtask_queue();
11131 return microtask_queue->IsRunningMicrotasks();

11133
11134String::Utf8Value::Utf8Value(v8::Isolate* v8_isolate, v8::Local<v8::Value> obj,
11135 WriteOptions options)
11136 : str_(nullptr), length_(0) {
11137 if (obj.IsEmpty()) return;
11138 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
11139 Local<Context> context = v8_isolate->GetCurrentContext();
11140 ENTER_V8_BASIC(i_isolate);
11141 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
11142 TryCatch try_catch(v8_isolate);
11143 Local<String> str;
11144 if (!obj->ToString(context).ToLocal(&str)) return;
11145 length_ = str->Utf8LengthV2(v8_isolate);
11146 str_ = i::NewArray<char>(length_ + 1);
11147 int flags = String::WriteFlags::kNullTerminate;
11148 if (options & REPLACE_INVALID_UTF8)
11149 flags |= String::WriteFlags::kReplaceInvalidUtf8;
11150 str->WriteUtf8V2(v8_isolate, str_, length_ + 1, flags);
11151}
11152
11153String::Utf8Value::~Utf8Value() { i::DeleteArray(str_); }
11154
11155String::Value::Value(v8::Isolate* v8_isolate, v8::Local<v8::Value> obj)
11156 : str_(nullptr), length_(0) {
11157 if (obj.IsEmpty()) return;
11158 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
11159 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
11160 Local<Context> context = v8_isolate->GetCurrentContext();
11161 ENTER_V8_BASIC(i_isolate);
11162 TryCatch try_catch(v8_isolate);
11163 Local<String> str;
11164 if (!obj->ToString(context).ToLocal(&str)) return;
11165 length_ = str->Length();
11166 str_ = i::NewArray<uint16_t>(length_ + 1);
11167 str->WriteV2(v8_isolate, 0, length_, str_,
11168 String::WriteFlags::kNullTerminate);
11169}
11170
11171String::Value::~Value() { i::DeleteArray(str_); }
11172
11173String::ValueView::ValueView(v8::Isolate* v8_isolate,
11174 v8::Local<v8::String> str) {
11175 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
11176 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
11177 i::DirectHandle<i::String> i_str = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*str);
11178 i::DirectHandle<i::String> i_flat_str = i::String::Flatten(i_isolate, i_str);
11179
11180 flat_str_ = Utils::ToLocal(i_flat_str);
11181
11182 i::DisallowGarbageCollectionInRelease* no_gc =
11183 new (no_gc_debug_scope_) i::DisallowGarbageCollectionInRelease();
11184 i::String::FlatContent flat_content = i_flat_str->GetFlatContent(*no_gc);
11185 DCHECK(flat_content.IsFlat());
11186 is_one_byte_ = flat_content.IsOneByte();
11187 length_ = flat_content.length();
11188 if (is_one_byte_) {
11189 data8_ = flat_content.ToOneByteVector().data();
11190 } else {
11191 data16_ = flat_content.ToUC16Vector().data();
11192 }
11193}
11194
11195String::ValueView::~ValueView() {
11196 using i::DisallowGarbageCollectionInRelease;
11197 DisallowGarbageCollectionInRelease* no_gc =
11198 reinterpret_cast<DisallowGarbageCollectionInRelease*>(no_gc_debug_scope_);
11199 no_gc->~DisallowGarbageCollectionInRelease();
11200}
11201
11202void String::ValueView::CheckOneByte(bool is_one_byte) const {
11203 if (is_one_byte) {
11204 Utils::ApiCheck(is_one_byte_, "v8::String::ValueView::data8",
11205 "Called the one-byte accessor on a two-byte string view.");
11206 } else {
11207 Utils::ApiCheck(!is_one_byte_, "v8::String::ValueView::data16",
11208 "Called the two-byte accessor on a one-byte string view.");
11209 }
11210}
11211
11212#define DEFINE_ERROR(NAME, name) \
11213 Local<Value> Exception::NAME(v8::Local<v8::String> raw_message, \
11214 v8::Local<v8::Value> raw_options) { \
11215 i::Isolate* i_isolate = i::Isolate::Current(); \
11216 API_RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, NAME, New); \
11217 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate); \
11218 i::Tagged<i::Object> error; \
11219 { \
11220 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate); \
11221 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> options; \
11222 if (!raw_options.IsEmpty()) { \
11223 options = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*raw_options); \
11224 } \
11225 auto message = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*raw_message); \
11226 i::DirectHandle<i::JSFunction> constructor = \
11227 i_isolate->name##_function(); \
11228 error = *i_isolate->factory()->NewError(constructor, message, options); \
11229 } \
11230 return Utils::ToLocal(i::direct_handle(error, i_isolate)); \
11231 }
11232
11233DEFINE_ERROR(RangeError, range_error)
11234DEFINE_ERROR(ReferenceError, reference_error)
11235DEFINE_ERROR(SyntaxError, syntax_error)
11236DEFINE_ERROR(TypeError, type_error)
11237DEFINE_ERROR(WasmCompileError, wasm_compile_error)
11238DEFINE_ERROR(WasmLinkError, wasm_link_error)
11239DEFINE_ERROR(WasmRuntimeError, wasm_runtime_error)
11240DEFINE_ERROR(WasmSuspendError, wasm_suspend_error)
11241DEFINE_ERROR(Error, error)
11242
11243#undef DEFINE_ERROR
11244
11245Local<Message> Exception::CreateMessage(Isolate* v8_isolate,
11246 Local<Value> exception) {
11247 auto obj = Utils::OpenHandle(*exception);
11248 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(v8_isolate);
11249 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
11250 i::HandleScope scope(i_isolate);
11251 return Utils::MessageToLocal(
11252 scope.CloseAndEscape(i_isolate->CreateMessage(obj, nullptr)));
11253}
11254
11255Local<StackTrace> Exception::GetStackTrace(Local<Value> exception) {
11256 auto obj = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*exception);
11257 if (!IsJSObject(*obj)) return {};
11258 auto js_obj = i::Cast<i::JSObject>(obj);
11259 i::Isolate* i_isolate = js_obj->GetIsolate();
11260 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
11261 auto stack_trace = i_isolate->GetDetailedStackTrace(js_obj);
11262 return Utils::StackTraceToLocal(stack_trace);
11263}
11264
11265Maybe<bool> Exception::CaptureStackTrace(Local<Context> context,
11266 Local<Object> object) {
11267 auto i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(context->GetIsolate());
11268 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT(i_isolate, context, Exception, CaptureStackTrace,
11269 i::HandleScope);
11270 auto obj = Utils::OpenHandle(*object);
11271 if (!IsJSObject(*obj)) return Just(false);
11272
11273 auto js_obj = i::Cast<i::JSObject>(obj);
11274
11275 i::FrameSkipMode mode = i::FrameSkipMode::SKIP_FIRST;
11276
11277 auto result = i::ErrorUtils::CaptureStackTrace(i_isolate, js_obj, mode, {});
11278
11279 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> handle;
11280 has_exception = !result.ToHandle(&handle);
11281 RETURN_ON_FAILED_EXECUTION_PRIMITIVE(bool);
11282 return Just(true);
11283}
11284
11285v8::MaybeLocal<v8::Array> v8::Object::PreviewEntries(bool* is_key_value) {
11286 auto object = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(this);
11287 i::Isolate* i_isolate = object->GetIsolate();
11288 if (i_isolate->is_execution_terminating()) return {};
11289 if (IsMap()) {
11290 *is_key_value = true;
11291 return Map::Cast(this)->AsArray();
11292 }
11293 if (IsSet()) {
11294 *is_key_value = false;
11295 return Set::Cast(this)->AsArray();
11296 }
11297
11298 Isolate* v8_isolate = reinterpret_cast<Isolate*>(i_isolate);
11299 ENTER_V8_NO_SCRIPT_NO_EXCEPTION(i_isolate);
11300 if (i::IsJSWeakCollection(*object)) {
11301 *is_key_value = IsJSWeakMap(*object);
11302 return Utils::ToLocal(i::JSWeakCollection::GetEntries(
11303 i::Cast<i::JSWeakCollection>(object), 0));
11304 }
11305 if (i::IsJSMapIterator(*object)) {
11306 auto it = i::Cast<i::JSMapIterator>(object);
11307 MapAsArrayKind const kind =
11308 static_cast<MapAsArrayKind>(it->map()->instance_type());
11309 *is_key_value = kind == MapAsArrayKind::kEntries;
11310 if (!it->HasMore()) return v8::Array::New(v8_isolate);
11311 return Utils::ToLocal(
11312 MapAsArray(i_isolate, it->table(), i::Smi::ToInt(it->index()), kind));
11313 }
11314 if (i::IsJSSetIterator(*object)) {
11315 auto it = i::Cast<i::JSSetIterator>(object);
11316 SetAsArrayKind const kind =
11317 static_cast<SetAsArrayKind>(it->map()->instance_type());
11318 *is_key_value = kind == SetAsArrayKind::kEntries;
11319 if (!it->HasMore()) return v8::Array::New(v8_isolate);
11320 return Utils::ToLocal(
11321 SetAsArray(i_isolate, it->table(), i::Smi::ToInt(it->index()), kind));
11322 }
11323 return v8::MaybeLocal<v8::Array>();
11324}

11501CpuProfilingOptions::CpuProfilingOptions(CpuProfilingMode mode,
11502 unsigned max_samples,
11503 int sampling_interval_us,
11504 MaybeLocal<Context> filter_context)
11505 : mode_(mode),
11506 max_samples_(max_samples),
11507 sampling_interval_us_(sampling_interval_us) {
11508 if (!filter_context.IsEmpty()) {
11509 Local<Context> local_filter_context = filter_context.ToLocalChecked();
11510 filter_context_.Reset(local_filter_context->GetIsolate(),
11511 local_filter_context);
11512 filter_context_.SetWeak();
11513 }
11514}

11520 .address());

11679static i::HeapGraphEdge* ToInternal(const HeapGraphEdge* edge) {
11680 return const_cast<i::HeapGraphEdge*>(
11681 reinterpret_cast<const i::HeapGraphEdge*>(edge));
11682}
11683
11684HeapGraphEdge::Type HeapGraphEdge::GetType() const {
11685 return static_cast<HeapGraphEdge::Type>(ToInternal(this)->type());
11686}
11687
11688Local<Value> HeapGraphEdge::GetName() const {
11689 i::HeapGraphEdge* edge = ToInternal(this);
11690 i::Isolate* i_isolate = edge->isolate();
11691 switch (edge->type()) {
11692 case i::HeapGraphEdge::kContextVariable:
11693 case i::HeapGraphEdge::kInternal:
11694 case i::HeapGraphEdge::kProperty:
11695 case i::HeapGraphEdge::kShortcut:
11696 case i::HeapGraphEdge::kWeak:
11697 return ToApiHandle<String>(
11698 i_isolate->factory()->InternalizeUtf8String(edge->name()));
11699 case i::HeapGraphEdge::kElement:
11700 case i::HeapGraphEdge::kHidden:
11701 return ToApiHandle<Number>(
11702 i_isolate->factory()->NewNumberFromInt(edge->index()));
11703 default:
11704 UNREACHABLE();
11705 }
11706}

11751
11752void HeapSnapshot::Delete() {
11753 i::Isolate* i_isolate = ToInternal(this)->profiler()->isolate();
11754 if (i_isolate->heap_profiler()->GetSnapshotsCount() > 1 ||
11755 i_isolate->heap_profiler()->IsTakingSnapshot()) {
11756 ToInternal(this)->Delete();
11757 } else {
11758 // If this is the last snapshot, clean up all accessory data as well.
11759 i_isolate->heap_profiler()->DeleteAllSnapshots();
11760 }
11761}

11951CFunction::CFunction(const void* address, const CFunctionInfo* type_info)
11952 : address_(address), type_info_(type_info) {
11953 CHECK_NOT_NULL(address_);
11954 CHECK_NOT_NULL(type_info_);
11955}
11956
11957CFunctionInfo::CFunctionInfo(const CTypeInfo& return_info,
11958 unsigned int arg_count, const CTypeInfo* arg_info,
11959 Int64Representation repr)
11960 : return_info_(return_info),
11961 repr_(repr),
11962 arg_count_(arg_count),
11963 arg_info_(arg_info) {
11964 DCHECK(repr == Int64Representation::kNumber ||
11965 repr == Int64Representation::kBigInt);
11966 if (arg_count_ > 0) {
11967 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < arg_count_ - 1; ++i) {
11968 DCHECK(arg_info_[i].GetType() != CTypeInfo::kCallbackOptionsType);
11969 }
11970 }
11971}
11972
11973const CTypeInfo& CFunctionInfo::ArgumentInfo(unsigned int index) const {
11974 DCHECK_LT(index, ArgumentCount());
11975 return arg_info_[index];
11976}

11978namespace api_internal {
11979V8_EXPORT v8::Local<v8::Value> GetFunctionTemplateData(
11980 v8::Isolate* isolate, v8::Local<v8::Data> raw_target) {
11981 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
11982 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> target = Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*raw_target);
11983 if (i::IsFunctionTemplateInfo(*target)) {
11984 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> data(
11985 i::Cast<i::FunctionTemplateInfo>(*target)->callback_data(kAcquireLoad),
11986 i_isolate);
11987 return Utils::ToLocal(data);
11988
11989 } else if (i::IsJSFunction(*target)) {
11990 i::DirectHandle<i::JSFunction> target_func = i::Cast<i::JSFunction>(target);
11991 if (target_func->shared()->IsApiFunction()) {
11992 i::DirectHandle<i::Object> data(
11993 target_func->shared()->api_func_data()->callback_data(kAcquireLoad),
11994 i_isolate);
11995 return Utils::ToLocal(data);
11996 }
11997 }
11998 Utils::ApiCheck(false, "api_internal::GetFunctionTemplateData",
11999 "Target function is not an Api function");
12000 UNREACHABLE();
12001}
12002} // namespace api_internal

12004void FastApiTypedArrayBase::ValidateIndex(size_t index) const {
12005 DCHECK_LT(index, length_);
12006}
12007
12008RegisterState::RegisterState()
12009 : pc(nullptr), sp(nullptr), fp(nullptr), lr(nullptr) {}
12010RegisterState::~RegisterState() = default;
12011
12012RegisterState::RegisterState(const RegisterState& other) { *this = other; }
12013
12014RegisterState& RegisterState::operator=(const RegisterState& other) {
12015 if (&other != this) {
12016 pc = other.pc;
12017 sp = other.sp;
12018 fp = other.fp;
12019 lr = other.lr;
12020 if (other.callee_saved) {
12021 // Make a deep copy if {other.callee_saved} is non-null.
12022 callee_saved =
12023 std::make_unique<CalleeSavedRegisters>(*(other.callee_saved));
12024 } else {
12025 // Otherwise, set {callee_saved} to null to match {other}.
12026 callee_saved.reset();
12027 }
12028 }
12029 return *this;
12030}

12072
12073const size_t HandleScopeImplementer::kEnteredContextsOffset =
12074 offsetof(HandleScopeImplementer, entered_contexts_);
12075
12076void HandleScopeImplementer::FreeThreadResources() { Free(); }
12077
12078char* HandleScopeImplementer::ArchiveThread(char* storage) {
12079 HandleScopeData* current = isolate_->handle_scope_data();
12080 handle_scope_data_ = *current;
12081 MemCopy(storage, this, sizeof(*this));
12082
12083 ResetAfterArchive();
12084 current->Initialize();
12085
12086 return storage + ArchiveSpacePerThread();
12087}
12088
12089int HandleScopeImplementer::ArchiveSpacePerThread() {
12090 return sizeof(HandleScopeImplementer);
12091}
12092
12093char* HandleScopeImplementer::RestoreThread(char* storage) {
12094 MemCopy(this, storage, sizeof(*this));
12095 *isolate_->handle_scope_data() = handle_scope_data_;
12096 return storage + ArchiveSpacePerThread();
12097}
12098
12099void HandleScopeImplementer::IterateThis(RootVisitor* v) {
12100#ifdef DEBUG
12101 bool found_block_before_persistent = false;
12102#endif
12103 // Iterate over all handles in the blocks except for the last.
12104 for (int i = static_cast<int>(blocks()->size()) - 2; i >= 0; --i) {
12105 Address* block = blocks()->at(i);
12106 // Cast possibly-unrelated pointers to plain Address before comparing them
12107 // to avoid undefined behavior.
12108 if (HasPersistentScope() &&
12109 (reinterpret_cast<Address>(
12110 last_handle_before_persistent_block_.value()) <=
12111 reinterpret_cast<Address>(&block[kHandleBlockSize])) &&
12112 (reinterpret_cast<Address>(
12113 last_handle_before_persistent_block_.value()) >=
12114 reinterpret_cast<Address>(block))) {
12115 v->VisitRootPointers(
12116 Root::kHandleScope, nullptr, FullObjectSlot(block),
12117 FullObjectSlot(last_handle_before_persistent_block_.value()));
12118 DCHECK(!found_block_before_persistent);
12119#ifdef DEBUG
12120 found_block_before_persistent = true;
12121#endif
12122 } else {
12123 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kHandleScope, nullptr, FullObjectSlot(block),
12124 FullObjectSlot(&block[kHandleBlockSize]));
12125 }
12126 }
12127
12128 DCHECK_EQ(HasPersistentScope() &&
12129 last_handle_before_persistent_block_.value() != nullptr,
12130 found_block_before_persistent);
12131
12132 // Iterate over live handles in the last block (if any).
12133 if (!blocks()->empty()) {
12134 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kHandleScope, nullptr,
12135 FullObjectSlot(blocks()->back()),
12136 FullObjectSlot(handle_scope_data_.next));
12137 }
12138
12139 saved_contexts_.shrink_to_fit();
12140 if (!saved_contexts_.empty()) {
12141 FullObjectSlot start(&saved_contexts_.front());
12142 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kHandleScope, nullptr, start,
12143 start + static_cast<int>(saved_contexts_.size()));
12144 }
12145 entered_contexts_.shrink_to_fit();
12146 if (!entered_contexts_.empty()) {
12147 FullObjectSlot start(&entered_contexts_.front());
12148 v->VisitRootPointers(Root::kHandleScope, nullptr, start,
12149 start + static_cast<int>(entered_contexts_.size()));
12150 }
12151}
12152
12153void HandleScopeImplementer::Iterate(RootVisitor* v) {
12154 HandleScopeData* current = isolate_->handle_scope_data();
12155 handle_scope_data_ = *current;
12156 IterateThis(v);
12157}
12158
12159char* HandleScopeImplementer::Iterate(RootVisitor* v, char* storage) {
12160 HandleScopeImplementer* scope_implementer =
12161 reinterpret_cast<HandleScopeImplementer*>(storage);
12162 scope_implementer->IterateThis(v);
12163 return storage + ArchiveSpacePerThread();
12164}
12165
12166std::unique_ptr<PersistentHandles> HandleScopeImplementer::DetachPersistent(
12167 Address* first_block) {
12168 std::unique_ptr<PersistentHandles> ph(new PersistentHandles(isolate()));
12169 DCHECK(HasPersistentScope());
12170 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(first_block);
12171
12172 Address* block_start;
12173 do {
12174 block_start = blocks_.back();
12175 ph->blocks_.push_back(blocks_.back());
12176#if DEBUG
12177 ph->ordered_blocks_.insert(blocks_.back());
12178#endif
12179 blocks_.pop_back();
12180 } while (block_start != first_block);
12181
12182 // ph->blocks_ now contains the blocks installed on the HandleScope stack
12183 // since BeginPersistentScope was called, but in reverse order.
12184
12185 // Switch first and last blocks, such that the last block is the one
12186 // that is potentially half full.
12187 DCHECK(!ph->blocks_.empty());
12188 std::swap(ph->blocks_.front(), ph->blocks_.back());
12189
12190 ph->block_next_ = isolate()->handle_scope_data()->next;
12191 block_start = ph->blocks_.back();
12192 ph->block_limit_ = block_start + kHandleBlockSize;
12193
12194 DCHECK_EQ(blocks_.empty(),
12195 last_handle_before_persistent_block_.value() == nullptr);
12196 last_handle_before_persistent_block_.reset();
12197 return ph;
12198}
12199
12200void InvokeAccessorGetterCallback(
12201 v8::Local<v8::Name> property,
12202 const v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
12203 // Leaving JavaScript.
12204 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(info.GetIsolate());
12205 RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kAccessorGetterCallback);
12206
12207 v8::AccessorNameGetterCallback getter;
12208 {
12209 Address arg = i_isolate->isolate_data()->api_callback_thunk_argument();
12210 // Currently we don't call InterceptorInfo callbacks via CallApiGetter.
12211 DCHECK(IsAccessorInfo(Tagged<Object>(arg)));
12212 Tagged<AccessorInfo> accessor_info =
12213 Cast<AccessorInfo>(Tagged<Object>(arg));
12214 getter = reinterpret_cast<v8::AccessorNameGetterCallback>(
12215 accessor_info->getter(i_isolate));
12216
12217 if (V8_UNLIKELY(i_isolate->should_check_side_effects())) {
12218 i::DirectHandle<Object> receiver_check_unsupported;
12219
12220 if (!i_isolate->debug()->PerformSideEffectCheckForAccessor(
12221 direct_handle(accessor_info, i_isolate),
12222 receiver_check_unsupported, ACCESSOR_GETTER)) {
12223 return;
12224 }
12225 }
12226 }
12227 ExternalCallbackScope call_scope(i_isolate, FUNCTION_ADDR(getter),
12228 v8::ExceptionContext::kAttributeGet, &info);
12229 getter(property, info);
12230}
12231
12232namespace {
12233
12234inline Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo> GetTargetFunctionTemplateInfo(
12235 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
12236 Tagged<Object> target = FunctionCallbackArguments::GetTarget(info);
12237 CHECK(IsFunctionTemplateInfo(target));
12238 return Cast<FunctionTemplateInfo>(target);
12239}
12240
12241inline void InvokeFunctionCallback(
12242 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info, CallApiCallbackMode mode) {
12243 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(info.GetIsolate());
12244 RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate, RuntimeCallCounterId::kFunctionCallback);
12245
12246 Tagged<FunctionTemplateInfo> fti = GetTargetFunctionTemplateInfo(info);
12247 v8::FunctionCallback callback =
12248 reinterpret_cast<v8::FunctionCallback>(fti->callback(i_isolate));
12249 switch (mode) {
12250 case CallApiCallbackMode::kGeneric: {
12251 if (V8_UNLIKELY(i_isolate->should_check_side_effects())) {
12252 if (!i_isolate->debug()->PerformSideEffectCheckForCallback(
12253 handle(fti, i_isolate))) {
12254 // Failed side effect check.
12255 return;
12256 }
12257 if (DEBUG_BOOL) {
12258 // Clear raw pointer to ensure it's not accidentally used after
12259 // potential GC in PerformSideEffectCheckForCallback.
12260 fti = {};
12261 }
12262 }
12263 break;
12264 }
12265 case CallApiCallbackMode::kOptimized:
12266 // CallFunction builtin should deoptimize an optimized function when
12267 // side effects checking is enabled, so we don't have to handle side
12268 // effects checking in the optimized version of the builtin.
12269 DCHECK(!i_isolate->should_check_side_effects());
12270 break;
12271 case CallApiCallbackMode::kOptimizedNoProfiling:
12272 // This mode doesn't call InvokeFunctionCallback.
12273 UNREACHABLE();
12274 }
12275
12276 ExternalCallbackScope call_scope(i_isolate, FUNCTION_ADDR(callback),
12277 info.IsConstructCall()
12278 ? v8::ExceptionContext::kConstructor
12279 : v8::ExceptionContext::kOperation,
12280 &info);
12281 callback(info);
12282}
12283} // namespace
12284
12285void InvokeFunctionCallbackGeneric(
12286 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
12287 InvokeFunctionCallback(info, CallApiCallbackMode::kGeneric);
12288}
12289
12290void InvokeFunctionCallbackOptimized(
12291 const v8::FunctionCallbackInfo<v8::Value>& info) {
12292 InvokeFunctionCallback(info, CallApiCallbackMode::kOptimized);
12293}
12294
12295void InvokeFinalizationRegistryCleanupFromTask(
12296 DirectHandle<NativeContext> native_context,
12297 DirectHandle<JSFinalizationRegistry> finalization_registry) {
12298 i::Isolate* i_isolate = finalization_registry->native_context()->GetIsolate();
12299 RCS_SCOPE(i_isolate,
12300 RuntimeCallCounterId::kFinalizationRegistryCleanupFromTask);
12301 // Do not use ENTER_V8 because this is always called from a running
12302 // FinalizationRegistryCleanupTask within V8 and we should not log it as an
12303 // API call. This method is implemented here to avoid duplication of the
12304 // exception handling and microtask running logic in CallDepthScope.
12305 if (i_isolate->is_execution_terminating()) return;
12306 Local<v8::Context> api_context = Utils::ToLocal(native_context);
12307 CallDepthScope<true> call_depth_scope(i_isolate, api_context);
12308 VMState<OTHER> state(i_isolate);
12309 JSFinalizationRegistry::Cleanup(i_isolate, finalization_registry);
12310}

12359
12360template <typename T>
12361bool ValidateFunctionCallbackInfo(const FunctionCallbackInfo<T>& info) {
12362 CHECK_GE(info.Length(), 0);
12363 // Theortically args-length is unlimited, practically we run out of stack
12364 // space. This should guard against accidentally used raw pointers.
12365 CHECK_LE(info.Length(), 0xFFFFF);
12366 if (info.Length() > 0) {
12367 CHECK(info[0]->IsValue());
12368 CHECK(info[info.Length() - 1]->IsValue());
12369 }
12370 auto* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(info.GetIsolate());
12371 CHECK_EQ(i_isolate, Isolate::Current());
12372 CHECK(!i_isolate->GetIncumbentContext().is_null());
12373 CHECK(info.This()->IsValue());
12374 CHECK(info.HolderSoonToBeDeprecated()->IsObject());
12375 CHECK(!info.Data().IsEmpty());
12376 CHECK(info.GetReturnValue().Get()->IsValue());
12377 return true;
12378}
12379
12380template <typename T>
12381bool ValidatePropertyCallbackInfo(const PropertyCallbackInfo<T>& info) {
12382 auto* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(info.GetIsolate());
12383 CHECK_EQ(i_isolate, Isolate::Current());
12384 CHECK(info.This()->IsValue());
12385 CHECK(info.HolderV2()->IsObject());
12386 CHECK(!i::IsJSGlobalObject(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*info.HolderV2())));
12387 // Allow usages of v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<T>::Holder() for now.
12388 // TODO(https://crbug.com/333672197): remove.
12389 START_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
12390 CHECK(info.Holder()->IsObject());
12391 CHECK_IMPLIES(info.Holder() != info.HolderV2(),
12392 i::IsJSGlobalObject(*Utils::OpenDirectHandle(*info.Holder())));
12393 END_ALLOW_USE_DEPRECATED()
12394 i::Tagged<i::Object> key = i::PropertyCallbackArguments::GetPropertyKey(info);
12395 CHECK(i::IsSmi(key) || i::IsName(key));
12396 CHECK(info.Data()->IsValue());
12397 USE(info.ShouldThrowOnError());
12398 if (!std::is_same_v<T, void>) {
12399 CHECK(info.GetReturnValue().Get()->IsValue());
12400 }
12401 return true;
12402}
12403
12404template <>

12406 return ValidateFunctionCallbackInfo(info);
12407}

12445
12446ExternalMemoryAccounter::~ExternalMemoryAccounter() {
12447#ifdef V8_ENABLE_MEMORY_ACCOUNTING_CHECKS
12448 DCHECK_EQ(amount_of_external_memory_, 0U);
12449#endif
12450}
12451
12452ExternalMemoryAccounter::ExternalMemoryAccounter(
12453 ExternalMemoryAccounter&& other) {
12454#if V8_ENABLE_MEMORY_ACCOUNTING_CHECKS
12455 amount_of_external_memory_ =
12456 std::exchange(other.amount_of_external_memory_, 0U);
12457 isolate_ = std::exchange(other.isolate_, nullptr);
12458#endif
12459}
12460
12461ExternalMemoryAccounter& ExternalMemoryAccounter::operator=(
12462 ExternalMemoryAccounter&& other) {
12463#if V8_ENABLE_MEMORY_ACCOUNTING_CHECKS
12464 if (this == &other) {
12465 return *this;
12466 }
12467 DCHECK_EQ(amount_of_external_memory_, 0U);
12468 amount_of_external_memory_ =
12469 std::exchange(other.amount_of_external_memory_, 0U);
12470 isolate_ = std::exchange(other.isolate_, nullptr);
12471#endif
12472 return *this;
12473}
12474
12475void ExternalMemoryAccounter::Increase(Isolate* isolate, size_t size) {
12476#ifdef V8_ENABLE_MEMORY_ACCOUNTING_CHECKS
12477 DCHECK(isolate == isolate_ || isolate_ == nullptr);
12478 isolate_ = isolate;
12479 amount_of_external_memory_ += size;
12480#endif
12481 isolate->AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryImpl(
12482 static_cast<int64_t>(size));
12483}
12484
12485void ExternalMemoryAccounter::Update(Isolate* isolate, int64_t delta) {
12486#ifdef V8_ENABLE_MEMORY_ACCOUNTING_CHECKS
12487 DCHECK(isolate == isolate_ || isolate_ == nullptr);
12488 DCHECK_GE(static_cast<int64_t>(amount_of_external_memory_), -delta);
12489 isolate_ = isolate;
12490 amount_of_external_memory_ += delta;
12491#endif
12492 isolate->AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryImpl(delta);
12493}
12494
12495void ExternalMemoryAccounter::Decrease(Isolate* isolate, size_t size) {
12496 internal::DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
12497 if (size == 0) {
12498 return;
12499 }
12500#ifdef V8_ENABLE_MEMORY_ACCOUNTING_CHECKS
12501 DCHECK_EQ(isolate, isolate_);
12502 DCHECK_GE(amount_of_external_memory_, size);
12503 amount_of_external_memory_ -= size;
12504#endif
12505 i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<i::Isolate*>(isolate);
12506 i_isolate->heap()->UpdateExternalMemory(-static_cast<int64_t>(size));
12507}
12508
12509int64_t
12510ExternalMemoryAccounter::GetTotalAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryForTesting(
12511 const Isolate* isolate) {
12512 const i::Isolate* i_isolate = reinterpret_cast<const i::Isolate*>(isolate);
12513 return i_isolate->heap()->external_memory();
12514}
